{"atom_id": "ig34_p0007_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 7, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This document, together with the SDTM, represents the most recent version of the CDISC submission data domain models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0007_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 7, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "All updates are intended to be backward-compatible.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0007_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 7, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The most significant changes since SDTMIG v3.3 include:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Expanded the scope of the DA domain to include study products in addition to study drugs. See Section 6.3.1, Product Accountability.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.1 Product Accountability"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Grouped specimen-based lab domains (e.g., CP, GF, LB) in Sections 6.3.5.1-6.3.5.9 and added a generic specification for these domains. See Section 6.3.5, Specimen-based Findings Domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.5 Specimen-based Findings Domains"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Expanded the scope of the IS domain for assessments of antigen-induced humoral or cell-mediated immune response. Added 3 new variables (i.e., Binding Agent, Molecule Secreted by Cells, Test Operational Objective). See Section 6.3.5.5, Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Updated the LB domain specification to include the following 10 new variables: Test Condition, Binding Agent, Test Operational Objective, Result Scale, Result Type, Collected Summary Result Type, Lower Limit of Detection, Method Sensitivity, Point in Time Flag, and Planned Duration. See Section 6.3.5.6, Laboratory Test Results.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Decommissioned the Morphology (MO) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Added Cell Phenotyping Findings (CP) and Genomics Findings (GF) domains. See Section 6.3.5.3, Cell Phenotype Findings (CP), and Section 6.3.5.4, Genomics Findings (GF).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Copied in Biospecimen Events (BE), Biospecimen Findings (BS), and Related Specimens (RELSPEC) from the provisional SDTMIG-PGx v1.0 in preparation for its eventual retirement. See Section 6.2.2, Biospecimen Events (BE); Section 6.3.5.2, Biospecimen Findings (BS); and Section 8.8, Related Specimens (RELSPEC).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.2.2 Biospecimen Events (BE)", "§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)", "§8.8 Related Specimens (RELSPEC)"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Updated QRS specifications and assumptions. Also introduced subsections to separate assumptions and examples describing the RS Disease Response use case and the RS Clinical Classifications use case. See Section 6.3.9, Questionnaires, Ratings, and Scales (QRS) Domains (FT, QS, RS).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.9 Questionnaires, Ratings, and Scales (QRS) Domains (FT, QS, RS)"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Updated the Tumor/Lesion (TU and TR) domain assumptions to describe use of indicator questions, disease recurrence conventions, and modeling of location of interest. See Section 6.3.12, Tumor/Lesion Domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.12 Tumor/Lesion Domains"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Expanded the scope of the SC domain to support collection over time. See Section 6.3.10, Subject Characteristics.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Updated guidance and examples for the FA domain. See Section 6.4, Findings About Events or Interventions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.4 Findings About Events or Interventions"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Corrected Core values for the following variables: DSDY, DSSTDY, LBSTREFC, MILOBXFL, and MIBLFL.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Updated Controlled Terminology for applicable variables across all domains, if available.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Removed Appendix C1, Trial Summary Codes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A detailed list of changes between versions is provided in Appendix E, Revision History.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Appendix E Revision History"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Version 3.1 was the first fully implementation-ready version of the CDISC submission data standards that was directly referenced by the US FDA for use in human clinical studies involving drug products.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "However, future improvements and enhancements will continue to be made as sponsors gain more experience submitting data in this format.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Therefore, CDISC will be preparing regular updates to the implementation guide to provide corrections, clarifications, additional domain models, examples, business rules, and conventions for using the standard domain models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because CDISC will produce further documentation for Controlled Terminology as separate publications, sponsors are encouraged to check the CDISC website (https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology) frequently for additional information.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.3 [Relationship to Prior CDISC Documents]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "See Section 4.3, Coding and Controlled Terminology Assumptions, for the most up-to-date information on applying Controlled Terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.3 Coding and Controlled Terminology Assumptions"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
