{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following guidelines may be helpful in reading this document:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0008_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 8, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "First, read the SDTM to gain a general understanding of SDTM concepts.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Next, read Sections 1-3 of this document to review the key concepts for preparing domains and submitting data to regulatory authorities. Refer to Appendix B, Glossary and Abbreviations, as necessary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Appendix B Glossary and Abbreviations"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Read Section 4, Assumptions for Domain Models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4 Assumptions for Domain Models"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Review Section 5, Models for Special-purpose Domains, and Section 6, Domain Models Based on the General Observation Classes, in detail, referring back to Section 4, Assumptions for Domain Models, as directed. See the implementation examples for each domain to gain an understanding of how to apply the domain models for specific types of data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5 Models for Special-purpose Domains", "§6 Domain Models Based on the General Observation Classes", "§4 Assumptions for Domain Models"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Read Section 7, Trial Design Model Datasets, to understand the fundamentals of the Trial Design Model and consider how to apply the concepts for typical protocols.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7 Trial Design Model Datasets"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Review Section 8, Representing Relationships and Data, to learn advanced concepts of how to express relationships between datasets, records, and additional variables not specifically defined in the models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8 Representing Relationships and Data"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Review Section 9, Study References, to learn about occasions when it is necessary to establish study-specific references that will be used in accordance with subject data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§9 Study References"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Finally, review the appendices as appropriate. Appendix C, Controlled Terminology, in particular, describes how CDISC Terminology is centrally managed by the CDISC Controlled Terminology Team. Efforts are made at publication time to ensure all SDTMIG domain/dataset specification tables and/or examples reflect the latest CDISC Terminology; users, however, should refer to https://www.cancer.gov/research/resources/terminology/cdisc as the authoritative source of controlled terminology, as CDISC Controlled Terminology is updated on a quarterly basis.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Appendix C Controlled Terminology"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This implementation guide covers most data collected in human clinical trials, but separate implementation guides provide information about certain data, and should be consulted when needed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following guides are available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/foundational/sdtmig:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The SDTM Implementation Guide: Associated Persons (SDTMIG-AP) provides structures for representing data collected about persons who are not study subjects.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The SDTM Implementation Guide for Medical Devices (SDTMIG-MD) provides structures for data about devices.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4 [How to Read this Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Historically, the SDTM Implementation Guide for Pharmacogenomics/Genetics (SDTMIG-PGx) has provided structures for pharmacogenetic/genomic data and for data about biospecimens. Much of the content of the SDTMIG-PGx has been incorporated into and/or superseded by the SDTMIG v3.4.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "1.4.1 How to Read a Domain Specification", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A domain specification table includes rows for all required and expected variables for a domain and for a set of permissible variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The permissible variables do not include all the variables that are allowed for the domain; they are a set of variables that the SDS Team considered likely to be included.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The columns of the table are:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Variable Name", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For variables that do not include a domain prefix, this name is taken directly from the SDTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For variables with a \"--\" placeholder in the SDTM, the \"--\" is replaced by the 2-character domain code.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Variable Label: A longer name for the variable", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "This may be the same as the label in the SDTM, or it may be customized for the domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Sponsors should create an appropriate label if they include in a dataset an allowable variable not in the domain specification.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Type: One of the 2 SAS datatypes, \"Num\" or \"Char\".  These values are taken directly from the SDTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Controlled Terms", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0009_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 9, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "As noted in the table note, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The controlled terminology might be of a type that would inherently be sponsor-defined.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The controlled terminology might be of a type that could be standardized, but for which a codelist not yet been developed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The controlled terminology might be terminology specified in value-level metadata.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The name of an external code system (e.g., MedDRA) will be listed in plain text.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Codelist", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A hyperlinked codelist name in parentheses indicates that the variable is subject to the CDISC Controlled Terminology in the named codelist.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Multiple hyperlinked codelist names indicate that the variable is subject to 1 or more of the named codelists from CDISC Controlled Terminology. If multiple codelists are in use for a single domain, value-level metadata would indicate where each codelist is applicable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A hyperlinked codelist name and an asterisk (*) indicate that the variable is subject to either the named codelist from the CDISC Controlled Terminology or to an external dictionary. The specific dictionary is identified in the metadata.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Format: \"ISO 8601 datetime or interval\" or \"ISO 8601 duration\" in plain text indicates that the variable values should be formatted in conformance with that standard.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Role: This is taken directly from the SDTM. Note that if a variable is either a Variable Qualifier or a Synonym Qualifier, the SDTM includes the qualified variable, but SDTMIG domain specifications do not.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.4.1 [How to Read a Domain Specification]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "CDISC Notes may include any of the following:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
