{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Derived Records and the use of --DRVFL", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although it is implicit in the general concept of a derived record that there is no collected result (--ORRES should be null), this is not an explicit requirement currently stated in published CDISC material.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This is being evaluated for clarification in a future release of the SDTMIG and/or Model document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Use of --LNKID and --LNKGRP", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The definition of --LNKID says that it is \"used to identify a record,\" and the definition of --LNKGRP says that it is \"used to identify a group of records.\"", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This implies that when setting up a relationship in RELREC, a row where RELTYPE = ONE will have an IDVAR of --LNKID (and not --LNKGRP); a row where RELTYPE = MANY will have an IDVAR of --LNKID (and not --LNKGRP).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The examples in this version of the SDTMIG have not been systematically reviewed to implement this distinction between --LNKID and --LNKGRP.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0010_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 10, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§1.5 [Known Issues]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This distinction between --LNKID and --LNKGRP, and the appropriateness of using other identification variables for linking, will be clarified in a future release of the SDTMIG and/or Model document, and at that time examples in the SDTMIG will be systematically reviewed and updated to reflect that clarification.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2 Fundamentals of the SDTM", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "2  Fundamentals of the SDTM", "heading_level": 1, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "2.1 Observations and Variables", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTMIG for Human Clinical Trials is based on the SDTM's general framework for organizing clinical trial information that is to be submitted to regulatory authorities.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTM is built around the concept of observations collected about subjects who participated in a clinical study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Each observation can be described by a series of variables, corresponding to a row in a dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Each variable can be classified according to its role.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A role determines the type of information conveyed by the variable about each distinct observation and how it can be used.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Variables can be classified into 5 major roles:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Identifier variables, such as those that identify the study, subject, domain, and sequence number of the record", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Topic variables, which specify the focus of the observation (e.g., the name of a lab test)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Timing variables, which describe the timing of the observation (e.g., start date and end date)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Qualifier variables, which include additional illustrative text or numeric values that describe the results or additional traits of the observation (e.g., units, descriptive adjectives)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rule variables, which describe the condition to start, end, branch, or loop in the Trial Design Model", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The set of Qualifier variables can be further categorized into 5 subclasses:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Grouping Qualifiers are used to group together a collection of observations within the same domain. Examples include --CAT and --SCAT.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Result Qualifiers describe the specific results associated with the topic variable in a Findings dataset. They answer the question raised by the topic variable. Result Qualifiers are --ORRES, --STRESC, and --STRESN.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Synonym Qualifiers specify an alternative name for a particular variable in an observation. Examples include --MODIFY and --DECOD, which are equivalent terms for a --TRT or --TERM topic variable, and --TEST and --LOINC, which are equivalent terms for a --TESTCD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Record Qualifiers define additional attributes of the observation record as a whole (rather than describing a particular variable within a record). Examples include --REASND, AESLIFE, and all other serious adverse event (SAE) flag variables in the AE domain; AGE, SEX, and RACE in the DM domain; and --BLFL, --POS, --LOC, --SPEC and --NAM in a Findings domain", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Variable Qualifiers are used to further modify or describe a specific variable within an observation and are only meaningful in the context of the variable they qualify. Examples include --ORRESU, --ORNRHI, and --ORNRLO, all of which are Variable Qualifiers of --ORRES; and --DOSU, which is a Variable Qualifier of --DOSE.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, in the observation, \"Subject 101 had mild nausea starting on study day 6,\" the Topic variable value is the term for the adverse event, \"NAUSEA\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Identifier variable is the subject identifier, \"101\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Timing variable is the study day of the start of the event, which captures the information, \"starting on study day 6,\" whereas an example of a Record Qualifier is the severity, the value for which is \"MILD\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.1 Observations and Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Additional Timing and Qualifier variables could be included to provide the necessary detail to adequately describe an observation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.2 Datasets and Domains", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "2.2 Datasets and Domains", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.2 Datasets and Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Observations about study subjects are normally collected for all subjects in a series of domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.2 Datasets and Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A domain is defined as a collection of logically related observations with a common topic.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.2 Datasets and Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The logic of the relationship may pertain to the scientific subject matter of the data or to its role in the trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.2 Datasets and Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Each domain is represented by a single dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0011_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 11, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.2 Datasets and Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Each domain dataset is distinguished by a unique, 2-character code that should be used consistently throughout the submission.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
