{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "2.3 The General Observation Classes", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Most subject-level observations collected during the study should be represented according to 1 of the 3 SDTM general observation classes: Interventions, Events, or Findings.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The lists of variables allowed to be used in each of these can be found in the SDTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Interventions class captures investigational, therapeutic, and other treatments that are administered to the subject (with some actual or expected physiological effect) either as specified by the study protocol (e.g., exposure to study drug), coincident with the study assessment period (e.g., concomitant medications), or self-administered by the subject (e.g., use of alcohol, tobacco, or caffeine).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Events class captures planned protocol milestones such as randomization and study completion, and occurrences, conditions, or incidents independent of planned study evaluations occurring during the trial (e.g., adverse events) or prior to the trial (e.g., medical history).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Findings class captures the observations resulting from planned evaluations to address specific tests or questions (e.g., laboratory tests, ECG testing, questions listed on questionnaires).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In most cases, the choice of observation class appropriate to a specific collection of data can be easily determined according to these descriptions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The majority of data, which typically consists of measurements or responses to questions, usually at specific visits or time points, will fit the Findings general observation class.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Additional guidance on choosing the appropriate general observation class is provided in Section 8.6.1, Guidelines for Determining the General Observation Class.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.6.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 8.6.1, Guidelines for Determining the General Observation Class", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.6.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "General assumptions for use with all domain models and custom domains based on the general observation classes are described in Section 4, Assumptions for Domain Models; specific assumptions for individual domains are included with the domain models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.3 The General Observation Classes", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 4, Assumptions for Domain Models", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.4 Datasets Other than General Observation Class Domains", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "2.4 Datasets Other than General Observation Class Domains", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.4 Datasets Other than General Observation Class Domains", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTM includes 4 types of datasets other than those based on the general observation classes:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.4 Datasets Other than General Observation Class Domains", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Domain datasets with subject-level data that do not conform to 1 of the 3 general observation classes. These include Demographics (DM), Comments (CO), Subject Elements (SE), and Subject Visits (SV), and are described in Section 5, Models for Special-purpose Domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.4 Datasets Other than General Observation Class Domains", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Trial Design Model (TDM) datasets, which represent information about the study design but do not contain subject data. These include datasets such as Trial Arms (TA) and Trial Elements (TE) and are described in Section 7, Trial Design Model Datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0012_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 12, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.4 Datasets Other than General Observation Class Domains", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Relationship datasets, such as the RELREC and SUPP-- datasets. These are described in Section 8, Representing Relationships and Data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.4 Datasets Other than General Observation Class Domains", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Study Reference datasets include Device Identifiers (DI) and Non-host Organism Identifiers (OI). These provide structures for representing study-specific terminology used in subject data. These are described in Section 9, Study References.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§9"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A sponsor should only submit domain datasets that were actually collected (or directly derived from the collected data) for a given study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Decisions on what data to collect should be based on the scientific objectives of the study, rather than the SDTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that any data collected that will be submitted in an analysis (ADaM) dataset must be traceable to a source in a tabulation (SDTM) dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The collected data for a given study may use standard domains from this and other SDTM implementation guides as well as additional custom domains based on the 3 general observation classes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A list of standard domains is provided in Section 3.2.1, Dataset-level Metadata.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§3.2.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Final domains will be published only in an SDTM implementation guide (this guide or another implementation guide, e.g., SDTMIG for Medical Devices).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Therapeutic-area standards projects and other projects may develop proposals for additional domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Draft versions of these domains may be made available in the CDISC wiki in the SDTM Draft Domains space (https://wiki.cdisc.org/display/SDD/SDTM+Draft+Domains+Home).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "These general rules apply when determining which variables to include in a domain:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Identifier variables, STUDYID, USUBJID, DOMAIN, and --SEQ are required in all domains based on the general observation classes. Other Identifiers may be added as needed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Any Timing variables are permissible for use in any submission dataset based on a general observation class except where restricted by specific domain assumptions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Any additional Qualifier variables from the same general observation class may be added to a domain model except where restricted by specific domain assumptions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Sponsors may not add any variables other than those described in the preceding 3 bullets. The SDTM allows for the inclusion of a sponsor's non-SDTM variables using the Supplemental Qualifiers special-purpose dataset structure, described in Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain. As the SDTM continues to evolve, certain additional standard variables may be added to the general observation classes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Standard variables must not be renamed or modified for novel usage. Their metadata should not be changed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A Permissible variable should be used in an SDTM dataset wherever appropriate.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If a study includes a data item that would be represented in a Permissible variable, then that variable must be included in the SDTM dataset, even if null. Refer to the Define-XML standard (available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/data-exchange/define-xml) for additional details on how to manage no data availability.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.5 The SDTM Standard Domain Models", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If a study did not include a data item that would be represented in a Permissible variable, then that variable should not be included in the SDTM dataset and should not be declared in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "2.6 Creating a New Domain", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This section describes the overall process for creating a custom domain, which must be based on 1 of the 3 SDTM general observation classes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The number of domains submitted should be based on the specific requirements of the study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "To create a custom domain,", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Confirm that none of the existing published domains will fit the need. A custom domain may only be created if the data are different in nature and do not fit into an existing published domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0013_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 13, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Establish a domain of a common topic; that is, where the nature of the data is the same rather than by a specific method of collection (e.g., electrocardiogram). Group and separate data within the domain using --CAT, --SCAT, --METHOD, --SPEC, --LOC, and so on, as appropriate. Examples of different", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "topics are: microbiology, tumor measurements, pathology/histology, vital signs, and physical exam results.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Do not create separate domains based on time; rather, represent both prior and current observations in a domain (e.g., CM for all non-study medications). Note that Adverse Events (AE) and Medical History (MH) are an exception to this best practice because of regulatory reporting needs.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "How collected data are used (e.g., to support analyses and/or efficacy endpoints) must not result in the creation of a custom domain. For example, if blood pressure measurements are endpoints in a hypertension study, they must still be represented in the Vital Signs (VS) domain, as opposed to a custom \"efficacy\" domain. Similarly, if liver function test results are of special interest, they must still be represented in the Laboratory Tests (LB) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Data that were collected on separate CRF modules or pages may fit into an existing domain (e.g., as separate questionnaires into the QS domain, prior and concomitant medications in the CM domain).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If it is necessary to represent relationships between data that are hierarchical in nature (e.g., a parent record must be observed before child records), then establish a domain pair (e.g., MB/MS, PC/PP). Note: Domain pairs have been modeled for microbiology data (MB/MS domains) and pharmacokinetics (PK) data (PC/PP domains) to enable dataset-level relationships to be described using RELREC. The domain pair uses DOMAIN as an identifier to group parent records (e.g., MB) from child records (e.g., MS) and enables a dataset-level relationship to be described in RELREC. Without using DOMAIN to facilitate description of the data relationships, RELREC, as currently defined, could not be used without introducing a variable that would group data like DOMAIN.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Check the SDTM Draft Domains area of the CDISC wiki (https://wiki.cdisc.org/display/SDD/SDTM+Draft+Domains+Home) for proposed domains developed since the last published version of the SDTMIG. These proposed domains may be used as custom domains in a submission.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Look for an existing, relevant domain model to serve as a prototype. If no existing model seems appropriate, choose the general observation class (Interventions, Events, or Findings) that best fits the data by considering the topic of the observation. As illustrated in the following figure, the general approach for selecting variables for a custom domain is:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Select and include the required identifier variables (e.g., STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID, --SEQ) and any permissible Identifier variables from the SDTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Include the topic variable from the identified general observation class (e.g., --TESTCD for Findings) in the SDTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Select and include the relevant qualifier variables from the identified general observation class in the SDTM. Variables belonging to other general observation classes must not be added.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Select and include the applicable timing variables in the SDTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Determine the domain code, one that is not a domain code in the CDISC Controlled Terminology SDTM Domain Abbreviations codelist (see  https://datascience.cancer.gov/resources/cancer-vocabulary/cdisc-terminology). If it is desired to have this domain code be part of CDISC Controlled Terminology, submit a request at https://ncitermform.nci.nih.gov/ncitermform/?version=cdisc. The sponsor-selected, 2-character domain code should be used consistently throughout the submission. AD, AX, AP, SQ, and SA may not be used as custom domain codes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Apply the 2-character domain code to the appropriate variables in the domain. Replace all variable prefixes (shown in the models as \"--\") with the domain code.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Set the order of variables consistent with the order defined in the SDTM for the general observation class.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0014_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 14, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Adjust the labels of the variables only as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted in the newly created domain. Use title case for all labels (title case means to capitalize the first letter of every word except for articles, prepositions, and conjunctions).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0015_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 15, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§2.6 Creating a New Domain", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Ensure that appropriate standard variables are being properly applied by comparing their use in the custom domain to their use in standard domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
