{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTMIG provides standard descriptions of some of the most commonly used data domains, with metadata attributes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "These include descriptive metadata attributes that should be included in a Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In addition, the CDISC domain models include 2 shaded columns that are not sent to the FDA, but which assist sponsors in preparing their datasets:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The CDISC Notes column provides information regarding the relevant use of each variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Core column indicates how a variable is classified (see Section 4.1.5, SDTM Core Designations).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.1.5"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 4.1.5, SDTM Core Designations", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.1.5"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The domain models in Section 6, Domain Models Based on the General Observation Classes, illustrate how to apply the SDTM when creating a specific domain dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In particular, these models illustrate the selection of a subset of the variables offered in 1 of the general observation classes, along with applicable timing variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The models also show how a standard variable from a general observation class should be adjusted to meet the specific content needs of a particular domain, including making the label more meaningful, specifying controlled terminology, and creating domain-specific notes and examples.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.1 Standard Metadata for Dataset Contents and Attributes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Thus, the domain models not only demonstrate how to apply the model for the most common domains but also give insight on how to apply general model concepts to other domains not yet defined by CDISC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2 Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "3.2 Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2 Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Define-XML document that accompanies a submission should also describe each dataset that is included in the submission and describe the natural key structure of each dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2 Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Most studies will include Demographics (DM) and a set of safety domains based on the 3 general observation classes—typically including Exposure (EX), Concomitant and Prior Medications (CM), Adverse Events (AE), Disposition (DS), Medical History (MH), Laboratory Test Results (LB), and Vital Signs (VS).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2 Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "However, choosing which data to submit will depend on the protocol and the needs of the regulatory review division or agency.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2 Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Dataset definition metadata should include the dataset filenames, descriptions, locations, structures, class, purpose, and keys, as shown in Section 3.2.1, Dataset-level Metadata.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§3.2.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0017_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 17, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2 Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In addition, comments can also be provided where needed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
