{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.2.1 Dataset-level Metadata", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Separate Supplemental Qualifier datasets of the form supp--.xpt are required. See Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "3.2.1.1  Primary Keys", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The table in Section 3.2.1, Dataset-level Metadata, shows examples of what a sponsor might submit as variables that comprise the primary key for SDTM datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§3.2.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because the purpose of the Keys column is to aid reviewers in understanding the structure of a dataset, sponsors should list all of the natural keys for the dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "These keys should define uniqueness for records within a dataset, and may define a record sort order.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The identified keys for each dataset should be consistent with the description of the dataset structure as described in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For all the general observation-class domains (and for some special-purpose domains), the --SEQ variable was created so that a unique record could be identified consistently across all of these domains via its use, along with STUDYID, USUBJID, and DOMAIN.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In most domains, --SEQ will be a surrogate key for a set of variables that comprise the natural key.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In certain instances, a supplemental qualifier (SUPP--) variable might also contribute to the natural key of a record for a particular domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "See Section 4.1.9, Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata, for how this should be represented, and for additional information on keys.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.1.9"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Definitions", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A natural key is a set of data (1 or more columns of an entity) that uniquely identifies that entity and distinguishes it from any other row in the table.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The advantage of natural keys is that they exist already; one does not need to introduce a new, \"unnatural\" value to the data schema.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "One of the difficulties in choosing a natural key is that just about any natural key one can think of has the potential to change.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because they have business meaning, natural keys are effectively coupled to the business, and they may need to be reworked when business requirements change.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "An example of such a change in clinical trials data would be the addition of a position or location that becomes a key in a new study, but which was not collected in previous studies.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A surrogate key is a single-part, artificially established identifier for a record.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Surrogate key assignment is a special case of derived data, one where a portion of the primary key is derived.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A surrogate key is immune to changes in business needs.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a033", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In addition, the key depends on only 1 field, so it is compact.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a034", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A common way of deriving surrogate key values is to assign integer values sequentially.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a035", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.1 Primary Keys", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The --SEQ variable in the SDTM datasets is an example of a surrogate key for most datasets; in some instances, however, --SEQ might be a part of a natural key as a replacement for what might have been a key (e.g., a repeat sequence number) in the sponsor's database.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a036", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.2 CDISC Submission Value-level Metadata", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "3.2.1.2  CDISC Submission Value-level Metadata", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a037", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.2 CDISC Submission Value-level Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In general, findings data models are closely related to normalized, relational data models in a vertical structure of 1 record per observation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a038", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.2 CDISC Submission Value-level Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because general observation class data structures are fixed, sometimes information that might appear as columns in a more horizontal (denormalized) structure in presentations and reports will instead be represented as rows in an SDTM Findings structure.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a039", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.2 CDISC Submission Value-level Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because many different types of observations are all presented in the same structure, there is a need to provide additional metadata to describe expected properties that differentiate (e.g., hematology lab results from serum chemistry lab results in terms of data type, standard units, and other attributes).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a040", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.2 CDISC Submission Value-level Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, the Vital Signs (VS) data domain could contain subject records related to diastolic and systolic blood pressure, height, weight, and body mass index (BMI).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0020_a041", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 20, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§3.2.1.2 CDISC Submission Value-level Metadata", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "These data are all submitted in the normalized SDTM", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch02_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0021_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 21, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.2.1 [Findings]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Findings structure of 1 row per vital signs measurement.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0021_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 21, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.2.1 [Findings]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This means that there could be 5 records per subject (1 for each test or measurement) for a single visit or time point, with the parameter names stored in the Test Code/Name variables, and the parameter values stored in result variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0021_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 21, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.2.1 [Findings]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because the unique test code/names could have different attributes (e.g., different origins, roles, definitions) there would be a need to provide value-level metadata for this information.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0021_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 21, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.2.1 [Findings]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The value-level metadata should be provided as a separate section of the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0021_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 21, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§3.2.1 [Findings]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For details on the CDISC Define-XML standard, see https://www.cdisc.org/standards/data-exchange/define-xml.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
