{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.1 [Review Study Data Tabulation Model and Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.1 Review Study Data Tabulation Model and Implementation Guide", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.1 [Review Study Data Tabulation Model and Implementation Guide]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Review the SDTM as well as this complete implementation guide before attempting to use any of the individual domain models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.2 [Relationship to Analysis Datasets]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.2 Relationship to Analysis Datasets", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.2 [Relationship to Analysis Datasets]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Specific guidance on preparing analysis datasets can be found in the CDISC Analysis Data Model (ADaM) Implementation Guide and other ADaM documents, available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/foundational/adam.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3 [Additional Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.3 Additional Timing Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3 [Additional Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Additional Timing variables can be added as needed to a standard domain model based on the 3 general observation classes, except for the cases specified in Assumption 4.4.8, Date and Time Reported in a Domain Based on Findings.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.8"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3 [Additional Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Timing variables can be added to special-purpose domains only where specified in the SDTMIG domain model assumptions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3 [Additional Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Timing variables cannot be added to SUPPQUAL datasets or to RELREC (described in Section 8, Representing Relationships and Data).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.3.1  EPOCH Variable Guidance", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When EPOCH is included in a Findings class domain, it should be based on the --DTC variable, since this is the date/time of the test or, for tests performed on specimens, the date/time of specimen collection.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For observations in Interventions or Events class domains, EPOCH should be based on the --STDTC variable, since this is the start of the intervention or event.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A possible, though unlikely, exception would be a finding based on an interval specimen collection that started in one epoch but ended in another.  --ENDTC might be a more appropriate basis for EPOCH in such a case.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors should not impute EPOCH values, but should, where possible, assign EPOCH values on the basis of CRF instructions and structure, even if EPOCH was not directly collected and date/time data was not collected with sufficient precision to permit assignment of an observation to an EPOCH on the basis of date/time data alone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If it is not possible to determine the epoch of an observation, then EPOCH should be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Methods for assigning EPOCH values can be described in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because EPOCH is a study-design construct, it is not applicable to interventions or events that started before the subject's participation in a study, nor to findings performed before participation in a study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For such records, EPOCH should be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.3.1 [EPOCH Variable Guidance]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that a subject's participation in a study includes screening, which generally occurs before the reference start date (RFSTDTC) in the Demographics (DM) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.4 [Order of the Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.4 Order of the Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.4 [Order of the Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The order of variables in the Define-XML document must reflect the order of variables in the dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.4 [Order of the Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The order of variables in CDISC domain models has been chosen to facilitate the review of the models and application of the models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.4 [Order of the Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Variables for the 3 general observation classes must be ordered with Identifiers variables first, followed by Topic, Qualifier, and Timing variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.4 [Order of the Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Within each role, variables must be ordered as shown in SDTM Sections 3.1.1, The Interventions Observation Class; 3.1.2, The Events Observation Class; 3.1.3, The Findings Observation Class; 3.1.3.1, Findings About Events or Interventions; 3.1.4, Identifiers for All Classes; and 3.1.5, Timing Variables for All Classes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§3.1.1", "§3.1.2", "§3.1.3", "§3.1.3.1", "§3.1.4", "§3.1.5"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.5 SDTM Core Designations", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0022_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 22, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Three categories are specified in the Core column in the domain models:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A Required variable is any variable that is basic to the identification of a data record (i.e., essential key variables and a topic variable) or is necessary to make the record meaningful. Required variables must always be included in the dataset and cannot be null for any record.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "An Expected variable is any variable necessary to make a record useful in the context of a specific domain. Expected variables may contain some null values, but in most cases will not contain null values for every record. When the study does not include the data item for an expected variable, however, a null column must still be included in the dataset, and a comment must be included in the Define-XML document to state that the study does not include the data item.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A Permissible variable should be used in an SDTM dataset wherever appropriate. Although domain specification tables list only some of the identifier, timing, and general observation class variables listed in the SDTM, all are permissible unless specifically restricted in this implementation guide (see Section 2.7, SDTM Variables Not Allowed in the SDTMIG) or by specific domain assumptions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§2.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Domain assumptions that say a Permissible variable is \"generally not used\" do not prohibit use of the variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If a study includes a data item that would be represented in a Permissible variable, then that variable must be included in the SDTM dataset, even if null. Indicate no data were available for that variable in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.5 [SDTM Core Designations]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If a study did not include a data item that would be represented in a Permissible variable, then that variable should not be included in the SDTM dataset and should not be declared in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.6 Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "SDTM datasets are normally named to be consistent with the domain code; for example, the Demographics dataset (DM) is named dm.xpt.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "dm.xpt", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "(See the SDTM Domain Abbreviation codelist, C66734, in CDISC Controlled Terminology (https://www.cancer.gov/research/resources/terminology/cdisc) for standard domain codes).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "C66734", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Exceptions to this rule are described in Section 4.1.7, Splitting Domains, for general observation class datasets and in Section 8, Representing Relationships and Data, for RELREC and SUPP-- datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.1.7", "§8"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In some cases, sponsors may need to define new custom domains and may be concerned that CDISC domain codes defined in the future will conflict with those they choose to use.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "To eliminate any risk of a sponsor using a name that CDISC later determines to have a different meaning, domain codes beginning with the letters X, Y, and Z have been reserved for the creation of custom domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.6 [Additional Guidance on Dataset Naming]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Any letter or number may be used in the second position. Note the use of codes beginning with X, Y, or Z is optional, and not required for custom domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.7 Splitting Domains", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors may choose to split a domain of topically related information into physically separate datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A domain based on a general observation class may be split according to values in --CAT. When a domain is split on --CAT, --CAT must not be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Findings About (FA) domain (see Section 6.4.4, Findings About Events or Interventions) may alternatively be split based on the domain of the value in --OBJ. For example, FACM would store findings about Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM) records. See Section 6.4.2, Naming Findings About Domains, for more details.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.4.4", "§6.4.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following rules must be adhered to when splitting a domain into separate datasets to ensure they can be appended back into 1 domain dataset:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The value of DOMAIN must be consistent across the separate datasets as it would have been if they had not been split (e.g., QS, FA).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "All variables that require a domain prefix (e.g., --TESTCD, --LOC) must use the value of DOMAIN as the prefix value (e.g., QS, FA).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0023_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 23, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--SEQ must be unique within USUBJID for all records across all the split datasets. If there are 1000 records for a USUBJID across the separate datasets, all 1000 records need unique values for --SEQ.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When relationship datasets (e.g., SUPPxx, FAxx, CO, RELREC) relate back to split parent domains, IDVAR would generally be --SEQ. When IDVAR is a value other than --SEQ (e.g., --GRPID, --REFID, --SPID), care should be used to ensure that the parent records across the split datasets have unique values for the variable specified in IDVAR, so that related children records do not accidentally join back to incorrect parent records.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Permissible variables included in one split dataset need not be included in all split datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For domains with 2-letter domain codes (i.e., other than SUPPxx and RELREC), split dataset names can be up to 4 characters in length. For example, if splitting by --CAT, dataset names would be the domain name plus up to 2 additional characters (e.g., QS36 for SF-36). If splitting Findings About by parent domain, then the dataset name would be the domain code, \"FA\", plus the 2-character domain code for parent domain code (e.g., \"FACM\"). The 4-character dataset-name limitation allows the use of a Supplemental Qualifier dataset associated with the split dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Supplemental Qualifier datasets for split domains would also be split. The nomenclature would include the additional 1 to 2 characters used to identify the split dataset (e.g., SUPPQS36, SUPPFACM). The value of RDOMAIN in the SUPP-- datasets would be the 2-character domain code (e.g., QS, FA).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "In RELREC, if a dataset-level relationship is defined for a split Findings About domain, then RDOMAIN may contain the 4-character dataset name, rather than the domain name \"FA\", as shown in the following example.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "relrec.xpt", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "Row | STUDYID | RDOMAIN | USUBJID | IDVAR | IDVARVAL | RELTYPE | RELID", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "1 | ABC | CM |  | CMSPID |  | ONE | 1", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "2 | ABC | FACM |  | FASPID |  | MANY | 1", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "See the SDTM Implementation Guide: Associated Persons (https://www.cdisc.org/standards/foundational/sdtmig/) for the naming of split AP datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "See the SDTM Define-XML specification (https://www.cdisc.org/standards/data-exchange/define-xml) for details regarding metadata representation when a domain is split into different datasets. For additional examples, see the Metadata Submission Guideline (MSG) for SDTMIG (https://www.cdisc.org/standards/foundational/sdtmig/).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0024_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 24, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.7 [Splitting Domains]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Note that submission of split SDTM domains may be subject to additional dataset-splitting conventions as defined by regulators via technical specifications and/or as negotiated with regulatory reviewers.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
