{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors are cautioned to recognize that a derived origin means that all values for that variable were derived, and that collected on the CRF applies to all values as well.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In some cases, both collected and derived values may be reported in the same field.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, some records in a Findings dataset such as Questionnaires (QS) contain values collected from the CRF; other records may contain derived values, such as a total score.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.8.2 [Origin Metadata for Records]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When both derived and collected values are reported in a variable, the origin is to be described using value-level metadata in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.1.9 Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Section 3.2, Using the CDISC Domain Models in Regulatory Submissions – Dataset Metadata, indicates that a sponsor should include in the metadata the variables that contribute to the natural key for a domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§3.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a033", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In a case where a dataset includes a mix of records with different natural keys, the natural key that provides the most granularity is the one that should be provided.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a034", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following example illustrates how to do this, and include a case where a Supplemental Qualifier variable is referenced because it forms part of the natural key.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a035", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Musculoskeletal System Findings (MK) Domain Example", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a036", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsor A chooses the following natural key for the MK domain:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a037", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "STUDYID, USUBJID, VISTNUM, MKTESTCD", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a038", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsor B collects data in such a way that the location (MKLOC and MKLAT) and method (MKMETHOD) variables need to be included in the natural key to identify a unique row.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0026_a039", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 26, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsor B then defines the following natural key for the MK domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "STUDYID, USUBJID, VISITNUM, MKTESTCD, MKLOC, MKLAT, MKMETHOD", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In certain instances a Supplemental Qualifier variable (i.e., a QNAM value; see Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain) might also contribute to the natural key of a record, and therefore needs to be referenced as part of the natural key for a domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The important concept here is that a domain is not limited by physical structure.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A domain may comprise more than 1 physical dataset (e.g., the main domain dataset and its associated Supplemental Qualifiers dataset).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Supplemental Qualifier variables should be referenced in the natural key by using a 2-part name.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The word QNAM must be used as the first part of the name to indicate that the contributing variable exists in a domain-specific SUPP--; the second part is the value of QNAM that ultimately becomes a column reference when the SUPPQUAL records are joined on to the main domain dataset (e.g., QNAM.XVAR when the SUPP-- record has a QNAM of \"XVAR\") .", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, sponsor B might have collected data that used different imaging methods, using imaging devices with different makes and models, and using different hand positions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The sponsor considers the make and model information and hand position to be essential data that contributes to the uniqueness of the test result, and so includes a device identifier (SPDEVID) in the data and creates a Supplemental Qualifier variable for hand position (QNAM = \"MKHNDPOS\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The natural key is then defined as follows:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "STUDYID, USUBJID, SPDEVID, VISITNUM, MKTESTCD, MKLOC, MKLAT, MKMETHOD, QNAM.MKHNDPOS", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "where the notation \"QNAM.MKHNDPOS\" means the Supplemental Qualifier whose QNAM is \"MKHNDPOS\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This approach becomes very useful in a Findings domain when --TESTCD values are \"generic\" and rely on other variables to completely describe the test.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The use of generic test codes helps to create distinct lists of manageable controlled terminology for --TESTCD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In studies where multiple repetitive tests or measurements are being made, for example in a rheumatoid arthritis study where repetitive measurements of bone erosion in the hands and wrists might be made using both X-ray and MRI equipment, the generic MKTEST \"Sharp/Genant Bone Erosion Score\" would be used in combination with other variables to fully identify the result.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Taking just the phalanges, a sponsor might want to express the following in a test in order to make it unique:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Left or right hand", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Phalangeal joint position (which finger, which joint)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rotation of the hand", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Method of measurement (x-ray or MRI)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Machine make and model", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When CDISC Controlled Terminology for a test is not available, and a sponsor creates --TEST and --TESTCD values, trying to encapsulate all information about a test within a unique value of a --TESTCD is not a recommended approach for the following reasons:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "It results in the creation of a potentially large number of test codes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The 8-character values of --TESTCD become less intuitively meaningful.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Multiple test codes are essentially representing the same test or measurement simply to accommodate attributes of a test within the --TESTCD value itself (e.g., to represent a body location at which a measurement was taken).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As a result, the preferred approach would be to use a generic (or simple) test code that requires associated qualifier variables to fully express the test detail.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This approach was used in creating the CDISC Controlled Terminology used in this example:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The MKTESTCD value \"SGBESCR\" is a generic test code, and additional information about the test is provided by separate qualifier variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The variables that completely specify a test may include domain variables and supplemental qualifier variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Expressing the natural key becomes very important in this situation in order to communicate the variables that contribute to the uniqueness of a test.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0027_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 27, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.1.9 [Assigning Natural Keys in the Metadata]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following variables would be used to fully describe the test. The natural key for this domain includes both parent dataset variables and a supplemental qualifier variable that contribute to the natural key of each row and to describe the uniqueness of the test.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
