{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.1 Variable-naming Conventions", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "SDTM variables are named according to a set of conventions, using fragment names (see Appendix D, CDISC Variable-naming Fragments).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Appendix D"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Variables with names ending in \"CD\" are \"short\" versions of associated variables that do not include the \"CD\" suffix (e.g., --TESTCD is the short version of --TEST).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Values of --TESTCD must be limited to 8 characters and cannot start with a number, nor can they contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This is to avoid possible incompatibility with SAS v5 transport files.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This limitation will be in effect until the use of other formats (e.g., Dataset-XML) becomes acceptable to regulatory authorities.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because QNAM serves the same purpose as --TESTCD within supplemental qualifier datasets, values of QNAM are subject to the same restrictions as values of --TESTCD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Values of other \"CD\" variables are not subject to the same restrictions as --TESTCD:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) and TSPARMCD (the companion to TSPARM) are limited to 8 characters and do not have the character restrictions that apply to --TESTCD. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that they will need to serve as variable names.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "ARMCD is limited to 20 characters and does not have the character restrictions that apply to --TESTCD. The maximum length of ARMCD is longer than for other \"short\" variables to accommodate the kind of values that are likely to be needed for crossover trials. For example, if ARMCD values for a 7-period crossover were constructed using 2-character abbreviations for each treatment and separating hyphens, the length of ARMCD values would be 20. This same rule applies to the ACTARMCD variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Variable descriptive names (labels), up to 40 characters, should be provided as data variable labels for all variables, including Supplemental Qualifier variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.1 [Variable-naming Conventions]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Use of variable names (other than domain prefixes), formats, decodes, terminology, and data types for the same type of data (even for custom domains and Supplemental Qualifiers) should be consistent within and across studies within a submission.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.2 Two-character Domain Identifier", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In order to minimize the risk of difficulty when merging/joining domains for reporting purposes, the 2-character domain identifier is used as a prefix in most variable names.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Variables in domain specification tables (see Section 5, Models for Special-purpose Domains; Section 6, Domain Models Based on the General Observation Classes; Section 7, Trial Design Model Datasets; Section 8, Representing Relationships and Data; and Section 9, Study References) already specify the complete variable names.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5", "§6", "§7", "§8", "§9"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When adding variables from the SDTM to standard domains or creating custom domains based on the general observation classes, sponsors must replace the \"--\" prefix in the SDTM tables of General Observation Class, Timing, and Identifier variables with the 2-character domain identifier (DOMAIN) value for that domain/dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The 2-character domain code is limited to A-Z for the first character, and A-Z, 0-9 for the second character.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "No other characters are allowed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This is for compatibility with SAS v5 transport files and with file naming requirements as part of the Electronic Common Technical Document (eCTD).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following variables are exceptions to the philosophy that all variable names are prefixed with the domain identifier:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Required Identifiers (STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Commonly used grouping and merge keys (e.g., VISIT, VISITNUM, VISITDY)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0028_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 28, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "All Demographics (DM) domain variables other than DMDTC and DMDY", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "All variables in RELREC and SUPPQUAL, and some variables in the Comments and Trial Design datasets", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Required identifiers are not prefixed because they are usually used as keys when merging/joining observations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.2 [Two-character Domain Identifier]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The --SEQ and the optional Identifiers --GRPID and --REFID are prefixed because they may be used as keys when relating observations across domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.3 Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "\"Subject\" is used to generically refer to both patients and healthy volunteers in order to be consistent with the recommendation in FDA guidance.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The term \"subject\" should be used consistently in all labels and Define-XML document comments.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "To identify a subject uniquely across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product, a unique identifier (USUBJID) should be assigned and included in all datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The unique subject identifier (USUBJID) is required in all datasets containing subject-level data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "USUBJID values must be unique for each trial participant (subject) across all trials in the submission.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This means that no 2 or more subjects, across all trials in the submission, may have the same USUBJID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In addition, the same person who participates in multiple clinical trials (when this is known) must be assigned the same USUBJID value in all trials.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "CDISC does not recommend any specific format for the values of USUBJID, only that the values need to be unique for all subjects in the submission, and across multiple submissions for the same compound.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Many sponsors concatenate values for the study, site, and subject into USUBJID, but this is not a requirement.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It is acceptable to use any format for USUBJID, as long as the values are unique across all subjects.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following dm.xpt sample rows illustrate a single subject who participates in 2 studies, first in ACME01 and later in ACME14.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.3 [Use of \"Subject\" and USUBJID]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that this is only one example of the possible values for USUBJID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
