{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.4 [Text Case in Submitted Data]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.4 Text Case in Submitted Data", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.4 [Text Case in Submitted Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It is recommended that text data be submitted in text that is all upper case (e.g., NEGATIVE).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.4 [Text Case in Submitted Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Exceptions may include long text data (e.g., comment text) and values of --TEST in Findings datasets (which may be more readable in title case if used as labels in transposed views).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.4 [Text Case in Submitted Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Values from CDISC Controlled Terminology or external code systems (e.g., MedDRA, SNOMED) or response values for QRS instruments specified by the instrument documentation should be in the case specified by those sources, which may be mixed case.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.4 [Text Case in Submitted Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The case used in the text data must match the case used in the controlled terminology provided in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.5 [Convention for Missing Values]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.5 Convention for Missing Values", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.5 [Convention for Missing Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Missing values for individual data items should be represented by nulls.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.5 [Convention for Missing Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Conventions for representing observations not done, using the SDTM --STAT and --REASND variables, are addressed in Section 4.5.1.2, Tests Not Done, and the individual domain models.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.5.1.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.6 Grouping Variables and Categorization", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Grouping variables are Identifiers and Qualifiers variables—such as the --CAT (Category) and --SCAT (Subcategory)—that group records in the SDTM domains/datasets and can be assigned by sponsors to categorize topic-variable values.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, a lab record with LBTEST = \"SODIUM\" might have LBCAT = \"CHEMISTRY\" and LBSCAT = \"ELECTROLYTES\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0029_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 29, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Values for --CAT and --SCAT should not be redundant with the domain name or dictionary classification provided by --DECOD and --BODSYS.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Hierarchy of Grouping Variables", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "STUDYID\nDOMAIN\n    --CAT\n  --SCAT\n    USUBJID\n        --GRPID\n        --LNKID\n        --LNKGRP", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "How Grouping Variables Group Data", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For the subject", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "All records with the same USUBJID value are a group of records that describe that subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Across subjects (records with different USUBJID values)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "All records with the same STUDYID value are a group of records that describe that study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "All records with the same DOMAIN value are a group of records that describe that domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--CAT (Category) and --SCAT (Sub-category) values further subset groups within the domain. Generally, --CAT/--SCAT values have meaning within a particular domain. However, it is possible to use the same values for --CAT/--SCAT in related domains (e.g., MH and AE). When values are used across domains, the meanings should be the same. Examples of where --CAT/--SCAT may have meaning across domains/datasets include:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Cases where different domains in the same general observation class contain similar conceptual information. Adverse Events (AE), Medical History (MH), and Clinical Events (CE), for example, are conceptually the same data, the only differences being when the event started relative to the study start and whether the event is considered a regulatory-reportable adverse event in the study. Neurotoxicities collected in oncology trials both as separate Medical History CRFs (MH domain) and Adverse Event CRFs (AE domain) could both identify/collect \"Paresthesia of the left arm\". In both domains, the --CAT variable could have the value of \"NEUROTOXICITY\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Cases where multiple datasets are necessary to capture data about the same topic. Following the oncology example, the existence and start and stop date of paresthesia of the left arm may be reported as an adverse event (AE domain), whereas the severity of the event is captured at multiple visits and recorded as Findings About (FA dataset). In both cases the --CAT variable could have a value of \"NEUROTOXICITY\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Cases where multiple domains are necessary to capture data that were collected together and have an implicit relationship, perhaps identified in the Related Records (RELREC) special-purpose dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Stress-test data collection may capture the following:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Information about the occurrence, start, stop, and duration of the test (in the Procedures (PR) domain)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Vital Signs recorded during the stress test (VS domain)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Treatments (e.g., oxygen) administered during the stress test (in an Interventions domain)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In such cases, the data collected during the stress tests recorded in 3 separate domains may all have --CAT/--SCAT values (STRESS TEST) that identify that data were collected during the stress test.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Within subjects (records with the same USUBJID values)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0030_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 30, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 [Grouping Variables and Categorization]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--GRPID values further group (subset) records within USUBJID. All records in the same domain with the same --GRPID value are a group of records within USUBJID. Unlike --CAT and --SCAT, --GRPID values are not intended to have any meaning across subjects and are usually assigned during or after data collection.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch03_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-24T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although --SPID and --REFID are Identifier variables, they may sometimes be used as grouping variables and may also have meaning across domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "--LNKID and --LNKGRP express values that are used to link records in separate domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As such, these variables are often used in IDVAR in a RELREC relationship when there is a dataset-to-dataset relationship.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§RELREC"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--LNKID is a grouping identifier used to identify a record in one domain that is related to records in another domain, often forming a one-to-many relationship.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--LNKGRP is a grouping identifier used to identify a group of records in one domain that is related to a record in another domain, often forming a many-to-one relationship.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Differences Between Grouping Variables", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The primary distinctions between --CAT/--SCAT and --GRPID are:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--CAT/--SCAT are known (identified) about the data before it is collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--CAT/--SCAT values group data across subjects.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--CAT/--SCAT may have some controlled terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--GRPID is usually assigned during or after data collection at the discretion of the sponsor.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--GRPID groups data only within a subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--GRPID values are sponsor-defined, and will not be subject to controlled terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Therefore, data that would be the same across subjects is usually more appropriate in --CAT/--SCAT, and data that would vary across subjects is usually more appropriate in --GRPID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, a concomitant medication administered as part of a known combination therapy for all subjects (e.g., \"Mayo Clinic Regimen\") would more appropriately use --CAT/--SCAT to identify the medication as part of that regimen.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Groups of medications recorded on a Serious Adverse Event (SAE) form as treatments for the SAE would more appropriately use --GRPID because groupings are likely to differ across subjects.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In domains based on the Findings general observation class, the --RESCAT variable can be used to categorize results after the fact.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.6 Grouping Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "--CAT and --SCAT by contrast, are generally defined by the sponsor or used by the investigator at the point of collection, not after assessing the value of Findings results.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.7 Submitting Free Text from the CRF", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.7 Submitting Free Text from the CRF", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.7 Submitting Free Text from the CRF", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors often collect free-text data on a CRF to supplement a standard field.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.7 Submitting Free Text from the CRF", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This often occurs as part of a list of choices accompanied by \"Other, specify.\"", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.7 Submitting Free Text from the CRF", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The manner in which these data are submitted will vary based on their role.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.7.1 \"Specify\" Values for Non-result Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.7.1  \"Specify\" Values for Non-result Qualifier Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.7.1 \"Specify\" Values for Non-result Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When free-text information is collected to supplement a standard non-result qualifier field, the free-text value should be placed in the SUPP-- dataset described in Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.7.1 \"Specify\" Values for Non-result Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When applicable, controlled terminology should be used for SUPP-- field names (QNAM) and their associated labels (QLABEL; see Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain, and Appendix C1, Supplemental Qualifiers Name Codes).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4", "§Appendix C1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0031_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 31, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.2.7.1 \"Specify\" Values for Non-result Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, when a description of \"Other Medically Important Serious Adverse Event\" category is collected on a CRF, the free-text description should be stored in the SUPPAE dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
