{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When variable length is referenced in the SDTMIG, this refers to the length in bytes of ASCII character strings.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Very large transport files have become an issue for certain regulatory authorities (e.g., US FDA) to process.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "One of the main contributors to large file sizes has been sponsors using the maximum length of 200 for character variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "To help rectify this situation:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The maximum SAS v5 transport file character variable length of 200 characters should not be used unless necessary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Sponsors should consider the nature of the data and apply reasonable, appropriate lengths to variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The length of flags will always be 1.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "--TESTCD and IDVAR will never be more than 8, so the length can always be set to 8.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.2.9 Variable Lengths", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The length for variables that use controlled terminology can be set to the length of the longest term.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
