{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.1 Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format Column", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As of SDTMIG v3.3, controlled terminology is represented in the following ways:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.1 Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format Column", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A single asterisk (*) when CDISC Controlled Terminology is not currently available but the SDS Team expects that sponsors may have their own controlled terminology and/or the CDISC Controlled Terminology Team may develop controlled terminology in the future", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.1 Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format Column", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The single applicable value for the variable DOMAIN (e.g., \"PR\")", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a033", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.1 Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format Column", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The name of a CDISC codelist, represented as a hyperlink in parentheses (e.g., \"(NY)\")", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a034", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.1 Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format Column", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A short reference to an external terminology (e.g., \"MedDRA\", \"ISO 3166-1 alpha-3\")", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0036_a035", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 36, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.1 Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format Column", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In addition, the Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format column has been used to indicate variables that use an ISO 8601 format.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.2 Controlled Terminology Text Case", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.3.2 Controlled Terminology Text Case", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.2 Controlled Terminology Text Case", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Terms from controlled terminology should be in the case that appears the source codelist or code system (e.g., CDISC codelist or external code system such as MedDRA).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.2 Controlled Terminology Text Case", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "See Section 4.2.4, Text Case in Submitted Data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The controlled terminology or a reference to the controlled terminology should be included in the Define-XML document file wherever applicable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "All values in the permissible value set for the study should be included, whether or not they are represented in the submitted data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that a null value should not be included in the permissible value set.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A null value is implied for any list of controlled terms unless the variable is \"Required\" (see Section 4.1.5, SDTM Core Designations).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.1.5"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When a domain or dataset specification includes a codelist for a variable, not every value in that codelist may have been part of planned data collection; only values that were part of planned data collection should be included in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, --PRESP variables are associated with the NY codelist, but only the value \"Y\" is allowed in --PRESP variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.3 Controlled Terminology Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Future versions of the Define-XML specification are expected to include information on representing subsets of controlled terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.4 Use of Controlled Terminology and Arbitrary Number Codes", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.3.4 Use of Controlled Terminology and Arbitrary Number Codes", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.4 Use of Controlled Terminology and Arbitrary Number Codes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Controlled terminology or human-readable text should be used instead of arbitrary number codes in order to reduce ambiguity for submission reviewers.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.4 Use of Controlled Terminology and Arbitrary Number Codes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, CMDECOD would contain human-readable dictionary text rather than a numeric code.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.4 Use of Controlled Terminology and Arbitrary Number Codes", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Numeric code values may be submitted as Supplemental Qualifiers if necessary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For events such as adverse events and medical history, populate --DECOD with the dictionary's preferred term and populate --BODSYS with the preferred body system name.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a dictionary is multi-axial, the value in --BODSYS should represent the system organ class (SOC) used for the sponsor's analysis and summary tables, which may not necessarily be the primary SOC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Populate --SOC with the dictionary-derived primary SOC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In cases where the primary SOC was used for analysis, --BODSYS and --SOC are the same.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If MedDRA is used to code events, the intermediate levels in the MedDRA hierarchy should also be represented in the dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A pair of variables has been defined for each of the levels of the hierarchy other than SOC and Preferred Term (PT): one to represent the text description and the other to represent the code value associated with it.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, --LLT should be used to represent the Lowest Level Term text description and --LLTCD should be used to represent the Lowest Level Term code value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For concomitant medications, populate CMDECOD with the drug's generic name and populate CMCLAS with the drug class used for the sponsor's analysis and summary tables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If coding to multiple classes, follow Section 4.2.8.1, Multiple Values for an Intervention or Event Topic Variable, or omit CMCLAS.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For concomitant medications, supplemental qualifiers may be used to represent additional coding dictionary information (e.g., a drug's ATC codes from the WHO Drug Dictionary; see Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.5 Storing Controlled Terminology for Synonym Qualifier Variables", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms by utilizing the Define-XML external codelist attributes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The topic variable for the Interventions and Events general observation-class models is often stored as verbatim text.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For an Events domain, the topic variable is --TERM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For an Interventions domain, the topic variable is --TRT.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For a Findings domain, the topic variable --TESTCD should use controlled terminology (e.g., \"SYSBP\" for systolic blood pressure).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a033", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If CDISC Controlled Terminology exists, it should be used; otherwise, sponsors should define their own controlled list of terms.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a034", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the verbatim topic variable in an Interventions or Event domain is modified to facilitate coding, the modified text is stored in --MODIFY.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0037_a035", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 37, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In most cases—other than Physical Examination (PE)—the [TRUNCATED_AT_PAGE_BOUNDARY]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "dictionary-coded text is derived into --DECOD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because the PEORRES variable is modified instead of the topic variable for PE, the dictionary-derived text would be placed in PESTRESC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.6 Storing Topic Variables for General Domain Models", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The variables used in each of the defined domains are:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
