{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Variables where the response is \"Yes\" or \"No\" (\"Y\" or \"N\") should normally be populated for both \"Y\" and \"N\" responses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This eliminates confusion regarding whether a blank response indicates \"N\" or is a missing value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "However, some variables are collected or derived in a manner that allows only 1 response, such as when a single checkbox indicates \"Yes\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In situations such as these, where it is unambiguous to populate only the response of interest, it is permissible to populate only 1 value (\"Y\" or \"N\") and leave the alternate value blank.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "An example of when it would be acceptable to use only a value of \"Y\" would be for Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) variables, where \"N\" is not necessary to indicate that a value is not the last observation before exposure.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.3.7 Use of \"Yes\" and \"No\" Values", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Note: Permissible values for variables with controlled terms of \"Y\" or \"N\" may be extended to include \"U\" or \"NA\" if it is the sponsor's practice to explicitly collect or derive values indicating \"Unknown\" or \"Not Applicable\" for that variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "heading_level": 1, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Timing variables (SDTM Section 3.1.5, Timing Variables for All Classes) are an essential component of all SDTM subject-level domain datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§3.1.5"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In general, all domains based on the 3 general observation classes should have at least 1 timing variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In the Events or Interventions general observation class, this could be the start date of the event or intervention.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In the Findings observation class, where data are usually collected at multiple visits, at least 1 timing variable must be used.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTMIG requires dates and times of day to be stored according to the international standard ISO 8601 (http://www.iso.org).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4 Actual and Relative Time Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "ISO 8601 provides a text-based representation of dates and/or times, intervals of time, and durations of time.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "An SDTM DTC variable may include data that is represented in ISO 8601 format as a complete date/time, a partial date/time, or an incomplete date/time.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTMIG template uses ISO 8601 for calendar dates and times of day, which are expressed as follows:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss(.n+)?(((+|-)hh:mm)|Z)?", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0038_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 38, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss(.n+)?(((+|-)hh:mm)|Z)?", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
