{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Other characters defined for use within the ISO 8601 standard are:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "[-] (hyphen): to separate the time elements \"year\" from \"month\" and \"month\" from \"day\" and to represent missing date components.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "[:] (colon): to separate the time elements \"hour\" from \"minute\" and \"minute\" from \"second\"", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "[/] (solidus): to separate components in the representation of date/time intervals", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "[P] (duration designator): precedes the components that represent the duration", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Spaces are not allowed in any ISO 8601 representations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Key aspects of the ISO 8601 standard are as follows:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "ISO 8601 represents dates as a text string using the notation YYYY-MM-DD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "YYYY-MM-DD", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "ISO 8601 represents times as a text string using the notation hh:mm:ss(.n+)?(((+|-)hh:mm)|Z)?.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "hh:mm:ss(.n+)?(((+|-)hh:mm)|Z)?", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The SDTM and the SDTMIG require use of the ISO 8601 extended format, which requires hyphen delimiters for date components and colon delimiters for time components.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The ISO 8601 basic format, which does not require delimiters, should not be used in SDTM datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When a date is stored with a time in the same variable (as a date/time), the date is written in front of the time and the time is preceded with \"T\" using the notation YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss (e.g. 2001-12-26T00:00:01).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Implementation of the ISO 8601 standard means that date/time variables are character/text data types.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.1 Formats for Date/Time Variables", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTM fragment employed for date/time character variables is DTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The concept of representing date/time precision is handled through use of the ISO 8601 standard.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "According to ISO 8601, precision (also referred to by ISO 8601 as \"completeness\" or \"representations with reduced accuracy\") can be inferred from the presence or absence of components in the date and/or time values.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Missing components are represented by right truncation or a hyphen (for intermediate components that are missing).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the date and time values are completely missing, the SDTM date field should be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Every component except year is represented as 2 digits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Years are represented as 4 digits; for all other components, 1-digit numbers are always padded with a leading zero.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following table provides examples of ISO 8601 representations of complete and truncated date/time values using ISO 8601 \"appropriate right truncations\" of incomplete date/time representations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0039_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 39, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that if no time component is represented, the [T] time designator (in addition to the missing time) must be omitted in ISO 8601 representation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
