{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that row 6, where a time is reported with no date information, represents a very unusual situation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because most data are collected as part of a visit, when only a time appears on a CRF, it is expected that the date of the visit would usually be used as the date of collection.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.2 Date/Time Precision", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Using a character-based data type to implement the ISO 8601 date/time standard will ensure that the date/time information will be machine- and human-readable without the need for further manipulation, and will be platform- and software-independent.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
