{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.3.1  Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As defined by ISO 8601, an interval of time is the part of a time axis, limited by 2 time \"instants\" such as the times represented in SDTM by the variables --STDTC and --ENDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "These variables represent the 2 instants that bound an interval of time; the duration is the value of an interval that is equal to the difference between these time points.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "ISO 8601 allows an interval to be represented in multiple ways.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "One representation, shown below, uses 2 dates in the format:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss/YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although this example represents the interval (by providing the start date/time and end date/time to bound the interval of time), it does not provide the value of the duration (the quantity of time).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Duration is frequently used during a review; however, the duration timing variable (--DUR) should generally be used in a domain if it was collected in lieu of a start date/time (--STDTC) and end date/time (--ENDTC).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If both --STDTC and --ENDTC are collected, durations can be calculated by the difference in these 2 values, and need not be in the submission dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Both duration and duration units can be provided in the single --DUR variable, in accordance with the ISO 8601 standard.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The values provided in --DUR should follow 1 of the following ISO 8601 duration formats:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
