{"atom_id": "ig34_p0040_a036", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 40, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 Intervals of Time and Use of Duration", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "[P] (duration designator): precedes the alphanumeric text string that represents the duration. Note that the use of the character \"P\" is based on the historical use of the term \"period\" for duration.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch04_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "[n] represents a positive number or zero.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "[W] is used as week designator, preceding a data element that represents the number of calendar weeks within the calendar year (e.g., P6W represents 6 weeks of calendar time).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The letter \"P\" must precede other values in the ISO 8601 representation of duration.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The \"n\" preceding each letter represents the number of years, months, days, hours, minutes, seconds, or the number of weeks.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As with the date/time format, \"T\" is used to separate the date components from time components.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Note that weeks cannot be mixed with any other date/time components such as days or months in duration expressions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As is the case with the date/time representation in --DTC, --STDTC, or --ENDTC, only the components of duration that are known or collected need to be represented.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As is the case with the date/time representation, if no time component is represented, the [T] time designator (in addition to the missing time) must be omitted in ISO 8601 representation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "ISO 8601 also allows that the \"lowest-order components\" of duration being represented may be represented in decimal format.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This may be useful if data are collected in formats such as \"one and one-half years\", \"two and a half weeks\", \"half a week\" or \"quarter of an hour\" and the sponsor wishes to represent this \"precision\" (or lack of precision) in ISO 8601 format.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This is ONLY allowed in the lowest-order (right-most) component in any duration representation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following table provides some examples of ISO 8601-compliant representations of durations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
