{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a034", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.1 [Duration]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Note that a leading zero is required with decimal values less than 1.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a035", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.3.2  Interval with Uncertainty", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a036", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When an interval of time is an amount of time (duration) following an event whose start date/time is recorded (with some level of precision, e.g., when one knows the start date/time and the duration following the start date/time), the correct ISO 8601 usage to represent this interval is:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a037", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss/PnYnMnDTnHnMnS", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a038", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "where the start date/time is represented before the solidus or foreword slash [/], the \"Pn...\" following the solidus represents a \"duration,\" and the entire representation is known as an \"interval.\"", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a039", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that this is the recommended representation of elapsed time, given a start date/time and the duration elapsed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a040", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When an interval of time is an amount of time (duration) measured prior to an event whose start date/time is recorded (with some level of precision, e.g., where one knows the end date/time and the duration preceding that end date/time), the syntax is:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a041", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "PnYnMnDTnHnMnS/YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a042", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.3.2 [Interval with Uncertainty]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "where the duration, \"Pn...\", is represented before the solidus [/], the end date/time is represented following the solidus, and the entire representation is known as an \"interval.\"", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a043", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.4 Use of the Study Day Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a044", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The permissible study day variables (i.e., --DY, --STDY, --ENDY) describe the relative day of the observation starting with the reference date as day 1.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0041_a045", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 41, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "They are determined by comparing the date portion of the respective date/time variables (--DTC, --STDTC, and --ENDTC) to the date portion of the subject reference start date (RFSTDTC from the Demographics domain).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The subject reference start date (RFSTDTC) is designated as study day 1.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The study day value is incremented by 1 for each date following RFSTDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Dates prior to RFSTDTC are decreased by 1, with the date preceding RFSTDTC designated as study day -1 (there is no study day 0).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This algorithm for determining Study Day is consistent with how people typically describe sequential days relative to a fixed reference point, but creates problems if used for mathematical calculations because it does not allow for a day 0.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As such, Study Day is not suited for use in subsequent numerical computations, such as calculating duration.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The raw date values should be used rather than Study Day in those calculations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "All study day values are integers. Thus, to calculate Study Day:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "--DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) + 1 if --DTC is on or after RFSTDTC\n--DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --DTC precedes RFSTDTC", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.4 [Use of the Study Day Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This method should be used across all domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.5 Clinical Encounters and Visits", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "All domains based on the 3 general observation classes should have at least 1 timing variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For domains in the Events or Interventions observation classes, and for domains in the Findings observation class, for which data are collected only once during the study, the most appropriate timing variable may be a date (e.g., --DTC, --STDTC) or some other timing variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For studies that are designed with a prospectively defined schedule of visit-based activities, domains for data that are to be collected more than once per subject (e.g., labs, ECG, vital signs) are expected to include VISITNUM as a timing variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Clinical encounters are described by the CDISC visit variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For planned visits, values of VISIT, VISITNUM, and VISITDY must be those defined in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset (see Section 7.3.1, Trial Visits).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.3.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "see Section 7.3.1, Trial Visits", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.3.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For planned visits:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Values of VISITNUM are used for sorting and should, wherever possible, match the planned chronological order of visits. Occasionally, a protocol will define a planned visit whose timing is unpredictable (e.g., planned in response to an adverse event, a threshold test value, or a disease event), and completely chronological values of VISITNUM may not be possible in such cases.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "There should be a one-to-one relationship between values of VISIT and VISITNUM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For visits that may last more than 1 calendar day, VISITDY should be the planned day of the start of the visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsor practices for populating visit variables for unplanned visits may vary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "VISITNUM should generally be populated, even for unplanned visits, as it is expected in many Findings domains, as described above. The easiest method of populating VISITNUM for unplanned visits is to assign the same value (e.g., 99) to all unplanned visits, although this method provides no differentiation between the unplanned visits and does not provide chronological sorting. Methods that provide a one-to-one relationship between visits and values of VISITNUM, that are consistent across domains, and that assign VISITNUM values that sort chronologically require more work and must be applied after all of a subject's unplanned visits are known.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "VISIT may be left null or may be populated with a generic value (e.g., \"Unscheduled\") for all unplanned visits, or individual values may be assigned to different unplanned visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "VISITDY must not be populated for unplanned visits; VISITDY is, by definition, the planned study day of visit. The actual study day of an unplanned visit belongs in a --DY variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0042_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 42, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.5 [Clinical Encounters and Visits]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following lb.xpt sample rows show how visit identifiers might be used for lab data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
