{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.6 [Representing Additional Study Days]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.6 Representing Additional Study Days", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.6 [Representing Additional Study Days]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTM allows for the representation of study days relative to the RFSTDTC reference start date variable in the DM dataset, using variables --DY, as described in Section 4.4.4, Use of the \"Study Day\" Variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.6 [Representing Additional Study Days]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 4.4.4, Use of the \"Study Day\" Variables", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.6 [Representing Additional Study Days]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The calculation of additional study days within subdivisions of time in a clinical trial may be based on 1 or more sponsor-defined reference dates not represented by RFSTDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.6 [Representing Additional Study Days]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In such cases, the sponsor may define supplemental qualifier variables and the Define-XML document should reflect the reference dates used to calculate such study days.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.6 [Representing Additional Study Days]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the sponsor wishes to define \"day within element\" or \"day within epoch\", the reference date/time will be an element start date/time in the Subject Elements (SE) dataset (see Section 5.3, Subject Elements).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.6 [Representing Additional Study Days]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 5.3, Subject Elements", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.7 Use of Relative Timing Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "--STRF and --ENRF", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The variables --STRF and --ENRF represent the timing of an observation relative to the sponsor-defined study reference period, when information such as \"BEFORE\", \"PRIOR\", \"ONGOING\", or \"CONTINUING\" is collected in lieu of a date and this collected information is in relation to the sponsor-defined study reference period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The sponsor-defined study reference period is the continuous period of time defined by the discrete starting point, RFSTDTC, and the discrete ending point, RFENDTC, for each subject in the Demographics (DM) dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "--STRF is used to identify the start of an observation relative to the sponsor-defined study reference period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "--ENRF is used to identify the end of an observation relative to the sponsor-defined study reference period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Allowable values for --STRF are \"BEFORE\", \"DURING\", \"DURING/AFTER\", \"AFTER\", and \"UNKNOWN\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although \"COINCIDENT\" and \"ONGOING\" are in the STENRF codelist, they describe timing relative to a point in time rather than an interval of time, so are not appropriate for use with --STRF variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It would be unusual for an event or intervention to be recorded as starting \"AFTER\" the study reference period, but could be possible, depending on how the study reference period is defined in a particular study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Allowable values for --ENRF are \"BEFORE\", \"DURING\", \"DURING/AFTER\", \"AFTER\" and \"UNKNOWN\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If --ENRF is used, then --ENRF = \"AFTER\" means that the event did not end before or during the study reference period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although \"COINCIDENT\" and \"ONGOING\" are in the STENRF codelist, they describe timing relative to a point in time rather than an interval of time, so are not appropriate for use with --ENRF variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As an example, a CRF checkbox that identifies concomitant medication use that began prior to the study reference period would translate into CMSTRF = \"BEFORE\", if selected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that in this example, the information collected is with respect to the start of the concomitant medication use only, and therefore the collected data corresponds to variable CMSTRF, not CMENRF.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note also that the information collected is relative to the study reference period, which meets the definition of CMSTRF.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Some sponsors may wish to derive --STRF and --ENRF for analysis or reporting purposes even when dates are collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors are cautioned that doing so in conjunction with directly collecting or mapping data such as \"BEFORE\", \"PRIOR\", and \"ONGOING\" to --STRF and --ENRF will blur the distinction between collected and derived values within the domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors wishing to do such derivations are instead encouraged to use analysis datasets for this derived data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In general, sponsors are cautioned that representing information using variables --STRF and --ENRF may not be as precise as other methods, particularly because information is often collected relative to a point in time or to a period of time other than the one defined as the study reference period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "SDTMIG v3.1.2 attempted to address these limitations by the addition of 4 new relative timing variables, which are described in the following section.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors should use the set of variables that allows for accurate representation of collected data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In many cases, this will mean using these new relative timing variables in place of --STRF and --ENRF.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "--STRTPT, --STTPT, --ENRTPT, and --ENTPT", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although the variables --STRF and --ENRF are useful in the case when relative timing assessments are made coincident with the start and end of the study reference period, they may not be suitable for expressing relative timing assessments (e.g., \"Prior\", \"Ongoing\") that are collected at other times of the study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As a result, 4 new timing variables were added in SDTMIG v3.1.2 to express a similar concept at any point in time.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a033", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The variables --STRTPT and --ENRTPT contain values similar to --STRF and --ENRF, but may be anchored with any timing description or date/time value expressed in the respective --STTPT and --ENTPT variables, and are not limited to the study reference period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0043_a034", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 43, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Unlike the variables --STRF and --ENRF, which for all domains are defined relative to one study [TRUNCATED_AT_PAGE_BOUNDARY]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0044_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 44, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "reference period, the timing variables --STRTPT, --STTPT, --ENRTPT, and --ENTPT are defined by each sponsor for each study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0044_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 44, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Allowable values for --STRTPT and --ENRTPT are as follows.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0044_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 44, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the reference time point corresponds to the date of collection or assessment:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0044_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 44, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Start values: An observation can start BEFORE that time point, can start COINCIDENT with that time point, or it can be UNKNOWN when it started.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0044_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 44, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "End values: An observation can end BEFORE that time point, can end COINCIDENT with that time point, can be known that it did not end but was ONGOING, or it can be UNKNOWN when it ended or if it was ongoing.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0044_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 44, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "AFTER is not a valid value in this case because it would represent an event after the date of collection.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0044_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 44, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.7 [Use of Relative Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the reference time point is prior to the date of collection or assessment:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
