{"atom_id": "ig34_p0045_a038", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 45, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.9 Use of Dates as Result Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0045_a039", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 45, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Dates are generally used only as timing variables to describe the timing of an event, intervention, or collection activity, but there may be occasions when it may be preferable to model a date as a result (--ORRES) in a Findings dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0045_a040", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 45, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that using a date as a result to a Findings question is unusual and atypical, and should be approached [TRUNCATED_AT_PAGE_BOUNDARY]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "with caution. This situation, however, may occasionally occur when (1) a group of questions (each of which has a date response) is asked and analyzed together; or (2) the event(s) and intervention(s) in question are not medically significant (e.g., when included in questionnaires). Consider the following cases:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Calculated due date", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Date of last day on the job", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Date of high school graduation", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "One approach to modeling these data would be to place the text of the question in --TEST and the response to the question (a date represented in ISO 8601 format) in --ORRES and --STRESC, as long as these date results do not contain the dates of medically significant events or interventions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Again, use extreme caution when storing dates as the results of findings.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.9 [Use of Dates as Result Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Remember, in most cases, these dates should be timing variables associated with a record in an Intervention or Events dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.10  Representing Time Points", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 10, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Time points can be represented using the time point variables --TPT, --TPTNUM, --ELTM, and the time-point anchors --TPTREF (text description) and --RFTDTC (the date/time).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that time-point data will usually have an associated --DTC value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The interrelationship of these variables is shown in the following figure.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
