{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "FIGURE", "verbatim": "[FIGURE: Timeline diagram with Reference Time Point (Usually a Dose) at left showing --TPTREF (Description) and --RFTDTC (Date/Time); arrow extends right to Collection Time Point showing --TPT (Description), --TPTNUM (Number), --DTC (Date/Time); Planned Elapsed Time bracket labeled --ELTM (ISO 8601) spans between the two points.]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": "pdf_p0046+middle", "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0046_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 46, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Values for these variables for vital signs measurements taken at 30, 60, and 90 minutes after dosing would look like the following.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
