{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PERIOD 2, DAY 1 | 5 | 4H | 3 | PM DOSE", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 18, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Within the context that defines uniqueness for a time point (which may include domain, visit, and reference time point), there must be a one-to-one relationship between values of --TPT and --TPTNUM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In other words, if domain, visit, and reference time point uniquely identify subject data, then if 2 subjects have records with the same values of DOMAIN, VISITNUM, --TPTREF, and --TPTNUM, these records may not have different time point descriptions in --TPT.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Within the context that defines uniqueness for a time point, there is likely to be a one-to-one relationship between most values of --TPT and --ELTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "However, because --ELTM can only be populated with ISO 8601 periods of time (as described in Section 4.4.3, Intervals of Time and Use of Duration for --DUR Variables), --ELTM may not be populated for all time points.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 4.4.3, Intervals of Time and Use of Duration for --DUR Variables", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, --ELTM is likely to be null for time points described by text such as \"pre-dose\" or \"before breakfast.\"", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When --ELTM is populated, if 2 subjects have records with the same values of DOMAIN, VISITNUM, --TPTREF, and --TPTNUM, then these records may not have different values in --ELTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When the protocol describes a time point with text (e.g., \"4-6 hours after dose,\" \"12 hours +/- 2 hours after dose\"), the sponsor may choose whether and how to populate --ELTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, a time point described as \"4-6 hours after dose\" might be associated with an --ELTM value of PT4H.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "PT4H", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A time point described as \"12 hours +/- 2 hours after dose\" might be associated with an --ELTM value of PT12H.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "PT12H", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a033", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Conventions for populating --ELTM should be consistent (the examples just given would probably not both be used in the same trial).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a034", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It would be good practice to indicate the range of intended timings by some convention in the values used to populate --TPT.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a035", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors may, of course, use more stringent requirements for populating --TPTNUM, --TPT, and --ELTM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a036", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.10 [Representing Time Points]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For instance, a sponsor could decide that all time points with a particular --ELTM value would have the same values of --TPTNUM, and --TPT, across all visits, reference time points, and domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a037", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.4.11  Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 11, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a038", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A disease milestone is an event or activity that can be anticipated in the course of a disease, but whose timing is not controlled by the study schedule.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a039", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A disease milestone may be something that occurred pre-study, but which represents a time at which data would have been collected (e.g., diagnosis of the disease under study).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a040", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A disease milestone may also be something which is anticipated to occur during a study and which, if it occurs, triggers the collection of related data outside the regular schedule of visits (e.g., adverse event of interest).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a041", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The types of disease milestones for a study are defined in the study-level Trial Disease Milestones (TM) dataset (see Section 7.3.3, Trial Disease Milestones).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.3.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a042", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 7.3.3, Trial Disease Milestones", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.3.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a043", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The times at which disease milestones occurred for a particular subject are summarized in the special-purpose Subject Disease Milestones (SM) domain (see Section 5.4, Subject Disease Milestones), a domain similar in structure to the Subject Visits (SV) and Subject Elements (SE) domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a044", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "Section 5.4, Subject Disease Milestones", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a045", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Not all studies will have disease milestones.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0048_a046", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 48, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a study does not have disease milestones, the TM and SM domains will not be present and the disease milestones timing variables may not be included in other domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Disease Milestone Naming", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Instances of disease milestones are given names at a subject level.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The name of a disease milestone is composed of a character string that depends on the disease milestone type (MIDSTYPE in TM and SM) and, if the type of disease milestone is one that may occur multiple times, a chronological sequence number for this disease milestone among other instances of the same type for the subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The character string used in the name of a disease milestone is usually a short form of the disease milestone type.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, if the type of disease milestone is \"EPISODE OF DISEASE UNDER STUDY\", the values of MIDS for instances of this type of event could include \"EPISODE1\", \"EPISODE2\"; or \"EPISODE01\", \"EPISODE02\", and so on.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The association between the longer text in MIDSTYPE and the shorter text in MIDS can be seen in SM, which includes both variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Disease Milestone Name (MIDS)", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If something that has been defined as a disease milestone for a particular study occurrs for a particular subject, it is represented as usual: in the appropriate findings, intervention, or events class record.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In addition, this record will include the MIDS timing variable, populated with the name of the disease milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The timing of a disease milestone is also represented in the special-purpose SM domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The record that represents a disease milestone does not include values for the timing variables RELMIDS and MIDSDTC, which are used to represent the timing of other observations relative to a disease milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The usual timing variables in the record for a disease milestone (e.g., --DTC, --STDTC, --ENDTC) provide the needed timing for this observation and for the timing information represented in the SM domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Timing Relative to a Disease Milestone (MIDS, RELMIDS, MIDSDTC)", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For an observation triggered by the occurrence of a disease milestone, the relationship of the observation to the disease milestone can be represented using the disease milestones timing variables MIDS, RELMIDS, and MIDSDTC to describe the timing of the observation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "MIDS is populated with the name of a disease milestone for this subject. MIDS is the \"anchor\" for describing the timing of the observation relative to the disease milestone. In this sense, its function is similar to --TPTREF for time points.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "RELMIDS is usually populated with a textual description of the temporal relationship between the observation and the disease milestone named in MIDS. Controlled Terminology has not yet been developed for RELMIDS, but is likely to include terms such as \"IMMEDIATELY BEFORE\", \"AT START OF\", \"DURING\", \"AT END OF\", and \"SHORTLY AFTER\". It is similar to --ELTM, except that --ELTM is represented ISO 8601 duration.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "MIDSDTC is populated with the date/time of the disease milestone. This is the --DTC for a finding, or the --STDTC for an event or intervention, and is the date recorded in SMSTDTC in the SM domain. Its function is similar to --RFTDTC for time points.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In some cases, data collected in conjunction with a disease milestone do not include the collection of a separate date for the related observation.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This is particularly common for pre-study disease milestones, but may occur with on-study disease milestones as well.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In such cases, MIDSDTC provides a related date/time in records that would not otherwise contain any date.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In records that do contain date/time(s) of the observation, MIDSDTC allows easy comparison of the date(s) of the observation to the (start) date of the disease milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In such cases, it functions much like the reference time point date/time (--RFTDTC) in observations at time points.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When a disease milestone is an event or intervention, some data triggered by the disease milestone may be modeled as findings about the disease milestone (i.e., FAOBJ is the disease milestone).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In such cases, RELMIDS should be used to describe the temporal relationship between the disease milestone and the subject of the question being asked in the finding, rather than as describing when the question was asked.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When the subject of the question is the disease milestone itself, RELMIDS may be populated with a value such as \"ENTIRE EVENT\" or \"ENTIRE TREATMENT\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0049_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 49, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When the subject of the question is a question about the occurrence of some activity or event related to the disease milestone, RELMIDS acts like an evaluation interval, describing the period of time on which the question is focused.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For questions about a possible cause of an event or about the indication for a treatment, RELMIDS would have a value such as \"WEEK PRIOR\" or \"IMMEDIATELY BEFORE\", or even just \"BEFORE\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "RELMIDS would be \"DURING\" for questions about things that may have occurred while an event or intervention disease milestone was in progress.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For sequelae of a disease milestone, RELMIDS would have a value such as \"AT DISCHARGE\" or \"WEEK AFTER\", or simply \"AFTER\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Use of Disease Milestone Timing Variables with Other Timing Variables", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The disease milestone timing variables provide timing relative to an activity or event that has been identified, for the particular study, as a disease milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Their use does not preclude the use of variables that collect actual date/times or timing relative to the study schedule.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The use of actual date/times is unaffected. The disease milestone timing variables may provide timing information in cases where actual date/times are unavailable, particularly for pre-study disease milestones. When the question text for an observation references a disease milestone but a separate date for the observation is not collected, the disease milestone timing variables should be populated but the actual date/s should not be imputed by populating them with the date of the disease milestone. Examples of such questions include disease stage at initial diagnosis of disease under study, or treatment for most recent disease episode.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Study-day variables should be populated wherever complete actual date/times are populated. This includes negative study days for pre-study observations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The timing variables EPOCH and TAETORD (Planned Order of Element within Arm) may be populated for on-study observations associated with disease milestones. However, pre-study disease milestones—those which occur before the start of study participation when informed consent is obtained—by definition do not have an associated EPOCH or TAETORD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Visit variables are expected in many Findings domains, but findings triggered by the occurrence of a study milestone might not occur at a scheduled visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Findings associated with pre-study disease milestones are often collected at a screening visit, although the test was not performed at that visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For findings associated with on-study disease milestones but not conducted at a scheduled visit, practices for populating VISITNUM as for an unscheduled visit should be followed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The use of time-point variables with disease milestone variables may occur in cases where a disease milestone triggers treatment, and time points relative to treatment are part of the study schedule. For instance, a migraine trial may call for assessments of symptom severity at prescribed times after treatment of the migraine. If the migraine episodes were treated as disease milestones, then the disease milestone timing variables might be populated in the exposure and symptom-severity records. If the study planned to treat multiple migraine episodes, the MIDS variable would provide a convenient way to determine the episode with which data were associated.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "An evaluation interval variable (--EVLINT or --EVINTX) can be used in conjunction with disease milestone variables. For instance, patient-reported outcome (PRO) instruments might be administered at the time of a disease milestone, and the questions in the instrument might include an evaluation interval.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 8, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0050_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 50, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.4.11 [Disease Milestones and Disease Milestone Timing Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The timing variables for start and end of an event or intervention relative to the study reference period (--STRF and --ENRF) or relative to a reference time point (--STRTPT and --STTPT, --ENRTPT and --ENTPT) can be used in conjunction with disease milestone variables. For example, a concomitant medication could be collected in association with a disease milestone, so that the disease milestone timing variables were populated but relative timing variables used for the start or end of the concomitant medication.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch05_4digit_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4 [Linking and Disease Milestones]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The timing variables for start and end of a planned assessment interval might be populated for an assessment triggered by a disease milestone, if applicable. For example, the occurrence of a particular event might trigger both a treatment and Holter monitoring for 24 hours after the treatment.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4 [Linking and Disease Milestones]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Linking and Disease Milestones", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4 [Linking and Disease Milestones]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When disease milestones have been defined for a study, the MIDS variable serves to link observations associated with a disease milestone in a way similar to the way that VISITNUM links observations collected at a visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4 [Linking and Disease Milestones]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If disease milestones were not defined for the study, it would be possible to link records associated with a disease milestone using RELREC, but the use of disease milestones has certain advantages:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§RELREC"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4 [Linking and Disease Milestones]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "RELREC indicates that there is a relationship between records or datasets, but not the nature of the relationship. Records with the same MIDS value are related to the same disease milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§RELREC"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.4 [Linking and Disease Milestones]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When disease milestones are defined, it is not necessary to create RELREC records to establish relationships between observations associated with a disease milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§RELREC"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5 [Other Assumptions]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5 Other Assumptions", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1 [Original and Standardized Results of Findings and Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.1 Original and Standardized Results of Findings and Tests Not Done", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.1.1 Original and Standardized Results", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The --ORRES variable contains the result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "--ORRES is an expected variable and should always be populated, except (1) when --STAT = \"NOT DONE\" (because there is no result for such a record) or (2) for derived records.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "NOT DONE", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Note: Records with --DRVFL = \"Y\" may combine data collected at more than 1 visit. In such cases, sponsors must define the value for VISITNUM, addressing the correct temporal sequence. If a new record is derived for a dataset by the sponsor or their agent (e.g., a CRO), then that new record should be flagged as derived. For example, in electrocardiogram (ECG) data, if a corrected QT interval value derived in-house by the sponsor were represented in an SDTM record, then EGDRVFL would be \"Y\". If a corrected QT interval value was received from a vendor or was produced by the ECG machine, the derived flag would be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When --ORRES is populated, --STRESС must also be populated, regardless of whether the data values are character or numeric.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The variable --STRESC is populated either by the conversion of values in --ORRES to values with standard units, or by the assignment of the value of --ORRES, as in the Physical Examination (PE) domain, where --STRESC could contain a dictionary-derived term.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A further step is necessary when --STRESC contains numeric values. These are converted to numeric type and written to --STRESN.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because --STRESC may contain a mixture of numeric and character values, --STRESN may contain null values, as shown in the following figure.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Figure. Original to Standardized Results", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "FIGURE", "verbatim": "[FIGURE: Three boxes connected by arrows left-to-right: --ORRES (All original values) → --STRESC (Derive or copy all results) → --STRESN (Numeric results only)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": "pdf_p0051+middle", "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When the original measurement or finding is a selection from a defined codelist, in general, the --ORRES and --STRESC variables contain results in decoded format (i.e., the textual interpretation of whichever code was selected from the codelist).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In some cases where the code values in the codelist are statistically meaningful standardized values or scores, which are defined by sponsors or by valid methodologies such as SF36 questionnaires, the --ORRES variables will contain the decoded format, whereas the --STRESC variables as well as the --STRESN variables will contain the standardized values or scores.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 8, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Occasionally data that are intended to be numeric are collected with characters attached that cause the character-to-numeric conversion to fail.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0051_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 51, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, numeric cell counts in the source data may be specified with a greater than (>) or less than (<) sign attached (e.g., >10,000, <1). In these cases, the value with the greater than (>) or less than (<) sign attached should be moved to the --STRESC variable, and --STRESN should be null. The rules for [TRUNCATED_AT_PAGE_BOUNDARY]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 10, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "modifying the value for analysis purposes should be defined in the analysis plan and a numeric value should only be imputed in the ADaM datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 11, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the value in --STRESC has different units, the greater than (>) or less than (<) sign should be maintained.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 12, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.1 [Original and Standardized Results]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "See Example 1, Rows 11 and 12, in Section 4.5.1.3, Examples of Original and Standard Units and Test Not Done.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.5.1.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.1.2 Tests Not Done", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the data on the CRF is missing and \"Yes/No\" or \"Done/Not Done\" was not explicitly captured, a record should not be created to indicate that the data was not collected, with the exception of QRS.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Regulatory agencies may require a record for all items on a CRF in QRS datasets (e.g., FT, QS, and clinical classifications in RS).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a record is created for a test not done, --REASND is populated only if a reason was explicitly collected except for QRS logically skipped items.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When an entire examination (e.g., laboratory draw, ECG, vital signs, physical examination), a group of tests (e.g., hematology, urinalysis), or an individual test (e.g., glucose, PR interval, blood pressure, hearing) is not done, and this information is explicitly captured with a \"Yes/No\" or \"Done/Not Done\" question, this information should be represented in the dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The reason for the missing information may or may not have been collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A sponsor has the following options:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Submit individual records for each test not done.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Submit 1 record for a group of tests that were not done.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following example illustrates the single-record approach for representing a group of tests not done.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0052_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 52, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.1.2 [Tests Not Done]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a single record is used to represent a group of tests were not done:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 8, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
