{"atom_id": "ig34_p0054_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 54, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.3.1 Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0054_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 54, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors may have test descriptions (--TEST) longer than 40 characters in their operational database.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0054_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 54, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because the --TEST variable is meant to serve as a label for a --TESTCD when a Findings dataset is transposed to a more horizontal format, the length of --TEST is limited to 40 characters (except as noted below) to conform to the limitations of the SAS V5 transport file format (https://documentation.sas.com/).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0054_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 54, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Therefore, sponsors have the choice to either insert the first 40 characters or a text string abbreviated to 40 characters in --TEST.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0054_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 54, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors have the following options for including the full description for these variables in the study metadata:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0054_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 54, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If the annotated CRF contains the full text, provide a reference to the aCRF page containing the full test description in the Define-XML document origin definition for --TEST.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0054_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 54, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If the annotated CRF does not specify the full text, then the full text should be documented in the Define-XML document and/or other submission materials (e.g., the clinical study data reviewer's guide).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This convention should also be applied to the qualifier value label (QLABEL) in Supplemental Qualifiers (SUPP--) datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "IETEST values in the Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Not Met (IE) and Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria (TI) domains are exceptions to the 40-character rule and are limited to 200 characters, because these are not expected to be transformed to column labels.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Values of IETEST that exceed 200 characters should be described in study metadata as per the convention above.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.1 [Test Name (--TEST) Greater than 40 Characters]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "See Section 6.3.4, Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Not Met, assumption 3; and Section 7.4.1, Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria, assumption 5.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.4", "§7.4.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.3.2 Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Some sponsors may collect data values longer than 200 characters for some variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because of the current requirement for the SAS V5 transport file format, it is not possible to store long text strings using only 1 variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Therefore, the SDTMIG has defined conventions for storing long text strings using multiple variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For general observation-class variables and supplemental qualifiers (i.e., non-standard variables, NSVs), the conventions are as follows:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The first 200 characters of text should be stored in the parent domain variable and each additional 200 characters of text should be stored in a record in the SUPP-- dataset (see Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Parent Domain).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When splitting a text string into several records, the text should be split between words to improve readability.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "When the text longer than 200 characters is for a supplemental qualifier, the first QNAM should describe the NSV without any numeric suffix.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The value for QNAMs for additional text (>200 characters) should contain a sequential variable name, which is formed by appending a 1-digit integer, beginning with 1, to the original domain variable name.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The value for QLABEL should be the original domain variable label.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The reason a digit integer or suffix is not appended to the label is because the long text string represents a single value for a variable. The physical representation (i.e., SAS V5 transport file format) does not change the concept described by the label.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "This is different conceptually from when there are multiple values for a non-result qualifier variable and values are individually stored in SUPP--. In that case, both QNAM and QLABEL must be uniquely named (see Section 4.2.8.3, Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable) because they represent multiple values for a single variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "In cases where the standard domain variable name is already 8 characters in length, sponsors should replace the last character with a digit when creating values for QNAM. As an example, for Other Action Taken in Adverse Events (AEACNOTH), values for QNAM for the SUPPAE records would have the values AEACNOT1, AEACNOT2, and so on.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "AEACNOT1", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "AEACNOT2", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, the text entered for MHTERM was longer than 200 characters and required 2 supplemental qualifier variables for the text that extended beyond what could be represented in the standard variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "mh.xpt", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
