{"atom_id": "ig34_p0055_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 55, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, the text entered for AEACNOTH was longer than 200 characters, but required only 1 supplemental qualifier for the text that extended beyond what could be represented in the standard variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The first 200 characters of text should be stored in the variable and separate additional 200 characters of text in supplemental qualifiers.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When splitting a text string into several records, the text should be split between words to improve readability.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The value for QLABEL should be the original domain variable label.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "Text Strings >200 Char Conventions for General Supplemental Qualifier Variables | Text Strings >200 Char Conventions for COVAL and Related Columns | Text Strings >200 Char Conventions for TSVAL and Related Columns | Text Strings >200 Char Conventions for IETEST", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "The first 200 characters of text should be stored in the variable and separate additional 200 characters of text in the SUPP-- dataset | The first 200 characters of text should be stored in COVAL and each additional 200 characters of text stored in additional columns COVAL+ | The first 200 characters of text should be stored in TSVAL and each additional 200 characters of text stored in additional columns TSVALn | If the inclusion/exclusion criteria text is >200 characters, put meaningful text in IETEST and describe the full text of the criteria, if appropriate", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "When splitting a text string into several records, the text should be split between words to improve readability | When splitting a text string into several records, the text should be split between words | When splitting a text string into several records, the text should be split between words | Not applicable", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.3.2 [Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters in Other Variables]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "The value for QLABEL should be the original domain variable label | The variable labels for COVAL+ to COVALn should be \"Comment\" | The variable labels for TSVAL+ to TSVALn should be \"Parameter Value\" | Not applicable", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.4 Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because observations may originate from more than 1 source (e.g., investigator, independent assessor), observations recorded in the Findings class include the --EVAL qualifier.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0056_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 56, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For the Interventions and Events observation classes, which do not include the --EVAL variable, all data are assumed to be attributed to the principal investigator.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The QEVAL variable can be used to describe the evaluator for any data item in a SUPP-- dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "See Section 8.4.1, Supplemental Qualifiers—SUPP-- Datasets for additional detail.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example illustrates a case where an adjudication committee evaluated an adverse event.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The evaluations of the adverse event by the primary investigator were represented in the standard AE dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The evaluations of the adjudication committee were represented in SUPPAE.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.4 [Evaluators in the Interventions and Events Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "See Section 8.4, Relating Non-standard Variable Values to a Datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.5 [Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.5 Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.5 [Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For assessments of clinical significance when the overall interpretation is a record in the domain, use the --CLSIG (Clinically Significant) variable on the record that contains the overall interpretation or a particular result.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.5 [Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, EGCLSIG = \"Y\" indicates that an ECG result of \"ATRIAL FIBRILLATION\" was clinically significant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.5 [Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Separate from clinical significance are results of \"NORMAL\" or \"ABNORMAL\", or lab values that are out of normal range.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.5 [Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "An ECG test with EGTESTCD = \"INTP\" (which addresses the ECG as a whole) should have a result of or \"NORMAL\" or \"ABNORMAL\". A record for EGTESTCD = \"INTP\" may also have EGCLSIG indicating whether the result is clinically significant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.5 [Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A record for a vital signs measurement (e.g., systolic blood pressure) or a lab test (e.g., hematocrit) that contains a measurement may have a normal range and a normal range indicator. It could also have --CLSIG indicating whether the result is clinically significant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.6 Supplemental Reason Variables", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTM general observation classes include the --REASND variable to submit the reason a response is not present (a result in a findings class or an --OCCUR value in an events or interventions variable).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For Events and Interventions domains where specified occurrences have a reason for the \"Y\" or \"N\" value of --OCCUR, the reason can be represented with the variable --REASOC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "However, sponsors sometimes collect the reason that something was done.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For the Interventions general observation class, --INDC is available to represent the medical condition for which the intervention was given, and --ADJ is available to represent the reason for a dose adjustment.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For the Findings general observation class, --REASPE is available to represent the reason a test was performed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If the sponsor collects a reason for performing an activity represented in an Events domain where the topic is not a medical condition, or a reason for an intervention other than a medical indication, the reason can be represented in the SUPP-- dataset (as described in Section 8.4.1, Supplemental Qualifiers—SUPP--Datasets) using the supplemental qualifier with QNAM of \"--REAS\" listed in Appendix C1, Supplemental Qualifiers Name Codes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§8.4.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0057_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 57, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.6 [Supplemental Reason Variables]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If multiple reasons are reported, refer to Section 4.2.8.3, Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.7 Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Interventions (e.g., concomitant medications) and events (e.g., medical history) can generally be collected in 2 different ways, by recording either verbatim free text or the responses to a prespecified list of treatments or terms.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because the method of solicitation for information on treatments and terms may affect the frequency at which they are reported, whether they were prespecified or not may be of interest to reviewers.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The --PRESP variable is used to indicate whether a specific intervention (--TRT) or event (--TERM) was solicited.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The --PRESP variable has controlled terminology of \"Y\" (for \"Yes\") or a null value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It is a permissible variable, and should only be used when the topic variable values come from a prespecified list.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Questions such as \"Did the subject have any concomitant medications?\" or \"Did the subject have any medical history?\" should not have records in an SDTM domain because these are not valid values for the topic variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "(1) these are not valid values for the respective topic variables of CMTRT and MHTERM, and (2) records whose sole purpose is to indicate whether or not a subject had records are not meaningful.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The --OCCUR variable is used to indicate whether a prespecified intervention or event occurred or did not occur.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It has controlled terminology of \"Y\" and \"N\" (for \"Yes\" and \"No\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It is a permissible variable and may be omitted from the dataset if no topic-variable values were prespecified.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a study collects both prespecified interventions and events as well as free-text events and interventions, the value of --OCCUR should be \"Y\" or \"N\" for all prespecified interventions and events, and null for those reported as free text.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "Situation Probably reported event occurred | Value of --PRESP | Value of --OCCUR | Value of --STAT", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "Spontaneously reported event occurred | Y | Y | ", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "Prespecified event occurred | Y | Y | ", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "Prespecified event did not occur | Y | N | ", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "Prespecified event no response | Y |  | NOT DONE", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Collection design may prespecify specific treatments or terms or prespecify a group of treatments or terms (e.g., \"Was a short-acting bronchodilator taken in the 8 hours prior to spirometry?\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When an explicit question asks about the occurrence of a group of interventions or events, the group value should be represented in --TRT or --TERM, respectively.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0058_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 58, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.7 [Presence or Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Refer to the standard domains in the Events and Interventions general observation classes for additional assumptions and examples.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.8 Accounting for Long-term Follow-up", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 8, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Studies often include long-term follow-up assessments to monitor a subject's condition.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Use cases include studies in terminally ill populations that periodically assess survival and studies involving chronic disease that include follow-up to assess relapse.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Long-term follow-up is often conducted via telephone calls rather than clinic visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Regardless of the method of collection of the information, the data should be stored in the appropriate special domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Overall study conclusion in the Disposition (DS) domain occurs once all contact with the subject ceases.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a study has a clinical treatment phase followed by a long-term follow-up phase, these 2 segments of the study can be represented as separate epochs within the overall study, each with its own epoch disposition record.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following example illustrates the recommended SDTM approach to storing these data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "An oncology study encompasses 2 months of clinical treatment and assessments followed by once-monthly telephone contacts.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The contacts continue until the subject ceases or stops.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "During the telephone contacts, the investigator collects information on the subject's survival status and medication use.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The answers to certain questions may trigger other data collection.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, if the subject's survival status is \"dead\", then this indicates that the subject has ceased participation in the study, so a study discontinuation record would need to be created.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In SDTM, the data related to these follow-up telephone contacts should be stored as follows:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Concomitant medications reported during the contact should be stored in the CM domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The subject's survival status should be stored in the Subject Status (SS) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The disposition of the subject at the time of the final follow-up contact should be stored in DS. Note that overall study conclusion is the point where any contact with the subject ceases, which in this example is also the conclusion of long-term follow-up.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.2.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The disposition of the subject at the conclusion of the clinical treatment phase would be stored in DS as the conclusion to that epoch.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Long-term follow-up would be represented as a separate epoch.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Therefore, in this example the subject could have 3 disposition records in DS, with the following-up epoch disposition and the overall study conclusion disposition being collected at the final telephone contact.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.8 [Accounting for Long-term Follow-up]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If the subject's survival status is \"dead\", the Demographics (DM) variables DTHDT and DTHFL must be appropriately populated.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "4.5.9 Baseline Values", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+sibling_index_backfill+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The variable --LOBXFL was introduced in SDTMIG v3.3 to address the need for a consistent definition of a value that can serve as a reference with which to compare post-treatment values.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This generic baseline definition approximates the concept of baseline and can be used to calculate post-treatment changes.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In domains where --BLFL was expected, its core value was changed from expected to permissible and the variable --LOBXFL with a core value of expected, was added to contain the consistent definition.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In domains where --BLFL was permissible, the variable --LOBXFL was added with a core value of permissible.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "Variable Name | Structure Where It is Defined | Requirement in That Structure | Definition | Intended Use", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "--LOBXFL | SDTM Findings | Expected or Permissible | Last non-missing value prior to RFXSTDTC (operationally derived) | Consistent pre-treatment reference value baseline for use across all studies and sponsors", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ABLFL | ADaM BDS | Conditionally Required | Flags the record that is the source of the baseline value for a given parameter specified in the statistical analysis plan (SAP; may differ both across and within studies and datasets) | Baseline for ADaM analysis as specified in the SAP", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "--BLFL | SDTM Findings | Permissible (formerly Expected in some domains) | A baseline defined by the sponsor (could be derived in the same manner as --LOBXFL or --BE, but is required to be) | Any sponsor-defined baseline use", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As shown in the table, each variable serves a specific need.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SDTM variable --LOBXFL (and/or --BLFL, if used) can be copied to ADaM for traceability and transparency, but only the ADaM variable ABLFL would be used to signify baseline for analysis.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0059_a033", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 59, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§4.5.9 [Baseline Values]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The content of --LOBXFL and ABLFL will be exactly the same when the SAP specifies that the baseline used for analysis is the last non-missing value prior to RFXSTDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch06b_fix+page_relocate_60to59", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
