{"atom_id": "ig34_p0062_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 62, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DOMAIN | Domain Abbreviation | Char | DM | Identifier | Two-character abbreviation for the domain. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0062_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 62, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. This must be a unique value, and could be a compound identifier formed by concatenating STUDYID-SITEID-SUBJID. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0062_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 62, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SUBJID | Subject Identifier for the Study | Char | | Topic | Subject identifier, which must be unique within the study. Often the ID of the subject as recorded on a CRF. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFSTDTC | Subject Reference Start Date/Time | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Reference start date/time for the subject in ISO 8601 character format. Usually equivalent to date/time when subject was first exposed to study treatment. See assumption 9 for additional detail on when RFSTDTC may be null. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFENDTC | Subject Reference End Date/Time | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Reference end date/time for the subject in ISO 8601 character format. Usually equivalent to the date/time when subject was determined to have ended the trial, and often equivalent to date/time of last exposure to study treatment. Required for all randomized subjects; null for screen failures or unassigned subjects. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFXSTDTC | Date/Time of First Study Treatment | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | First date/time of exposure to any protocol-specified treatment or therapy, equal to the earliest value of EXSTDTC. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFXENDTC | Date/Time of Last Study Treatment | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Last date/time of exposure to any protocol-specified treatment or therapy, equal to the latest value of EXENDTC (or the latest value of EXSTDTC if EXENDTC was not collected or is missing). | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 8, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFCSTDTC | Date/Time of First Challenge Agent Admin | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Used only when protocol specifies a challenge agent to induce a condition that the investigational treatment is intended to cure, mitigate, treat, or prevent. Equal to the earliest value of AGSTDTC for the challenge agent. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFCENDTC | Date/Time of Last Challenge Agent Admin | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Used only when protocol specifies a challenge agent to induce a condition that the investigational treatment is intended to cure, mitigate, treat, or prevent. Equal to the latest value of AGENDTC for the challenge agent (or the latest value of AGSTDTC if AGENDTC was not collected or is missing). | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 10, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFICDTC | Date/Time of Informed Consent | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Date/time of informed consent in ISO 8601 character format. This will be the same as the date of informed consent in the Disposition domain, if that protocol milestone is documented. Would be null only in studies not collecting the date of informed consent. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 11, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "RFPENDTC | Date/Time of End of Participation | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Date/time when subject ended participation or follow-up in a trial, as defined in the protocol, in ISO 8601 character format. Should correspond to the last known date of contact. Examples include completion date, withdrawal date, last follow-up, date recorded for lost to follow up, and death date. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 12, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DTHDTC | Date/Time of Death | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Record Qualifier | Date/time of death for any subject who died, in ISO 8601 format. Should represent the date/time that is captured in the clinical-trial database. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 13, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DTHFL | Subject Death Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Indicates the subject died. Should be \"Y\" or null. Should be populated even when the death date is unknown. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 14, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
