{"atom_id": "ig34_p0063_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 63, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ARMCD | Planned Arm Code | Char | * | Record Qualifier | ARMCD is limited to 20 characters. It is not subject to the character restrictions that apply to TESTCD. The maximum length of ARMCD is longer than for other \"short\" variables to accommodate the kind of values that are likely to be needed for crossover trials. For example, if ARMCD values for a 7-period crossover were constructed using 2-character abbreviations for each treatment and separating hyphens, the length of [TRUNCATED_AT_PAGE_BOUNDARY] | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 24, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "(ARMCD continued) | ARMCD values would be 20. If the subject was not assigned to a trial arm, ARMCD is null and ARMNRS is populated. With the exception of studies which use multistage arm assignments, must be a value of ARMCD in the Trial Arms dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 24, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ARM | Description of Planned Arm | Char | * | Synonym Qualifier | Name of the arm to which the subject was assigned. If the subject was not assigned to an arm, ARM is null and ARMNRS is populated. With the exception of studies which use multistage arm assignments, must be a value of ARM in the Trial Arms dataset. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 25, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ACTARMCD | Actual Arm Code | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Code of actual arm. ACTARMCD is limited to 20 characters. It is not subject to the character restrictions that apply to TESTCD. The maximum length of ACTARMCD is longer than for other short variables to accommodate the kind of values that are likely to be needed for crossover trials. With the exception of studies which use multistage arm assignments, must be a value of ARMCD in the Trial Arms dataset. If the subject was not assigned to an arm or followed a course not described by any planned arm, ACTARMCD is null and ARMNRS is populated. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 26, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ACTARM | Description of Actual Arm | Char | * | Synonym Qualifier | Description of actual arm. With the exception of studies which use multistage arm assignments, must be a value of ARM in the Trial Arms dataset. If the subject was not assigned to an arm or followed a course not described by any planned arm, ACTARM is null and ARMNRS is populated. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 27, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ARMNRS | Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null | Char | (ARMNULRS) | Record Qualifier | A coded reason that arm variables (ARM and ARMCD) and/or actual arm variables (ACTARM and ACTARMCD) are null. Examples: \"SCREEN FAILURE\", \"NOT ASSIGNED\", \"ASSIGNED, NOT TREATED\", \"UNPLANNED TREATMENT\". It is assumed that if the arm and actual arm variables are null, the same reason applies to both arm and actual arm. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 28, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "(ARMNULRS)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ACTARMUD | Description of Unplanned Actual Arm | Char | | Record Qualifier | A description of actual treatment for a subject who did not receive treatment described in a planned trial arm. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 29, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "COUNTRY | Country | Char | | Record Qualifier | Country of the investigational site in which the subject participated in the trial. Generally represented using ISO 3166-1 Alpha-3. Note that regulatory agency specific requirements (e.g., US FDA) may require other terminologies; in such cases, follow regulatory requirements. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 30, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DMDTC | Date/Time of Collection | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time of demographic data collection. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 31, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DMDY | Study Day of Collection | Num | | Timing | Study day of collection measured as integer days. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 32, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "1In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0064_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 64, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "2Food and Drug Administration. Collection of Race and Ethnicity Data in Clinical Trials. US Department of Health and Human Services;2016. Accessed January 8, 2020. https://www.fda.gov/downloads/regulatoryinformation/guidances/ucm126396.pdf", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "DM –Assumptions", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. Investigator and site identification: Companies use different methods to distinguish sites and investigators.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "CDISC assumes that SITEID will always be present, with INVID and INVNAM used as necessary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This should be done consistently and the meaning of the variable made clear in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. Every subject in a study must have a subject identifier (SUBJID).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In some cases a subject may participate in more than 1 study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "To identify a subject uniquely across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product, a unique identifier (USUBJID) must be included in all datasets.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Subjects occasionally change sites during the course of a clinical trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors must decide how to populate variables such as USUBJID, SUBJID and SITEID based on their operational and analysis needs, but only 1 DM record should be submitted for each subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Supplemental Qualifiers dataset may be used if appropriate to provide additional information.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. Concerns for subject privacy suggest caution regarding the collection of variables like BRTHDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This variable is included in the Demographics model in the event that a sponsor intends to submit it; however, sponsors should follow regulatory guidelines and guidance as appropriate.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. With the exception of trials that use multistage processes to assign subjects to arms described below, ARM and ACTARM must be populated with ARM values from the Trial Arms (TA) dataset and ARMCD and ACTARMCD must be populated with ARMCD values from the TA dataset or be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The ARM and ARMCD values in the TA dataset have a one-to-one relationship, and that one-to-one relationship must be preserved in the values used to populate ARM and ARMCD in DM, and to populate the values of ACTARM and ACTARMCD in DM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Rules for the arm-related variables:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "i. If ARMCD is null, then ARM must be null and ARMNRS must be populated with the reason ARMCD is null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "ii. If ACTARMCD is null, then ACTARM must be null and ARMNRS must be populated with the reason ACTARMCD is null. Both ARMCD and ACTARMCD will be null for subjects who were not assigned to treatment. The same reason will provide the reason that both are null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "iii. ARMNRS may not be populated if both ARMCD and ACTARMCD are populated. ARMCD and ACTARMCD will be populated if the subject was assigned to an arm and received treatment consistent with 1 of the arms in the TA dataset. If ARMCD and ACTARMCD are not the same, that is sufficient to explain the situation; ARMNRS should not be populated.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "iv. If ARMNRS is populated with \"UNPLANNED TREATMENT\", ACTARMUD should be populated with a description of the unplanned treatment received.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "\"UNPLANNED TREATMENT\"", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. Multistage assignment to treatment: Some trials use a multistage process for assigning a subject to an arm (see Section 7.2.1, Trial Arms, Example Trial 3).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.2.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "See Section 7.2.1, Trial Arms, Example Trial 3", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.2.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In such a case, best practice is to create ARMCD values composed of codes representing the results of the multiple stages of the treatment assignment process.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a subject is partially assigned, then truncated codes representing the stages completed can be used in ARMCD, and similar truncated codes can be used in ACTARMCD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The descriptions used to populate ARM and ACTARM should be similarly truncated, and the one-to-one relationship between these truncated codes should be maintained for all affected subjects in the trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Example 3 below provides an example of this situation; see also Section 5.3, Subject Elements, Example 2.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
