{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "i. Example 1 below shows how to handle a subject who was a screen failure and was never treated.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "ii. The Subject Elements (SE) dataset records the series of elements a subject passed through in the course of a trial, and these determine the value of ACTARMCD. The following examples include sample data for both datasets to illustrate this relationship.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0065_a032", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 65, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.2 [Demographics (DM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. Example 2 below shows how subjects who started the trial but were never assigned to an arm would be handled.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07a_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When the values of the variables may be exactly the same, particularly with RFSTDTC-RFENDTC and RFXSTDTC-RFXENDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "However, there are certain study designs where the start of the reference period is defined differently, such as studies that have a washout period before randomization or have a medical procedure required during screening (e.g., biopsy).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In these cases, RFSTDTC may be the enrollment date, which is prior to first dose.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Because study day values are calculated using RFSTDTC, in this case study days would not be based on the date of first dose.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "RFXSTDTC and RFXENDTC always represent the date/time of first and last study exposure.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The study reference period often duplicates the reference period defined in RFSTDTC and RFENDTC, but not always.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Therefore, this pair of variables is important as they guarantee that a reviewer will always be able to reference the first and last study exposure period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "RFXSTDTC should be the same as SSTDTC for the first treatment element described in the SE dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§2.3.2.1 [Special-Purpose Domains: SE]"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "RFXENDTC may often be the same as the SEENDTC for the last treatment element described in the SE dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "RFCSTDTC and RFCENDTC always represent the date/time of first and last exposure to the challenge agent.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "They represent the entire period of a subject's involvement in a study, from providing informed consent through the last participation event or activity.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "There may be times when this period coincides with other reference periods but that is unusual.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "An example of when these periods might coincide with the study reference period, RFSTDTC to RFENDTC, might be an observational trial where no study intervention is administered.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "RFICIDITC should correspond to the date of the informed consent protocol milestone in Disposition (DS), if that protocol milestone is documented in DS.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In the event that there are multiple informed consents, this will be the date of the first.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "RFPENDTC will be the last date of any record for the subject in the database at the time it is locked for submission.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0066_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 66, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5 [General Observation Classes]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As such, it may not be the last date of participation in the study if the submission includes interim data.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch07b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
