{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "5.3 Subject Elements (SE)", "heading_level": 2, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SE – Description/Overview", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A special-purpose domain that contains the actual order of elements followed by the subject, together with the start date/time and end date/time for each element.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Subject Elements dataset consolidates information about the timing of each subject's progress through the study elements of the trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For elements that involve study treatments, the identification of which element the subject passed through (e.g., drug X vs. placebo) is likely to derive from data in the Exposure domain or another Interventions domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The dates of a subject's transition from one element to the next will be taken from the Interventions domain(s) and from other relevant domains, according to the definitions of ELEMENT values in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset (see Section 7.2.2, Trial Elements).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SE dataset is particularly useful for studies with multiple treatment periods, such as crossover studies.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SE dataset contains the date/times at which a subject moved from one element to another, so when this dataset, the Trial Arms (TA; see Section 7.2.1, Trial Arms) dataset, and the Trial Elements (TE; see Section 7.2.2, Trial Elements) dataset are included in a submission, reviewers can relate all observations made about a subject to that subject's progression through the trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix+F-B08-RA-5_verbatim_restore", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Comparison of the – DTC of a finding observation to the element transition dates (values of SESTDTC and SEENDTC) identifies which element the subject was in at the time of the finding. Similarly, one can determine the element during which an event or intervention started or ended.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "\"Day within Element\" or \"Day within Epoch\" can be derived. Such variables can relate an observation to the start of an element or epoch in the same way that study day (–DY) variables relate it to the reference start date (RFSTDTC) for the study as a whole. See Section 4.4.4, Use of the \"Study Day\" Variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Having knowledge of SE start and end dates can be helpful in the determination of baseline values.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SE – Specification", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "se.xpt, Subject Elements — Special Purpose. One record per actual Element per subject, Tabulation.", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "Variable Name | Variable Label | Type | Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format | Role | CDISC Notes | Core", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "STUDYID | Study Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Unique identifier for a study. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DOMAIN | Domain Abbreviation | Char | SE | Identifier | Two-character abbreviation for the domain. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0079_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 79, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SESEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. Should be assigned in to be consistent chronological order. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ETCD | Element Code | Char | * | Topic | 1. ETCD (the companion to ELEMENT) is limited to 8 characters and does not have special character restrictions. These values should be short for ease of use in programming, but it is not expected that ETCD will need to serve as a variable name. 2. If an element occurs more than once in a study protocol, it is considered a new element, then use \"UNPLAN\" as the value for ETCD to represent this element. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "ELEMENT | Description of Element | Char | * | Synonym Qualifier | The name of the element. If ETCD has a value of \"UNPLAN\", the value for ELEMENT would be as specified in the Comment Concepts) section after a comment in the CRF.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "TAETORD | Planned Order of Element within Arm | Num | | Timing | Number that gives the planned order of the elements within the subject's assigned trial arm.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 7, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the element in the planned sequence of elements for the arm to which the subject was assigned.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 8, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SESTDTC | Start Date/Time of Element | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Start date/time for an element for each subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 9, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
