{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SESTDY | Study Day of Start of Element | Num | | Timing | Study day of start of element relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 11, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SEENDY | Study Day of End of Element | Num | | Timing | Study day of end of element relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 12, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix+F-B08-RA-6_Core_column_added", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SEUPDES | Description of Unplanned Element | Char | | Synonym Qualifier | Description of what happened to the subject during an unplanned element. Used only if ETCD has the value of \"UNPLAN\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 13, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "*In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SE – Assumptions", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix+sibling_index_backfill", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Submission of the SE dataset is strongly recommended, as it provides information needed by reviewers to place observations in context within the study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "As noted in the SE - Description/Overview, the TE and TA datasets should also be submitted, as these define the design and the terms referenced by the SE dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SE domain allows the submission of data on the timing of the trial elements a subject actually passed through in their participation in the trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Section 7.2.2, Trial Elements, and Section 7.2.1, Trial Arms, provide additional information on these datasets, which define a trial's planned elements and describe the planned sequences of elements for the arms of the trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For any particular subject, the dates in the SE table are the dates when the transition events identified in the TE table occurred. Judgment may be needed to match actual events in a subject's experience with the definitions of transition events (i.e., events that mark the start of new elements) in the TE table; actual events may vary from the plan.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For instance, in a single-dose pharmacokinetics (PK) study, the transition events might correspond to study drug doses of 5 and 10 mg. If a subject actually received a dose of 7 mg when they were scheduled to receive 5 mg, a decision will have to be made on how to represent this in the SE domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Judgment will also have to be used in deciding how to represent a subject's experience if an element does not proceed or end as planned.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0080_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 80, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For instance, the plan might identify a trial element that is to start with the first dose of a series of 5 daily doses and end 1 week after the subject transitions to the next treatment element. If the subject actually started the next treatment epoch (see Section 7.1, Introduction to Trial Design Model Datasets, and Section 7.1.2, Definitions of Trial Design Concepts) after a comment in the CRF, whether the sponsor would have to decide whether to represent this as an abnormally long element, or as a normal element plus an unplanned non-treatment element.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+batch08b_fix", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. If the sponsor decides that the subject's experience for a particular period of time cannot be represented with one of the planned elements, then that period of time should be represented as an unplanned element. The value of ETCD for an unplanned element is \"UNPLAN\" and SEUPDES should be populated with a description of the unplanned element.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. The values of SESTDTC provide the chronological order of the actual subject elements. SESEQ should be assigned to be consistent with the chronological order. Note that the requirement that SESEQ be consistent with chronological order is more stringent than in most other domains, where --SEQ values need only be unique within subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "6. When TAETORD is included in the SE domain, it represents the planned order of an element in an arm. This should not be confused with the actual order of the elements, which will be represented by their chronological order and SESEQ. TAETORD will not be populated for subject elements that are not planned for the arm to which the subject was assigned. Thus, TAETORD will not be populated for any element with an ETCD value of \"UNPLAN\". TAETORD also will not be populated if a subject passed through an element that, although defined in the TE dataset, was out of place for the arm to which the subject was assigned. For example, if a subject in a parallel study of drug A vs. drug B was assigned to receive drug A but received drug B instead, then TAETORD would be left blank for the SE record for their drug B element. If a subject was assigned to receive the sequence of elements A, B, C, D, and instead received A, D, B, C, then the sponsor would have to decide for which of these SE records TAETORD should be populated. The rationale for this decision should be documented in the Comments column of the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "7. For subjects who follow the planned sequence of elements for the arm to which they were assigned, the values of EPOCH in the SE domain will match those associated with the elements for the subject's arm in the TA dataset. The sponsor will have to decide what value, if any, of EPOCH to assign SE records for unplanned elements and in other cases where the subject's actual elements deviate from the plan. The sponsor's methods for such decisions should be documented in the Define-XML document, in the row for EPOCH in the SE dataset table.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "8. Because there are, by definition, no gaps between elements, the value of SEENDTC for one element will always be the same as the value of SESTDTC for the next element.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "9. Note that SESTDTC is required, although --STDTC is not required in any other subject-level dataset. The purpose of the dataset is to record the elements a subject actually passed through. If it is known that a subject passed through a particular element, then there must be some information (perhaps imprecise) on when it started. Thus, SESTDTC may not be null, although some records may not have all the components (e.g., year, month, day, hour, minute) of the date/time value collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "10. The following identifier variables are permissible and may be added as appropriate: --GRPID, --REFID, --SPID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "11. Care should be taken in adding additional timing variables:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. The purpose of --DTC and --DY is to record the date and study day on which data was collected. Elements are generally \"derived\" in the sense that they are a secondary use of data collected elsewhere; it is not generally useful to know when those date/times were recorded.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. --DUR could be added only if the duration of an element was collected, not derived.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. It would be inappropriate to add the variables that support time points (--TPT, --TPTNUM, --ELTM, --TPTREF, and --RFTDTC), because the topic of this dataset is elements.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SE – Examples", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0081_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 81, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "STUDYID and DOMAIN, which are required in the SE and Demographics (DM) domains, have not been included in the following examples, to improve readability.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§5.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows data for 2 subjects for a crossover trial with 4 epochs.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Row 1: The record for the SCREEN element for subject 789. Note that only the date of the start of the SCREEN element was collected, whereas for the end of the element (which corresponds to the start of IV dosing) both date and time were collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Row 2: The record for the IV element for subject 789. The IV element started with the start of IV dosing and ended with the start of oral dosing, and full date/times were collected for both.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Row 3: The record for the ORAL element for subject 789. Only the date, and not the time, of the start of follow-up was collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Row 4: The FOLLOWUP element for subject 789 started and ended on the same day. Presumably, the element had a positive duration, but no times were collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Rows 5-8: Subject 790 was treated incorrectly. This subject entered the IV element before the ORAL element, although the planned order of elements for this subject was ORAL, then IV. The sponsor has assigned EPOCH values for this subject according to the actual order of elements, rather than the planned order. Per Assumption 6, TAETORD is missing for the elements that were out of order. The correct order of elements is the subject's ARMCD, shown in the DM dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Rows 9-10: Subject 791 was screened, randomized to the IV-ORAL arm, and received the IV treatment, but did not return to the unit for the treatment epoch or follow-up.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0082_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 82, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.3 [Subject Elements (SE)]", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "se.xpt", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
