{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char |  | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SMSEQ | Sequence Number | Num |  | Identifier | Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of subject records. Should be assigned to be consistent chronological order. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "MIDS | Disease Milestone Instance Name | Char | * | Topic | Name of the specific disease milestone. For types of disease milestones that can occur multiple times, the name will end with a sequence number. Example: \"HYPO1\". | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "MIDSTYPE | Disease Milestone Type | Char | * | Record Qualifier | The type of disease milestone. Example: \"HYPOGLYCEMIC EVENT\". | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SMSTDTC | Start Date/Time of Milestone | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Start date/time of milestone instance (if milestone is an intervention or event) or date of milestone (if Milestone is a finding). | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SMENDTC | End Date/Time of Milestone | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | End date/time of disease milestone instance. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SMSTDY | Study Day of Start of Milestone | Num |  | Timing | Study day of start of disease milestone instance, relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SMENDY | Study Day of End of Milestone | Num |  | Timing | Study day of end of disease milestone instance, relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "¹In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SM – Assumptions", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. Disease milestones are observations or activities whose timings are of interest in the study. The types of disease milestones are defined at the study level in the TM dataset. The purpose of the SM dataset is to provide a summary timeline of the milestones for a particular subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. The name of the disease milestone is recorded in MIDS.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0084_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 84, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. For disease milestones that can occur only once (TMRPT = \"N\"), the value of MIDS may be the value in MIDSTYPE or may an abbreviated version.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. For types of disease milestones that can occur multiple times, MIDS will usually be an abbreviated version of MIDSTYPE and will always end with a sequence number. Sequence numbers should start with 1 and indicate the chronological order of the instances of this type of disease milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. The timing variables SMSTDTC and SMENDTC hold start and end date/times of data collected for the disease milestone(s) for each subject. SMSTDY and SMENDY represent the corresponding study day variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. The start date/time of the disease milestone is the critical date/time, and must be populated. If the disease milestone is an event, then the meaning of \"start date\" for the event may need to be defined.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. The start study day will not be populated if the start date/time includes only a year or only a year and month.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. The end date/time for the disease milestone is less important than the start date/time. It will not be populated if the disease milestone is a finding without an end date/time or if it is an event or intervention for which an end date/time has not yet occurred or was not collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. The end study day will not be populated if the end date/time includes only a year or only a year and month.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SM – Examples", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this study, the disease milestones of interest were initial diagnosis and hypoglycemic events, as shown in Section 7.3.3, Trial Disease Milestones, Example 1.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.3.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Row 1: Shows that subject 001's initial diagnosis of diabetes occurred in October 2005. Because this is a partial date, SMDY is not populated. No end date/time was recorded for this milestone.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Rows 2-3: Show that subject 001 had 2 hypoglycemic events. In this case, only start date/times have been collected. Because these date/times include full dates, SMSTDY has been populated in each case.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Row 4: Shows that subject 002's initial diagnosis of diabetes occurred on May 15, 2010. Because a full date was collected, the study day of this milestone was populated. Diagnosis was pre-study, so the study day of the disease milestone is negative. No hypoglycemic events were recorded for this subject.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
