{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Information in SM is taken from records in other domains. In this study, diagnosis was represented in the Medical History (MH) domain, and hyypoglycemic events were represented in the Clinical Events (CE) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0085_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 85, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§5.4 [Subject Disease Milestones (SM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The MH records for diabetes (MHEVDTYP = \"DIAGNOSIS\") are the records which represent the disease milestones for the defined MIDSTYPE of \"DIAGNOSIS\", so these records include the MIDS variable with the value \"DIAG\". Because these are records for disease milestones rather than associated records, the variables RELMIDS and MIDSDTC are not needed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
