{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SV – Description/Overview", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A special purpose domain that contains information for each subject's actual and planned visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The Subject Visits domain consolidates information about the timing of subject visits that is otherwise spread over domains that include the visit variables (VISITNUM and possibly VISIT and/or VISITDY).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Unless the beginning and end of each visit is collected, populating the SV dataset will involve derivations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In a simple case, where, for each subject visit, exactly 1 date appears in every such domain, the SV dataset can be created easily by populating both SVSTDTC and SVENDTC with the single date for a visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When there are multiple dates and/or date/times for a visit for a particular subject, the derivation of values for SVSTDTC and SVENDTC may be more complex.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The method for deriving these values should be consistent with the visit definitions in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset (see Section 7.3.1, Trial Visits).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.3.1", "Trial Visits (TV)"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For some studies, a visit may be defined to correspond with a clinic visit that occurs within 1 day, whereas for other studies, a visit may reflect data collection over a multiday period.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The SV dataset provides reviewers with a summary of a subject's visits over the course of their participation in a study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Comparison of an individual subject's SV dataset with the TV dataset, which describes the planned visits for the trial, supports the identification of planned but not completed visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": [], "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0086_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 86, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Comparison of the values of SVSTDY and SVENDY to VISIT and/or VISITDY can often highlight departures from the planned timing of visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
