{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "SVUPDES | Description of Unplanned Visit | Char | | Record Qualifier | Description of what happened to the subject during an unplanned visit. Only populated for unplanned visits. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "SV – Assumptions", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Subject Visits domain allows the submission of data on the timing of the trial visits for a subject, including both those visits they actually passed through in their participation in the trial and those visits that did not occur. Refer to Section 7.3.1, Trial Visits (TV), as the TV dataset defines the planned visits for the trial.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§7.3.1", "Trial Visits (TV)"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Subjects can have 1 and only 1 record per VISITNUM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Subjects who screen fail, withdraw, die, or otherwise discontinue study participation will not have records for planned visits subsequent to their final disposition event.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Planned and unplanned visits with a subject, whether or not they are physical visits to the investigational site, are represented in this domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. SVPRESP = \"Y\" identifies rows for planned visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. For planned visits, SVOCCUR indicates whether the visit occurred.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. For unplanned visits, SVPRESP and SVOCCUR are null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. See Section 4.5.7, Presence of/Absence of Prespefified Interventions and Events, for more information on the use of --PRESP and --OCCUR.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": ["§4.5.7"], "cross_refs": ["§4.5.7", "Presence of/Absence of Prespecified Interventions and Events"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The identification of an actual visit with a planned visit sometimes calls for judgment. In general, data collection forms are prepared for particular visits, and the fact that data was collected on a form labeled with a planned visit is sufficient to make the association. Occasionally, the association will not be so clear, and the sponsor will need to make decisions about how to label actual visits. The sponsor's rules for making such decisions should be documented in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0087_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 87, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Records for unplanned visits should be included in the SV dataset. For unplanned visits, SVUPDES can be populated with a description of the reason for the unplanned visit. Some judgment may be required to determine what constitutes an unplanned visit. When data are collected outside a planned visit, that act of collecting data may or may not be described as a \"visit.\" The encounter should generally be treated as a visit if data from the encounter are included in any domain for which VISITNUM is included; a record with a missing value for VISITNUM is generally less useful than a record with [TRUNCATED_AT_PAGE_BOUNDARY]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "VISITNUM populated. If the occasion is considered a visit, its date/times must be included in the SV table and a value of VISITNUM must be assigned. Refer to Section 4.4.5, Clinical Encounters and Visits, for information on the population of visit variables in unplanned visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.5", "Clinical Encounters and Visits"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The variable SVCNTMOD is used to record the way in which the visit was conducted. For example, for visits to a clinic, SVCNTMOD = \"IN PERSON\", visits conducted remotely might have values such as \"TELEPHONE CALL\", \"REMOTE AUDIO VIDEO\", or \"IVRS\". If there are multiple contact modes, refer to Section 4.2.8.3, Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": ["§4.2.8.3"], "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.3", "Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The planned study day of visit variable (VISITDY) should not be populated for unplanned visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If SVSTDY is included, it is the actual study day corresponding to SVSTDTC. In studies for which VISITDY has been populated, it may be desirable to populate SVSTDY, as this will facilitate the comparison of planned (VISITDY) and actual (SVSTDY) study days for the start of a visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "If SVENDY is included, it is the actual day corresponding to SVENDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "For many studies, all visits are assumed to occur within 1 calendar day, and only 1 date is collected for the visit. In such a case, the values for SVENDTC duplicate values in SVSTDTC. However, if the data for a visit is actually collected over several physical visits and/or over several days, then SVSTDTC and SVENDTC should reflect this fact. Note that it is fairly common for screening data to be collected over several days, but for the data to be treated as belonging to a single planned screening visit, even in studies for which all other visits are single-day visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Differentiating between planned and unplanned visits may be challenging if unplanned assessments (e.g., repeat labs) are performed during the time period of a planned visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Algorithms for populating SVSTDTC and SVENDTC from the dates of assessments performed at a visit may be particularly challenging for screening visits, since baseline values collected at a screening visit are sometimes historical data from tests performed before the subject started screening for the trial. Therefore dates prior to informed consent are not part of the determination of SVSTDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The following Identifier variables are permissible and may be added as appropriate: --SEQ, --GRIDID, --REFID, and --SPID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Care should be taken in adding additional timing variables:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. If TAETORD and/or EPOCH are added, then the values must be those at the start of the visit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. The purpose of --DTC and --DY in other domains with start and end dates (Event and Intervention Domains) is to record the date on which data was collected. For a visit that occurred, it is not necessary to submit the date on which information about the visit was recorded. When SVPRESP = \"Y\" and SVOCCUR = \"N\", --DTC and --DY are available for use to represent the date on which it was recorded that the visit did not take place.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. --DUR could be added if the duration of a visit was collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. It would be inappropriate to add the variables that support time points (--TPT, --TPTNUM, --ELTM, --TPTREF, and --RFTDTC), because the topic of this dataset is visits.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0088_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 88, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§5.5 [Subject Visits (SV)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "e. --STRF and --ENRF could be used to say whether a visit started and ended before, during, or after the study reference period, although this seems unnecessary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
