{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| STUDYID | Study Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Unique identifier for a study. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| DOMAIN | Domain Abbreviation | Char | AG | Identifier | Two-character abbreviation for the domain. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined reference number. May be preprinted on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number from the procedure or test page. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGLNKID | Link ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to link related records across domains.This may be a one-to-one or a one-to-many relationship. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGLNKGRP | Link Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to link related records across domains.This will usually be a many-to-one relationship. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGTRT | Reported Agent Name | Char | | Topic | Verbatim medication name that is either preprinted or collected on a CRF. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGMODIFY | Modified Reported Name | Char | | Synonym Qualifier | If AGTRT is modified to facilitate coding, then AGMODIFY will contain the modified text. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGDECOD | Standardized Agent Name | Char | * | Synonym Qualifier | Standardized or dictionary-derived text description of AGTRT or AGMODIFY. Equivalent to the generic medication name in WHO Drug. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document. If an intervention term does not have a decode value in the dictionary, then AGDECOD will be left blank. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGCAT | Category for Agent | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of agent. Examples: \"CHALLENGE AGENT\", \"PET TRACER\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSCAT | Subcategory for Agent | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Further categorization of agent. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0092_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 92, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGPRESP | AG Pre-Specified | Char | (NY) | Variable Qualifier | Used to indicate whether (\"Y\"/null) information about the use of a specific agent was solicited on the CRF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGOCCUR | AG Occurrence | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | When the use of specific agent is solicited, AGOCCUR is used to indicate whether (\"Y\"/\"N\") use of the agent occurred. Values are null for agents not specifically solicited. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate that a question about a prespecified agent was not answered. Should be null or have a value of \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGREASND | Reason Procedure Agent Not Collected | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes the reason a response to a question about the occurrence of a procedure agent was not collected. Used in conjunction with AGSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGCLAS | Agent Class | Char | * | Variable Qualifier | Drug class. May be obtained from coding. When coding to a single class, populate with class value. If using a dictionary and coding to multiple classes, follow guidance in Section 4.2.8.3, Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable, or omit AGCLAS. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGCLASCD | Agent Class Code | Char | * | Variable Qualifier | Class code corresponding to AGCLAS. Drug class. May be obtained from coding. When coding to a single class, populate with class code. If using a dictionary and coding to multiple classes, follow guidance in Section 4.2.8.3, Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable, or omit AGCLASCD. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGDOSE | Dose per Administration | Num | | Record Qualifier | Amount of AGTRT taken. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGDOSTXT | Dose Description | Char | | Record Qualifier | Dosing amounts or a range of dosing information collected in text form. Units may be stored in AGDOSU. Examples: \"200-400\", \"15-20\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGDOSU | Dose Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Units for AGDOSE and AGDOSTXT. Examples: \"ng\", \"mg\", \"mg/kg\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGDOSFRM | Dose Form | Char | (FRM) | Variable Qualifier | Dose form for AGTRT. Examples: \"TABLET\", \"AEROSOL\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGDOSFRQ | Dosing Frequency per Interval | Char | (FREQ) | Record Qualifier | Usually expressed as the number of repeated administrations of AGDOSE within a specific time period. Example: \"ONCE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGROUTE | Route of Administration | Char | (ROUTE) | Variable Qualifier | Route of administration for AGTRT. Example: \"ORAL\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITNUM | Visit Number | Num | | Timing | 1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISIT | Visit Name | Char | | Timing | 1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITDY | Planned Study Day of Visit | Num | | Timing | Planned study day of the visit based upon RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TAETORD | Planned Order of Element within Arm | Num | | Timing | Number that gives the planned order of the element within the arm for the element in which the agent administration started. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the start date/time of the agent administration started. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSTDTC | Start Date/Time of Agent | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | The date/time when administration of the treatment indicated by AGTRT and the dosing variables began. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGENDTC | End Date/Time of Agent | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | The date/time when administration of the treatment indicated by AGTRT and the dosing variables ended. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSTDY | Study Day of Start of Agent | Num | | Timing | Study day of start of agent relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGENDY | Study Day of End of Agent | Num | | Timing | Study day of end of agent relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGDUR | Duration of Agent | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Collected duration for an agent episode. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0093_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 93, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSTRF | Start Relative to Reference Period | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Describes the start of the agent relative to sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| | | | | | (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics). If information such as \"PRIOR\", \"ONGOING\", or \"CONTINUING\" was collected, this information may be translated into AGSTRF. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGENRF | End Relative to Reference Period | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Describes the end of the agent relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics). If information such as \"PRIOR\", \"ONGOING\", or \"CONTINUING\" was collected, this information may be translated into AGENRF. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSTRTPT | Start Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Identifies the start of the agent as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable AGSTTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGSTTPT | Start Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by AGSTRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-15\", \"VISIT 1\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGENRTPT | End Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Identifies the end of the agent as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable AGENTPT. Identifies the end of the agent as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable AGENTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AGENTPT | End Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by AGENRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-25\", \"VISIT 2\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "1In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "AG – Assumptions", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. Purpose of the domain: Some tests involve administration of substances, and it has been unclear in which domain these should be represented.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. The Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM) domain seemed particularly inappropriate when the substance was one that would never be given as a medication. Even substances that are medications are not being used as such when they are given as part of a testing procedure.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. The Exposure (EX) domain also seemed inappropriate; although the testing procedure might be part of the study plan, these data would not be used or analyzed in the same way as data about study treatments. The AG domain was created to fill this gap.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. The AG domain has advantages over the Procedures (PR) domain for this purpose. It allows recording of multiple substance administrations for a single testing procedure. It also separates data about substance administrations from data about procedures that do not involve substance administration.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. Information about the conduct of the procedure with which the procedure agent administration was associated, if collected, should be represented in the PR domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. Examples and structure", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0094_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 94, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Examples of agents administered as part of a procedure include a short-acting bronchodilator administered as part of a reversibility assessment and contrast agents or radio-labeled substances used in imaging studies.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. The structure of the AG domain is 1 record per agent intervention episode, or prespecified agent assessment per subject. It is the sponsor's responsibility to define an intervention episode. This definition may vary based on the sponsor's requirements for review and analysis.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. AG description and coding", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. AGTRT captures the name of the agent and it is the topic variable. It is a required variable and must have a value. AGTRT should include only the agent name, and should not include dosage, formulation, or other qualifying information. For example, \"ALBUTEROL 2 PUFF\" is not a valid value for AGTRT. This example should be expressed as AGTRT = \"ALBUTEROL\", AGDOSE = \"2\", AGDOSU = \"PUFF\", and AGDOSFRM = \"AEROSOL\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. AGMODIFY should be included if the sponsor's procedure permits modification of a verbatim term for coding.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. AGDECOD is the standardized agent term derived by the sponsor from the coding dictionary. It is possible that the reported term (AGTRT) or the modified term (AGMODIFY) can be coded using a standard dictionary. In such cases, sponsors are expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. Prespecified terms; presence or absence of procedure agents", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. AGPRESP is used to indicate whether an agent was prespecified.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. AGOCCUR is used to indicate whether a prespecified agent was used. A value of \"Y\" indicates that the agent was used and \"N\" indicates that it was not.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. If an agent was not prespecified, the value of AGOCCUR should be null. AGPRESP and AGOCCUR are permissible fields and may be omitted from the dataset if all agents were collected as free text. Values of AGOCCUR may also be null for prespecified agents if no Y/N response was collected; in this case, AGSTAT = \"NOT DONE\", and AGREASND could be used to describe the reason the answer was missing.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. Any identifier variables, timing variables, or interventions general observation-class qualifiers may be added to the AG domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. However, --INDC, although allowed, would not generally be used because substance administrations represented in AG are given as part of a testing procedure rather than with therapeutic intent.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. The variables --DOSTOT and --DOSRGM, although allowed, would generally not be used because procedure agents are likely to be recorded at the level of single administrations.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "AG – Examples", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example captures data about the allergen administered to the subject as part of a bronchial allergen challenge (BAC) test. Prior to the BAC, the subject had a skin-prick allergen test to help identify the allergen to be used for the BAC test. The skin-prick test identified grass as the allergen to be used in the BAC test. Data from the allergen skin test are not shown, but the CRF for the BAC includes collection of the allergen chosen for use in the BAC. A predetermined set of ascending doses of the chosen allergen was used in the screening BAC test. The results of the screening BAC are not shown, but would be represented in the Respiratory System Findings (RE) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Row 1:      The first dose given in the BAC was saline.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0095_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 95, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.1 [Procedure Agents (AG)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Rows 2-4:   Three successively higher doses of grass allergen were given.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
