{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DOMAIN | Domain Abbreviation | Char | CM | Identifier | Two-character abbreviation for the domain. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined reference number. Example: a number preprinted on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or record identifier defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: line number on a concomitant medication page. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMTRT | Reported Name of Drug, Med, or Therapy | Char | | Topic | Verbatim medication name that is either preprinted or collected on a CRF. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMMODIFY | Modified Reported Name | Char | | Synonym Qualifier | If CMTRT is modified to facilitate coding, then CMMODIFY will contain the modified text. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDECOD | Standardized Medication Name | Char | | Synonym Qualifier | Standardized or dictionary-derived text description of CMTRT or CMMODIFY. Equivalent to the generic drug name in WHO Drug. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document. If an intervention term does not have a decode value in the dictionary, then CMDECOD will be left blank. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMCAT | Category for Medication | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of medications/treatment. Examples: \"PRIOR\", \"CONCOMITANT\", \"ANTI-CANCER MEDICATION\", \"GENERAL CONMED\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSCAT | Subcategory for Medication | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of medications/treatment. Examples: \"CHEMOTHERAPY\", \"HORMONAL THERAPY\", \"ALTERNATIVE THERAPY\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMPRESP | CM Pre-specified | Char | (NY) | Variable Qualifier | Used to indicate whether (\"Y\"/null) information about the use of a specific medication was solicited on the CRF. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMOCCUR | CM Occurrence | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | When the use of a specific medication is solicited, CMOCCUR is used to indicate whether (\"Y\"/\"N\") use of the medication occurred. Values are null for medications not specifically solicited. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate that a question about the occurrence of a prespecified intervention was not answered. Should be null or have a value of \"NOT DONE\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMREASND | Reason Medication Not Collected | Char | | Record Qualifier | Reason not done. Used in conjunction with CMSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMINDC | Indication | Char | | Record Qualifier | Denotes why a medication was taken or administered. Examples: \"NAUSEA\", \"HYPERTENSION\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0098_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 98, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMCLAS | Medication Class | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Drug class. May be obtained from coding. When coding to a single class, populate with class value. If using a dictionary and coding to multiple classes, then follow Section 4.2.8.3, Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable, or omit CMCLAS. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMCLASCD | Medication Class Code | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Class code corresponding to CMCLAS. Drug class. May be obtained from coding. When coding to a single class, populate with class code. If using a dictionary and coding to multiple classes, then follow Section 4.2.8.3, Multiple Values for a Non-result Qualifier Variable, or omit CMCLASCD. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.2.8.3"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDOSE | Dose per Administration | Num | | Record Qualifier | Amount of CMTRT given. Not populated when CMDOSTXT is populated. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDOSTXT | Dose Description | Char | | Record Qualifier | Dosing amounts or a range of dosing information collected in text form. Units may be stored in CMDOSU. Examples: \"200-400\", \"15-20\". Not populated when CMDOSE is populated. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDOSU | Dose Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Units for CMDOSE, CMDOSTOT, or CMDOSTXT. Examples: \"ng\", \"mg\", \"mg/kg\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDOSFRM | Dose Form | Char | (FRM) | Variable Qualifier | Dose form for CMTRT. Examples: \"TABLET\", \"LOTION\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDOSFRQ | Dosing Frequency per Interval | Char | (FREQ) | Record Qualifier | Usually expressed as the number of repeated administrations of CMDOSE within a specific time period. Examples: \"BID\" (twice daily), \"Q12H\" (every 12 hours). | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDOSTOT | Total Daily Dose | Num | | Record Qualifier | Total daily dose of CMTRT using the units in CMDOSU. Used when dosing is collected as total daily dose. Total dose over a period other than day could be recorded in a separate supplemental qualifier variable. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDOSRGM | Intended Dose Regimen | Char | | Record Qualifier | Text description of the (intended) schedule or regimen for the Intervention. Example: \"TWO WEEKS ON, TWO WEEKS OFF\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMROUTE | Route of Administration | Char | (ROUTE) | Variable Qualifier | Route of administration for the intervention. Examples: \"ORAL\", \"INTRAVENOUS\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMADJ | Reason for Dose Adjustment | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes reason or explanation of why a dose is adjusted. Examples: \"ADVERSE EVENT\", \"INSUFFICIENT RESPONSE\", \"NON-MEDICAL REASON\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMRSDISC | Reason the Intervention Was Discontinued | Char | | Record Qualifier | When dosing of a treatment is recorded over multiple successive records, this variable is applicable only for the (chronologically) last record for the treatment. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "TAETORD | Planned Order of Element within Arm | Num | | Timing | Number that gives the planned order of the element within the arm for the element in which the medication administration started. Null for medications that started before study participation. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the start date/time of the medication administration. Null for medications that started before study participation. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSTDTC | Start Date/Time of Medication | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Start date/time of the medication administration represented in ISO 8601 character format. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMENDTC | End Date/Time of Medication | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | End date/time of the medication administration represented in ISO 8601 character format. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSTDY | Study Day of Start of Medication | Num | | Timing | Study day of start of medication relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMENDY | Study Day of End of Medication | Num | | Timing | Study day of end of medication relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMDUR | Duration | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Collected duration for a treatment episode. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSTRF | Start Relative to Reference Period | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Describes the start of the medication relative to sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics). If information such as \"PRIOR\" was collected, this information may be translated into CMSTRF. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0099_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 99, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMENRF | End Relative to Reference Period | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Describes the end of the medication relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics). If information such as \"PRIOR\", \"ONGOING\", or \"CONTINUING\" was collected, this information may be translated into CMENRF. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSTRTPT | Start Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Identifies the start of the medication as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable CMSTTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMSTTPT | Start Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference time point referred to by CMSTRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-15\", \"VISIT 1\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMENRTPT | End Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Identifies the end of the medication as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable CMENTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "CMENTPT | End Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference time point referred to by CMENRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-25\", \"VISIT 2\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "1In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "CM – Assumptions", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. The structure of the CM domain is 1 record per medication intervention episode, constant-dosing interval, or prespecified medication assessment per subject. It is the sponsor's responsibility to define an intervention episode. This definition may vary based on the sponsor's requirements for review and analysis. The submission dataset structure may differ from the structure used for collection. One common approach is to submit a new record when there is a change in the dosing regimen. Another approach is to collapse all records for a medication to a summary level with either a dose range or the highest dose level. Other approaches may also be reasonable as long as they meet the sponsor's evaluation requirements.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. CM description and coding", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. CMTRT is the topic variable and captures the name of the concomitant medication/therapy or the prespecified term used to collect information about the occurrence of any of a group of medications and/or therapies. It is a required variable and must have a value. CMTRT only includes the medication/therapy name and does not include dosage, formulation, or other qualifying information. For example, \"ASPIRIN 100MG TABLET\" is not a valid value for CMTRT. This example should be expressed as CMTRT= \"ASPIRIN\", CMDOSE= \"100\", CMDOSU= \"MG\", and CMDOSFRM= \"TABLET\". When referring to a prespecified group of medications/therapies, CMTRT contains the description of the group used to solicit the occurrence response.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. CMMODIFY should be included if the sponsor's procedure permits modification of a verbatim term for coding.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. CMDECOD is the standardized medication/therapy term derived by the sponsor from the coding dictionary. It is expected that the reported term (CMTRT) or the modified term (CMMODIFY) will be coded using a standard dictionary. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. When CMDECOD values from the WHODrug Dictionary are longer than 200 characters, split the values at semicolons rather than spaces when implementing guidance in Section 4.5.3.2, Text Strings Greater than 200 Characters.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.5.3.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. Prespecified terms; presence or absence of concomitant medications", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0100_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 100, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Information on concomitant medications is generally collected in 2 different ways, either by recording free text or using a prespecified list of terms. Because the solicitation of information on specific concomitant medications may affect the frequency at which they are reported, the fact that a specific medication was solicited may be of interest to reviewers. CMPRESP and CMOCCUR are used together to indicate whether the intervention in CMTRT was prespecified and whether it occurred, respectively.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R9", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "CMOCCUR is used to indicate whether a prespecified medication was used.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "A value of \"Y\" indicates that the medication was used and \"N\" indicates that it was not.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If a medication was not prespecified, the value of CMOCCUR should be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "CMPRESP and CMOCCUR are permissible fields and may be omitted from the dataset if all medications were collected as free text.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Values of CMOCCUR may also be null for prespecified medications if no Y/N response was collected; in such cases, CMSTAT = \"NOT DONE\", and CMREASND could be used to describe the reason the answer was missing.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Variables for timing relative to a time point", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "CMSTRTPT, CMSTPPT, CMENRTPT, and CMENTPT may be populated as necessary to indicate when a medication was used relative to specified time points.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For example, assume a subject uses birth control medication.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The subject has used the same medication for many years and continues to do so.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The date the subject began using the medication (or at least a partial date) would be stored in CMSTDTC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "CMENDC could be used to indicate that the use is unknown/has not yet happened.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This fact can be recorded by setting CMENTPT = \"2007-04-30\" (the date the assessment was made) and CMENRTPT = \"ONGOING\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Although any identifier variables, timing variables, or interventions general observation-class qualifiers may be added to the CM domain, the following qualifiers would generally not be used: --MOOD, --LOT.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "CM – Examples", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Sponsors collect the timing of concomitant medication use with varying specificity, depending on the pattern of use; the type, purpose, and importance of the medication; and the needs of the study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "It is often unnecessary to record every unique instance of medication use, since the same information can be conveyed with start and end dates and frequency of use.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "If appropriate, medications taken as needed (intermittently or sporadically over a time period) may be reported with a start and end date and a frequency of \"PRN\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The example below shows 3 subjects who took the same medication on the same day.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-6: For subject ABC-0001, each instance of aspirin use was recorded separately, and the frequency in each record is (CMDOSFRQ) is \"ONCE\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 7-9: For subject ABC-0002, frequency was once a day (\"QD\") in the first and third records (where CMSEQ = \"1\" and \"3\"), but twice a day in the second record (where CMSEQ = \"2\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0101_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 101, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.2 [Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 10: Records for subject ABC-0003 are collapsed into a single entry that spans the relevant time period, with a frequency of \"PRN\". This is shown as an example only, not as a recommendation. This approach assumes that knowing exactly when aspirin was used is not important for evaluating safety and efficacy in the study.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
