{"atom_id": "ig34_p0103_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 103, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.3 [Exposure Domains]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Clinical trial study designs can range from open label (where subjects and investigators know which product each subject is receiving) to blinded (where the subject, investigator, or anyone assessing the outcome is unaware of the treatment assignment(s) to reduce potential for bias).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10+option_E_rerun_p103+trim_to_first_sentence", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z", "note": "trimmed_2-sentence_paragraph_to_first_sentence_only_per_IR2; second sentence moved to a022 (option E salvage)"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0103_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 103, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.1.3 [Exposure Domains]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "To support standardization of various collection methods and details, as well as process differences between open-label and blinded studies, 2 SDTM domains based on the Interventions General Observation Class are available to represent details of subject exposure to protocol-specified study treatment(s): Exposure (EX) and Exposure as Collected (EC).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "main-session-option-E-salvage", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R10+option_E_salvage_p103_a022", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z", "note": "Recovered from original 11a writer (oh-my-claudecode:writer) a006 verbatim; Option E rerun executor captured §6.1.3 intro as 1 SENTENCE instead of 2; this re-inserts the second sentence missed by rerun. PDF p.103 §6.1.3 intro is one paragraph with 2 sentences, atomized per IR2 v1.1 M2 (1 sentence = 1 atom)."}}
