{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a015", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 15, "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCIBI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a016", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 16, "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "ML – Assumptions", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a017", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 17, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The ML domain is used to represent consumption of any food or nutritional item that would not be represented in the exposure domains (EC/EX), Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM), Procedure Agents (AG), or Substance Use (SU). Examples of nutritional items that would not be represented in other domains include:", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a018", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 18, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Investigational nutritional products (represented in EC/EX)", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a019", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 19, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Food or drink used to treat hypoglycemic events (represented in CM)", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a020", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 20, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Glucose given as part of a glucose tolerance test (represented in AG)", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a021", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 21, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Caffeinated drinks (represented in SU)", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a022", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 22, "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The nutritional items represented in ML may be prospectively defined within a protocol, collected retrospectively as potential precipitants of clinical events, and/or to describe nutritional intake.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a023", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 23, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Additional timing variables", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a024", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 24, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Any additional timing variables may be added to this domain.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a025", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 25, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Consumption of a food product is considered to occur over an interval of time (as opposed to a point in time). If start and end date/times are collected, they should be represented in MLSTDTC and MLENDTC, respectively. If only a start date/time is collected, it should not be copied to MLENDTC.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0122_a026", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 122, "atom_index_on_page": 26, "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Any identifier variables, timing variables, or findings general observation-class qualifiers may be added to the ML domain, but the following qualifiers would generally not be used: --MOOD, --LOT, --LOC, --LAT, --DIR, --PORTOT.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15"}
