{"atom_id": "ig34_p0124_a007", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 124, "atom_index_on_page": 7, "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example describes a study that examines the effect of physical modifications in a cafeteria on selection/consumption among school students.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15+OptionE_p124_rerun"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0124_a008", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 124, "atom_index_on_page": 8, "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "Group | Arms | Details", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15+OptionE_p124_rerun"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0124_a009", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 124, "atom_index_on_page": 9, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "1 | Control | Students received standard meals in a standard cafeteria environment.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15+OptionE_p124_rerun"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0124_a010", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 124, "atom_index_on_page": 10, "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "2 | Experimental: choice architecture | Students were exposed to modifications to the physical environment in the cafeteria to \"nudge\" students towards healthier choices. Physical modifications included: Placing vegetables at the beginning of the lunch line Placing fruits in attractive bowls, trays lined with appealing fabric, and fruit options next to cash registers Promoting fruits and vegetables with prominently displayed signage and images Placing white milk selection more predominantly than chocolate milk (e.g., white milk displayed in front of chocolate milk)", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15+OptionE_p124_rerun"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0124_a011", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 124, "atom_index_on_page": 11, "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Food-card data was collected over a 7-month period by students receiving a school meal 1 day per week.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15+OptionE_p124_rerun"}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0124_a012", "source": "SDTMIG v3.4 (no header footer).pdf", "source_short": "ig34", "page": 124, "atom_index_on_page": 12, "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Students who brought a lunch from home or those not eating lunch in the cafeteria on a study day were excluded.", "parent_section": "§6.1.4 [Meal Data (ML)]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "cross_refs": null, "figure_ref": null, "table_ref": null, "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+TOC_anchor+R1-R15+OptionE_p124_rerun"}
