{"atom_id": "ig34_p0134_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 134, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AECAT | Category for Adverse Event | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of related records. Examples: \"BLEEDING\", \"NEUROPSYCHIATRIC\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0134_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 134, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESCAT | Subcategory for Adverse Event | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of adverse event. Example: \"NEUROLOGIC\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0134_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 134, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEPRESP | Pre-Specified Adverse Event | Char | (NY) | Variable Qualifier | A value of \"Y\" indicates that this adverse event was prespecified on the CRF. Values are null for spontaneously reported events (i.e., those collected as free-text verbatim terms). | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0134_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 134, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEBODSYS | Body System or Organ Class | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Dictionary derived. Body system or organ class used by the sponsor from the coding dictionary (e.g., MedDRA). When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor's analyses and summary tables, which may not necessarily be the primary SOC. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "| Variable Name | Variable Label | Type | Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format1 | Role | CDISC Notes | Core |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEBDSYCD | Body System or Organ Class Code | Num | MedDRA | Variable Qualifier | Dictionary derived. Code for the body system or organ class used by the sponsor. When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor's analyses and summary tables, which may not necessarily be the primary SOC. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESOC | Primary System Organ Class | Char | MedDRA | Variable Qualifier | Dictionary-derived text description of the primary SOC. Will be the same as AEBODSYS if the primary SOC was used for analysis. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESOCCD | Primary System Organ Class Code | Num | MedDRA | Variable Qualifier | Dictionary-derived code for the primary SOC. Will be the same as AEBDSYCD if the primary SOC was used for analysis. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AELOC | Location of Event | Char | (LOC) | Record Qualifier | Describes anatomical location relevant for the event (e.g., \"ARM\" for skin rash). | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESEV | Severity/Intensity | Char | (AESEV) | Record Qualifier | The severity or intensity of the event. Examples: \"MILD\", \"MODERATE\", \"SEVERE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESER | Serious Event | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Is this a serious event? Valid values are \"Y\" and \"N\". | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEACN | Action Taken with Study Treatment | Char | (ACN) | Record Qualifier | Describes changes to the study treatment as a result of the event. AEACN is specifically for the relationship to study treatment. AEACNOTH is for actions unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment. Examples of AEACN values include ICH E2B values: \"DRUG WITHDRAWN\", \"DOSE REDUCED\", \"DOSE INCREASED\", \"DOSE NOT CHANGED\", \"UNKNOWN\" and \"NOT APPLICABLE\". | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEACNOTH | Other Action Taken | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes other actions taken as a result of the event that are unrelated to dose adjustments of study treatment. Usually reported as free text. Example: \"TREATMENT UNBLINDED. PRIMARY CARE PHYSICIAN NOTIFIED\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEACNDEV | Action Taken with Device | Char | (DEACNDEV) | Record Qualifier | An action taken with a device as the result of the event. The device may or may not be a device under study. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEREL | Causality | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Records the investigator's opinion as to the causality of the event to the treatment. ICH does not establish any required or recommended terms for non-device relatedness. ICH E2A and E2B examples include (up-cased here for alignment to SDTM conventions) terms such as \"NOT RELATED\", \"UNLIKELY RELATED\", \"POSSIBLY RELATED\", \"RELATED\", but these example terms do not establish any conventions or expectations. Controlled terminology may be defined in the future. Check with regulatory authority for population of this variable. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AERLDEV | Relationship of Event to Device | Char | * | Record Qualifier | A judgment as to the likelihood that the device caused the adverse event. The relationship is to a device identified in the data (i.e., has an SPDEVID). The device may be ancillary or under study. Terminology: In the EU, follow the European Commission Guidelines on Medical Devices, Clinical Investigations: SAE Reporting (MEDDEV 2.7/3) (e.g., Not Related, Unlikely, Possible, Probable, Causal Relationship), with device-specific definitions. No required Controlled Terminology in US. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AERELNST | Relationship to Non-Study Treatment | Char | | Record Qualifier | Records the investigator's opinion as to whether the event may have been due to a treatment other than study drug. May be reported as free text. Example: \"MORE LIKELY RELATED TO ASPIRIN USE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEPATT | Pattern of Adverse Event | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate the pattern of the event over time. Examples: \"INTERMITTENT\", \"CONTINUOUS\", \"SINGLE EVENT\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AEOUT | Outcome of Adverse Event | Char | (OUT) | Record Qualifier | Description of the outcome of an event. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESCAN | Involves Cancer | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Was the serious event associated with the development of cancer? Valid values are \"Y\" and \"N\". This is a legacy seriousness criterion. It is not included in ICH E2A or E2B. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESCONG | Congenital Anomaly or Birth Defect | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Was the serious event associated with congenital anomaly or birth defect? Valid values are \"Y\" and \"N\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESDISAB | Persist or Signif Disability/Incapacity | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Did the serious event result in persistent or significant disability/incapacity? Valid values are \"Y\" and \"N\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0135_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 135, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| AESDTH | Results in Death | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Did the serious event result in death? Valid values are \"Y\" and \"N\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R10..R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
