{"atom_id": "ig34_p0141_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 141, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 3 | ABC123 | AE | 123101 | 3 | HEADACHE | Headache | | Nervous system disorders | MILD | N | DOSE NOT CHANGED | POSSIBLY RELATED | RECOVERED/RESOLVED | TREATMENT | 2005-10-21 | 2005-10-21 | 11 | 11 |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0141_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 141, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Example 3", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0141_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 141, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, a CRF module that asked whether or not nausea, vomiting, or diarrhea occurred was included in the study only once. In the context of this study, the conditions that occurred were reportable as adverse events. No additional data about these events was collected. No other AE information was collected via general questions. The responses to the probing questions \"Yes\", \"No\", or \"Not Done\" were represented in the FA domain (see Section 6.4, Findings About Events or Interventions). This is an example of unusually sparse AE data collection; the AE dataset is populated with the term and the flag indicating that it was prespecified, but timing information is limited to the date of collection, and other expected qualifiers are not available. RELREC may be used to relate AE records and FA records.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.4"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0141_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 141, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.1 [Adverse Events (AE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The subject shown in this example experienced nausea and vomiting. The subject did not experience diarrhea, so no record for that term exists in the AE dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
