{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BESEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of records within a dataset for a subject. May be any valid number (including decimals) and does not have to start at 1. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Optional group identifier, used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEREFID | Reference ID | Char | | Identifier | Internal or external identifier for the specimen affected or created by the event. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BESPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Optional sponsor-defined reference number. Example: Line number on a CRF page. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BETERM | Reported Term for the Biospecimen Event | Char | | Topic | Topic variable for an event observation, which is the verbatim or pre-specified name of the event. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEMODIFY | Modified Reported Term | Char | | Synonym Qualifier | If the value for BETERM is modified for coding purposes, then the modified text is placed here. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEDECOD | Dictionary-Derived Term | Char | (BEDECOD) | Synonym Qualifier | Dictionary-derived text description of BETERM or BEMODIFY, if applicable. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BECAT | Category for Biospecimen Event | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of topic-variable values. Example: COLLECTION, PREPARATION, TRANSPORT. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BESCAT | Subcategory for Biospecimen Event | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of BECAT values. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BELOC | Anatomical Location of Event | Char | (LOC) | Record Qualifier | Describes the anatomical location relevant for the event (e.g. BRAIN, LUNG). | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEPARTY | Accountable Party | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Party accountable for the transferable object (e.g. specimen) as a result of the activity performed in the associated BETERM variable. The party could be an individual (e.g. subject), an organization (e.g., sponsor), or a location that is a proxy for an individual or organization (e.g., site). It is usually a somewhat general term that is further identified in the BEPRTYID variable. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0143_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 143, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEPRTYID | Identification of Accountable Party | Char | | Record Qualifier | Identification of the specific party accountable for the transferable object (e.g. Specimen) after the action in BETERM is taken. Used in conjunction with BEPARTY. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITNUM | Visit Number | Num | | Timing | Clinical encounter number. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISIT | Visit Name | Char | | Timing | Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITDY | Planned Study Day of Visit | Num | | Timing | Planned study day of VISIT. Should be an integer. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEDTC | Date/Time of Specimen Collection | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date and time of specimen collection. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BESTDTC | Start Date/Time of Biospecimen Event | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Start date/time of the event. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEENDTC | End Date/Time of Biospecimen Event | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | End date/time of the event. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BESTDY | Study Day of Start of Biospecimen Event | Num | | Timing | Actual study day of start of observation expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEENDY | Study Day of End of Biospecimen Event | Num | | Timing | Actual study day of end of observation expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| BEDUR | Duration of Biospecimen Event | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Collected duration and unit of a biospecimen event. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from start and end date/times. Example: P1DT2H (for 1 day, 2 hours). | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "BE – Assumptions", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. The BE domain contains data about actions taken that affect or may affect a specimen, such as specimen collection, freezing and thawing, aliquoting, and transportation. This domain is intended to be applicable to any specimen tracking data, regardless of the reason for specimen collection.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. The value in BEREFID identifies the specimen most affected by the event. For aliquoting, this would be the child specimen(s) created by the event, rather than the parent specimen. BEREFID should not contain any identifiers other than specimen IDs.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. BELOC holds the relevant anatomic location of the subject, so it should only be populated when the subject participates in and is directly affected by the event given in BETERM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. BEPARTY and BEPRTYID together identify the individual or organization that takes responsibility for the biospecimen as a result of the action in BETERM. For example, if BETERM is COLLECTED, BEPARTY would be a general term defining the type of responsible party, such as SITE, and BEPRTYID would contain the site identifier, such as 02. If BEPARTY is sufficient to uniquely identify the party (such as SPONSOR in a single-sponsor study), then BEPRTYID may be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. Usually BEPARTY and BEPRTYID refer to who has possession of the biospecimen after the action in BETERM. In the cases where a biospecimen is lost or destroyed for example, BEPARTY and BEPRTYID may be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "6. Timing variables:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. BESTDTC and BEENDTC hold the start and end date/times for the event given in BETERM. If the end date/time is the same as the start date/time for the event, then BEENDTC is null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0144_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 144, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. Unlike other Events domains, BEDTC does not hold the date/time of data collection. Instead, it holds the date/time of specimen collection, in alignment with the use of --DTC for specimen-related findings. BEDTC values for extracted or otherwise derived specimens are copied from that of the parent specimen.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. VISITNUM, VISIT, and VISITDY values for all records refer to the visit in which the originally collected specimen was collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "7. The following variables generally would not be used in BE: dictionary coding variables (--LLT, --LLTCD, --PTCD, --HLT, --HLTCD, --HLGT, --HLGTCD), AE-specific variables (--SEV, --SER, --ACN, --ACNOTH, --ACNDEV, --REL, --RELNST, --PATT, --OUT, --SCAN, --SCONG, --SDISAB, --SDTH, --SHOSP, --SLIFE, --SOD, --SMIE, --CONTRT), toxicity variables (--TOX, --TOXGR).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "BE – Examples", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z", "action_p145_a004": "OptionH_R15_sibling_continuity_Example1_SENTENCE_to_HEADING_L5_sib1", "ts_p145_a004": "2026-04-25T08:39:09.200979+00:00"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, a specimen is collected, flash frozen, thawed, and shipped to another location.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Some tests are very sensitive to specimen handling processes such as flash freezing or time spent in transit. Therefore, it is important to record when the processes were started and completed. Such information is recorded in the BE domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 1: Shows specimen collection. The value in SPDEVID for this row identifies the vessel into which the specimen is collected.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 2-4: Show the start and end date/times of flash freezing, storing while frozen, and thawing. The value in SPDEVID for row 3 identifies the freezer in which the specimen is stored.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 5: Records the transportation of a biospecimen. Because there is only one ABC Lab, BEPRTYID is null. The value in SPDEVID for this row identifies the shipping container.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
