{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Findings related to specimen handling processes are stored in the Biospecimen (BS) domain. These processes can be important to maintain the integrity of the specimens used in genetic variation and gene expression testing. Depending on how a study is designed, there might be very specific specimen handling specifications contained in the protocol for all labs to follow. Other protocols may let the labs determine the processes to follow. This example illustrates the latter approach.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 1: Shows the volume of the biospecimen.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0145_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 145, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 2-3: Show the flash freeze temperature and material, associated via RELREC with BE row 2.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
