{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 2", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace", "action_p146_a016": "OptionH_R15_sibling_continuity_Example2_L4sib1_to_L5sib2", "ts_p146_a016": "2026-04-25T08:39:09.200979+00:00"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Cell-free RNA, which can be obtained from plasma, may be useful for some tumor-specific cancer detection,[1] but has poor integrity.[2]In this example, a blood sample was drawn, centrifuged to get plasma, and stored in a pretreated container before being shipped to the lab. The lab then extracted and purified RNA from the plasma, divided the RNA into 3 aliquots, and sequenced 1 aliquot immediately while freezing and storing the other 2 for later use.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["[1]", "[2]"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 1:\tShows the collection of the blood sample.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 2:\tShows the extraction of the plasma via centrifuge. BESPDEVID holds the identifier for the container into which the plasma is placed. (Not shown: any preservatives with which the container comes pretreated, which would be stored in the Device Properties (DO) domain.)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 3:\tShows the transportation of the plasma from the site to the lab.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 4:\tShows the extraction of the RNA, which includes purification and quality control testing to make sure the sample is of a high enough quality to be viable. BESPDEVID holds the identifier for the purification kit.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 5-7:\tShow the aliquoting of the RNA.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0146_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 146, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 8:\tShows the sequencing of the first RNA aliquot. (Not shown: results from sequencing, which would be stored in the Pharmacogenomics Findings (PF) domain.)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 6, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal_repair", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p146_wholesale_replace"}}
