{"atom_id": "ig34_p0147_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 147, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The specimen type is given in a supplemental qualifier that mimics the standard findings variable --SPEC, and draws from the 2 codelists (GENSMP and SPECTYPE) for its values, depending on whether or not the biospecimen is a sample of the subject's genetic material.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["GENSMP", "SPECTYPE"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p147_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0147_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 147, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Rows 1-2:\tGive the specimen types for the first 2 specimens as blood and plasma, respectively. These values come from the SPECTYPE codelist.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["SPECTYPE"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p147_wholesale_replace"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0147_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 147, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.2 [Biospecimen Events (BE)]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Rows 3-6:\tGive the specimen type for all subsequent specimens as RNA. \"RNA\" is one of the terms in the GENSMP codelist.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["GENSMP"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15+drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-25T08:37:25.202985+00:00", "action": "OptionE_p147_wholesale_replace"}}
