{"atom_id": "ig34_p0149_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 149, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.3 [Clinical Events (CE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| CESEV | Severity/Intensity | Char | (SEVYRS) | Record Qualifier | The severity or intensity of the event. Examples: \"MILD\", \"MODERATE\", \"SEVERE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0149_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 149, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.3 [Clinical Events (CE)]", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| CETOXGR | Standard Toxicity Grade | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Toxicity grade according to a standard toxicity scale (e.g., Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events (CTCAEv5.0)). Sponsor should specify grade numbering scheme and whether a text grade value is from a numeric scale, represented only by the numeric scale, or both. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+R15", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
