{"atom_id":"ig34_p0161_a0011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":161,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This below represents a multidrug (isoniazid and levofloxacin) investigational treatment trial for multidrug-resistant tuberculosis (MDR-TB). The protocol allows for a subject to discontinue levofloxacin and continue single treatment of isoniazid throughout the remainder of the study. Disposition of study participation and disposition of each drug was collected. Whether a record with DSCAT = \"DISPOSITION EVENT\" represents disposition of the subject's participation in the study or disposition of a study treatment is represented in DSSCAT. In this example, disposition of the study and of each drug a subject received for each of the study's 2 treatment epochs.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0161_a0012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":161,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 1:\tIndicates that the physician, per protocol, removed levofloxacin treatment due to high-level positive cultures. This record represents the treatment discontinuation for levofloxacin, for the first treatment epoch. Note that because this subject did not receive levofloxacin during the second treatment epoch, there is no record for DSCAT = \"LEVOFLOXACIN\" with EPOCH = \"TREATMENT 2\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0161_a0013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":161,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 2, 4:\tRepresent the treatment continuation and completion for isoniazid each treatment epoch, as indicated by DSSCAT = \"ISONIAZID\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0161_a0014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":161,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 3, 5:\tRepresent the study disposition for each treatment epoch, as indicated by DSSCAT = \"STUDY PARTICIPATION\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
