{"atom_id": "ig34_p0167_a0004", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 3: Shows disposition of study participation for the screening epoch. The subject completed this epoch.", "parent_section": "§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 167, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_OptionE", "rerun_reason": "writer_17b_corruption_p166_167"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0167_a0005", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 4: Shows that drug C was ended during the second cycle (TAETORD = \"2\") of the treatment epoch.", "parent_section": "§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 167, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_OptionE", "rerun_reason": "writer_17b_corruption_p166_167"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0167_a0006", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 5: Shows that drugs A and B were ended on the same day during the third cycle (TAETORD = \"6\") of the treatment epoch.", "parent_section": "§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 167, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_OptionE", "rerun_reason": "writer_17b_corruption_p166_167"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0167_a0007", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 6: Shows disposition of study participation in the treatment epoch. The subject did not complete treatment, due to disease progression. The date of disposition of the treatment epoch, DSSTDTC, is the date the subject started the follow-up epoch. For this study, that was defined as 4 weeks after the start of the last treatment element. This means that although the subject's last dose of treatment was \"2015-04-14\", the end of the treatment period was later, on \"2015-04-26\", when the subject started the follow-up treatment.", "parent_section": "§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 167, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_OptionE", "rerun_reason": "writer_17b_corruption_p166_167"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0167_a0008", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 7: Shows disposition of study participation in the follow-up epoch. The subject died.", "parent_section": "§6.2.4 Disposition (DS)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 167, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_OptionE", "rerun_reason": "writer_17b_corruption_p166_167"}}
