{"atom_id": "ig34_p0168_a0022", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| HODUR | Duration of Healthcare Encounter | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Collected duration of the healthcare encounter. Used only if collected on the CRF and not derived from the start and end datetimes. Example: \"PT 2 days 2 hours\". | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 168, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0168_a0023", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| HOSTRTPT | Start Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STERPT) | Timing | Identifies the start of the observation as being before or after the sponsor-defined reference time point defined by variable =STRTPT. Timing Variables. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 168, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0168_a0024", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| HOSTIPT | Start Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the sponsor-defined reference point referred to by STRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-15\", \"VISIT 1\". | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 168, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0001", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| HOENRTPT | End Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STERPT) | Timing | Identifies the end of the event as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable HOENTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0002", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| HOENTPT | End Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by HOENTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-25\", \"VISIT 2\". | Perm |", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0003", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "¹In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0004", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "HO – Assumptions", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0005", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The Healthcare Encounters (HO) dataset includes inpatient and outpatient healthcare events (e.g., hospitalizations, nursing home stays, rehabilitation facility stays, ambulatory surgery).", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0006", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Values of HOTERM typically describe the location or place of the healthcare encounter (e.g., \"HOSPITAL\" rather than \"HOSPITALIZATION\"). HOSTDTC should represent the start or admission date and HOENDTC the end or discharge date.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0007", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Data collected about healthcare encounters may include the reason for the encounter. The following supplemental qualifiers may be appropriate for representing such data:", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0008", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. The supplemental qualifier with QNAM = \"HOINDC\" would be used to represent the indication/medical condition for the encounter (e.g., stroke). Note that --INDC is an Interventions class variable, so is not a standard variable for HO, which is an Events class domain.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0009", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. The supplemental qualifier with QNAM = \"HOREAS\" would be used to represent a reason for the encounter other than a medical condition (e.g., annual checkup).", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0010", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. If collected data includes the name of the provider or the facility where the encounter took place, this may be represented using the supplemental qualifier with QNAM = \"HONAM\". Note that --NAM is a Findings class variable, so is not a standard variable for HO, which is an Events class domain.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0011", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. Any identifier variables, timing variables, or Events general observation-class qualifiers may be added to the HO domain, but the following Qualifiers would generally not be used: --SER, --ACN, --ACNOTH, --REL, --RELNST, --SCAN, --SCONG, --SDISAB, --SDTH, --SHOSP, --SLIFE, --SOD, --SMIE, --BODYS, --LOC, --SEV, --TOX, --TOXGR, --PATT, --CONTRT.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0012", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "HO – Examples", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0013", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 1, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0014", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, a healthcare encounter CRF collects verbatim descriptions of the encounter.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0015", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-2: Subject ABC123101 was hospitalized and then moved to a nursing home.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0016", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 3-5: Subject ABC123102 was in a hospital in the general ward and then in the intensive care unit. This same subject was transferred to a rehabilitation facility.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0169_a0017", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 6-7: Subject ABC123103 has 2 hospitalization records.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 169, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
