{"atom_id": "ig34_p0170_a0001", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, the dates of an initial hospitalization are collected as well as the date/time of ICU stay.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 170, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0170_a0002", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Subsequent to discharge from the initial hospitalization, follow-up healthcare encounters, including admission to a rehabilitation facility, visits with healthcare providers, and home nursing visits were collected.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 170, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0170_a0003", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Repeat hospitalizations are categorized separately.", "parent_section": "§6.2.5 Healthcare Encounters (HO)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "page": 170, "extracted_by": {"agent": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7"}}
