{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain for a subject. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHREFID | Reference ID | Char | | Identifier | Internal or external medical history identifier. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined reference number. May be preprinted on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Line number on a Medical History CRF page. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHTERM | Reported Term for the Medical History | Char | | Topic | Verbatim or preprinted CRF term for the medical condition or event. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHMODIFY | Modified Reported Term | Char | | Synonym Qualifier | If MHTERM is modified to facilitate coding, then MHMODIFY will contain the modified text. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHDECOD | Dictionary-Derived Term | Char | * | Synonym Qualifier | Dictionary-derived text description of MHTERM or MHMODIFY. Equivalent to the Preferred Term (PT in MedDRA). The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHEVDTYP | Medical History Event Date Type | Char | (MHEDTTYP) | Variable Qualifier | Specifies the aspect of the medical condition or event by which MHSTDTC and/or the MHENDTC is defined. Examples: \"DIAGNOSIS\", \"SYMPTOMS\", \"RELAPSE\", \"INFECTION\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHCAT | Category for Medical History | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of related records. Examples: \"CARDIAC\", \"GENERAL\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHSCAT | Subcategory for Medical History | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of the condition or event. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHPRESP | Medical History Event Pre-Specified | Char | (NY) | Variable Qualifier | A value of \"Y\" indicates that this medical history event was prespecified on the CRF. Values are null for spontaneously reported events (i.e., those collected as free-text verbatim terms). | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0171_a0028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 171, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHOCCUR | Medical History Occurrence | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used when the occurrence of specific medical history conditions is solicited, to indicate whether (\"Y\"/\"N\") a medical condition (MHTERM) had ever occurred. Values are null for spontaneously reported events. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | The status indicates that the prespecified question was not asked/answered. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHREASND | Reason Medical History Not Collected | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes the reason why data for a prespecified condition was not collected. Used in conjunction with MHSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHBODSYS | Body System or Organ Class | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Dictionary-based. Body system or organ class that is involved in an event or measurement from a standard hierarchy (e.g., MedDRA). When using a multi-axial dictionary such as MedDRA, this should contain the SOC used for the sponsor's analyses and summary tables which may not necessarily be the primary SOC. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TAETORD | Planned Order of Element within Arm | Num | | Timing | Number that gives the planned order of the element within the arm for the element in which the assessment was made. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the start date/time of the medical history event. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHDTC | Date/Time of History Collection | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Collection date and time of the medical history observation represented in ISO 8601 character format. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHSTDTC | Start Date/Time of Medical History Event | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Start date/time of the medical history event represented in ISO 8601 character format. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHENDTC | End Date/Time of Medical History Event | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | End date/time of the medical history event. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHDY | Study Day of History Collection | Num | | Timing | Study day of medical history collection, measured as integer day. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHENRF | End Relative to Reference Period | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Describes the end of the event relative to the sponsor-defined reference period. The sponsor-defined reference period is a continuous period of time defined by a discrete starting point and a discrete ending point (represented by RFSTDTC and RFENDTC in Demographics). Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHENRTPT | End Relative to Reference Time Point | Char | (STENRF) | Timing | Identifies the end of the event as being before or after the reference time point defined by variable MHENTPT. Not all values of the codelist are allowable for this variable. See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| MHENTPT | End Reference Time Point | Char | | Timing | Description or date/time in ISO 8601 character format of the reference point referred to by MHENRTPT. Examples: \"2003-12-25\", \"VISIT 2\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "1In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "MH – Assumptions", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. Prior treatments, including prior medications and procedures, should be submitted in an appropriate dataset from the Interventions class (e.g., Concomitant/Prior Medications (CM) or Procedures (PR)).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. MH description and coding", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. MHTERM is the topic variable and captures the verbatim term collected for the condition or event or the prespecified term used to collect information about the occurrence of any of a group of conditions or events. MHTERM is a required variable and must have a value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0172_a0018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 172, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. MHMODIFY is a permissible variable and should be included if the sponsor's procedure permits modification of a verbatim term for coding. The modified term is listed in MHMODIFY. The variable should be populated as per the sponsor's procedures; null values are permitted.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. If the sponsor codes the reported term (MHTERM) using a standard dictionary, then MHDECOD will be populated with the preferred term derived from the dictionary. The sponsor is expected to provide the dictionary name and version used to map the terms utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. MHBODSYS is the system organ class (SOC) from the coding dictionary associated with the adverse event by the sponsor. This value may differ from the primary SOC designated in the coding dictionary's standard hierarchy.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "e. If a CRF collects medical history by prespecified body systems and the sponsor also codes reported terms using a standard dictionary, then MHDECOD and MHBODSYS are populated using the standard dictionary. MHCAT and MHSCAT should be used for the prespecified body systems.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. Additional categorization and grouping", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. MHCAT and MHSCAT may be populated with the sponsor's predefined categorization of medical history events, which are often prespecified on the CRF. Note that even if the sponsor uses the body system terminology from the standard dictionary, MHBODSYS and MHCAT may differ; MHBODSYS is derived from the coding system, whereas MHCAT is effectively assigned when the investigator records a condition under the prespecified category.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "i. This categorization should not group all records (within the MH domain) into one generic group such as \"Medical History\" or \"General Medical History\" because this is redundant information with the domain code. If no smaller categorization can be applied, then it is not necessary to include or populate this variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "ii. Examples of MHCAT could include \"General Medical History\" (see above assumption; if \"General Medical History\" is an MHCAT value, then there should be other MHCAT values), \"Allergy Medical History, \" and \"Reproductive Medical History\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. MHGRPID may be used to link (or associate) different records together to form a block of related records at the subject level within the MH domain. It should not be used in place of MHCAT or MHSCAT, which are used to group data across subjects. For example, if a group of syndromes reported for a subject were related to a particular disease, then the MHGRPID variable could be populated with the appropriate text.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. Prespecified terms; presence or absence of events", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Information on medical history is generally collected in 2 different ways, either by recording free text or using a prespecified list of terms. The solicitation of information on specific medical history events may affect the frequency at which they are reported; therefore, the fact that a specific medical history event was solicited may be of interest to reviewers. MHPRESP and MHOCCUR are used together to indicate whether the condition in MHTERM was prespecified and whether it occurred, respectively. A value of \"Y\" in MHPRESP indicates that the term was prespecified.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. MHOCCUR is used to indicate whether a prespecified medical condition occurred; a value of \"Y\" indicates that the event occurred and \"N\" indicates that it did not.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. If a medical history event was reported using free text, the values of MHPRESP and MHOCCUR should be null. MHPRESP and MHOCCUR are permissible fields and may be omitted from the dataset if all medical history events were collected as free text.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0173_a0013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 173, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. MHSTAT and MHREASND provide information about prespecified medical history questions for which no response was collected. MHSTAT and MHREASND are permissible fields and may be omitted from the dataset if all medications were collected as free text or if all prespecified conditions had responses in MHOCCUR.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "| Situation | Value of MHPRESP | Value of MHOCCUR | Value of MHSTAT |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| Spontaneously reported event occurred | | | |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| Pre-specified event occurred | Y | Y | |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| Pre-specified event did not occur | Y | N | |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| Pre-specified event has no response | Y | | NOT DONE |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "e. When medical history events are collected with the recording of free text, a record may be entered into the data management system to indicate \"no medical history\" for a specific subject or prespecified body system category (e.g., gastrointestinal). For these subjects or categories within subject, do not include a record in the MH dataset to indicate that there were no events.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. Timing variables", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Relative timing assessments such as \"Ongoing\" or \"Active\" are common in the collection of MH information. MHENRF may be used when this relative timing assessment is coincident with the start of the study reference period for the subject represented in the Demographics (DM) dataset (RFSTDTC). MHENRTPT and MHENTPT may be used when \"Ongoing\" is relative to another date such as the screening visit date. See the examples in this section and in Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. Additional timing variables (e.g., MHSTRF) may be used when appropriate.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "6. MH event date type", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. MHEVDTYP is a domain-specific variable that can be used to indicate the aspect of the event that is represented in the event start and/or end date/times (MHSTDTC and/or MHENDTC). If a start date and/or end date is collected without further specification of what constitutes the start or end of the event, then MHEVDTYP is not needed. However, when data collection specifies how the start or end date is to be reported, MHEVDTYP can be used to provide this information. For example, when collecting the date of diagnosis, it would be used to populate MHSTDTC; MHEVDTYP would be populated with \"DIAGNOSIS\". If MHEVDTYP is not needed for any collected data, it need not be included in the dataset. If MHEVDTYP is included in the dataset, it should be populated only when the data collection specifies the aspect of the event that is to be used to populate the start and/or end date; otherwise, it should be null.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. When data collected about an event includes 2 different dates that could be considered the start or end of an event, then an MH record will be created for each. For example, if data collection included both a date of onset of symptoms and a date of diagnosis, there would be 2 records for the event, one with MHSTDTC the date of onset of symptoms and MHEVDTYP = \"SYMPTOMS\" and a second with MHSTDTC the date of diagnosis and MHENDTYP = \"DIAGNOSIS\". In such a case, it is recommended that the 2 records be linked by means such as a common value of MHSPID or MHGRPID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0174_a0013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 174, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "7. Any identifiers, timing variables, or Events general observation-class qualifiers may be added to the MH domain, but the following Qualifiers would generally not be used: --SER, --ACN, --ACNOTH, --REL, --RELNST, --OUT, --SCAN, --SCONG, --SDISAB, --SDTH, --SHOSP, --SLIFE, --SOD, --SMIE.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "MH – Examples", "heading_level": 4, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, a General Medical History CRF collected verbatim descriptions of conditions and events by body system (e.g., endocrine, metabolic), did not collect start date, but asked whether or not the condition was ongoing at the time of the visit. Another CRF page was used for cardiac history events. This page asked for date of onset of symptoms and date of diagnosis, but did not include the ongoing question.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-3: MHCAT indicates that these data were collected on the General Medical History CRF, and MHSCAT indicates the body system for which the event was collected. The reported events were coded using a standard dictionary. MHDECOD and MHBODSYS display the preferred term and body system assigned through the coding process. MHENRTPT was populated based on the response to the \"Ongoing\" question on the General Medical History CRF. MHENTPT displays the reference date for MHENRTPT, that is, the date the information was collected. If \"Yes\" was specified for Ongoing, MHENRTPT = \"ONGOING\"; if \"No\" was checked, MHENRTPT = \"BEFORE\". See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables, for further guidance.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 4-5: MHCAT indicates that these data were collected on the Cardiac Medical History CRF. Because 2 kinds of start date were collected for congestive heart failure, there are 2 records for this event, with start dates of MHEVDTYP = \"SYMPTOM ONSET\" and MHEVDTYP = \"DIAGNOSIS\". The sponsor grouped these 2 records using the MHGRPID value \"CHF\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "mh.xpt", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "| Row | STUDYID | DOMAIN | USUBJID | MHSEQ | MHGRPID | MHTERM | MHDECOD | MHEVDTYP | MHCAT | MHSCAT | MHBODSYS | MHSTDTC | MHENRTPT | MHENTPT |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 1 | ABC123 | MH | 123101 | 1 | | ASTHMA | Asthma | | GENERAL MEDICAL HISTORY | RESPIRATORY | Respiratory system disorders | | ONGOING | 2004-09-18 |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 2 | ABC123 | MH | 123101 | 2 | | FREQUENT HEADACHES | Headache | | GENERAL MEDICAL HISTORY | CNS | Central and peripheral nervous system disorders | | ONGOING | 2004-09-18 |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 3 | ABC123 | MH | 123101 | 3 | | BROKEN LEG | Bone fracture | | GENERAL MEDICAL HISTORY | OTHER | Musculoskeletal system disorders | | BEFORE | 2004-09-18 |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 4 | ABC123 | MH | 123101 | 4 | CHF | CONGESTIVE HEART FAILURE | Cardiac failure congestive | SYMPTOM ONSET | CARDIAC MEDICAL HISTORY | | Cardiac disorders | 2004-09-17 | | |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 5 | ABC123 | MH | 123101 | 5 | CHF | CONGESTIVE HEART FAILURE | Cardiac failure congestive | DIAGNOSIS | CARDIAC MEDICAL HISTORY | | Cardiac disorders | 2004-09-19 | | |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Example 2", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In this example, data from 3 CRF modules related to medical history were collected:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A General Medical History CRF collected descriptions of conditions and events by body system (e.g., endocrine, metabolic) and asked whether the conditions were ongoing at study start. The reported events were coded using a standard dictionary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A second CRF collected stroke history. Terms were selected from a list of terms taken from the standard dictionary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "A third CRF asked whether the subject had any of a list of 4 specific risk factors.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0175_a0018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 175, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In all of the records shown below, MHCAT is populated with the CRF module (general medical history, stroke history, or risk factors) through which the data were collected. MHPRESP and MHOCCUR were populated only when the term was prespecified, in keeping with MH assumption 4.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0176_a0001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 176, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-3:\tShow records from the General Medical History CRF. MHSCAT displays the body systems specified on the CRF. The coded terms are represented in MHDECOD. MHENRF has been populated based on the response to the \"Ongoing at Study Start\" question on the CRF. If \"Yes\" was specified, MHENRF = \"DURING/AFTER\"; if \"No\" was checked, MHENRF = \"BEFORE\". See Section 4.4.7, Use of Relative Timing Variables, for further guidance on using --STRF and --ENRF.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§4.4.7"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0176_a0002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 176, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 4:\tShows the record from the Stroke History CRF. MHSTDTC was populated with the date and time at which the event occurred.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0176_a0003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 176, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.2.6 Medical History (MH)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 5-8:\tShow records from the Risk Factors CRF. MHPRESP values of \"Y\" indicate that each risk factor was prespecified on the CRF. MHOCCUR is populated with \"Y\" or \"N\", corresponding to the CRF response to the questions for the 4 prespecified risk factors. The terms used to describe these risk factors were chosen to have associated codes in the standard dictionary.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
