{"atom_id": "ig34_p0178_a0017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 178, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.7 Protocol Deviations (DV)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0178_a0018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 178, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.2.7 Protocol Deviations (DV)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| DVSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7_batch18", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
