{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| DADTC | Date/Time of Collection | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date and time of the product accountability assessment represented in ISO 8601 character format. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| DADY | Study Day of Visit/Collection/Exam | Num | | Timing | Study day of product accountability assessment, measured in integer days. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"NOTE","verbatim":"1In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"DA – Assumptions","heading_level":4,"sibling_index":3,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a015","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"1. This domain records the amount of study product transferred to or from the study subject.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"a. Transfers of devices are not represented in this domain, but in the Device Tracking and Disposition (DT) domain. See the SDTMIG for Medical Devices (available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/foundational/medical-devices-sdtmig/).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a017","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"b. For drugs, transfers are usually recorded using the tests \"Dispensed Amount\" and \"Returned Amount\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"c. Test terminology for other products may be different; for example, for nutrition, the tests might be \"Prepared Amount\" and \"Unused Amount\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"2. DACAT may be used to differentiate transfers of different groups of products (e.g., rescue medications vs. investigational medications).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"3. DAREFID and DASPID are both available for capturing label information.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0181_a021","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":181,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.1 Product Accountability (DA)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"4. The following qualifiers would not generally be used in DA: --MODIFY, --POS, --BODSYS, --ORNRLO, --ORNRHI, --STNRLO, --STNRHI, --STNRC, --NRIND, --RESCAT, --XFN, --NAM, --LOINC, --SPEC, --SPCCND, --METHOD, --BLFL, --FAST, --DRVRL, --TOX, --TOXGR, --SEV.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
