{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGLOBXFL | Last Observation Before Exposure Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Operationally derived indicator used to identify the last non-missing value prior to RFXSTDTC. The value should be \"Y\" or null. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OptionE_executor_rerun_NEW3_outer_pipe_explicit_null_key", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGBLFL | Baseline Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be \"Y\" or null. Note that EGBLFL is retained for backward compatibility. The authoritative baseline for statistical analysis is in an ADaM dataset. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OptionE_executor_rerun_NEW3_outer_pipe_explicit_null_key", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGDRVFL | Derived Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be \"Y\" or null. Records that represent the average of other records, or that do not come from the CRF, or are not as originally collected or received are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If EGDRVFL=\"Y\", then EGORRES could be null, with EGSTRESC and EGSTRESN (if the result is numeric) having the derived value. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OptionE_executor_rerun_NEW3_outer_pipe_explicit_null_key", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGEVAL | Evaluator | Char | (EVAL) | Record Qualifier | Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Used only for results that are subjective (e.g., assigned by a person or a group). Should be null for records that contain collected or derived data. Examples: \"INVESTIGATOR\", \"ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE\", \"VENDOR\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OptionE_executor_rerun_NEW3_outer_pipe_explicit_null_key", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGEVALID | Evaluator Identifier | Char | (MEDEVAL) | Variable Qualifier | Used to distinguish multiple evaluators with the same role recorded in EGEVAL. Examples: \"RADIOLOGIST 1\" or \"RADIOLOGIST 2\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OptionE_executor_rerun_NEW3_outer_pipe_explicit_null_key", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGCLSIG | Clinically Significant, Collected | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate whether a collected observation is clinically significant based on judgment. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OptionE_executor_rerun_NEW3_outer_pipe_explicit_null_key", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0187_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 187, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.3 ECG Test Results (EG)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EGREPNUM | Repetition Number | Num | | Record Qualifier | The incidence number of a test that is repeated within a given timeframe for the same test. The level of granularity can vary (e.g., within a time point, within a visit). Examples: multiple measurements of blood pressure, multiple analyses of a sample. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OptionE_executor_rerun_NEW3_outer_pipe_explicit_null_key", "ts": "2026-04-25T00:00:00Z"}}
