{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| BSTPT | Planned Time Point Name | Char |  | Timing | Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See BSTPTNUM and BSTPTREF. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| BSTPTNUM | Planned Time Point Number | Num |  | Timing | Numerical version of BSTPT used in sorting. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| BSELTM | Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Elapsed time relative to a planned fixed reference (BSTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| BSTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char |  | Timing | Name of the fixed reference point referred to by BSELTM, BSTPTNUM, and BSTPT. Examples: PREVIOUS DOSE, PREVIOUS MEAL. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| BSRFTDTC | Date/Time of Reference Time Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by BSTPTREF. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"NOTE","verbatim":"1In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"BS – Assumptions","heading_level":5,"sibling_index":3,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"1. The BS domain is used to store findings related to specimen handling and specimen characteristics such as type, amount, or size. BS is not restricted to PGx-related specimens.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"2. For biospecimens of genetic material, BSSPEC values are drawn from the GENSMP (C111114) codelist.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"3. Non-genetic BSSPEC values are drawn from the SPEC (C77529) codelist, which is part of the SEND terminology listing. BSANTREG is used to further define BSSPEC when it is desirable to identify a specific region within an organ.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"4. To adapt BS for use with the SDTMIG, use the SPECTYPE (C78734) codelist in BSSPEC, add --LOC, --LAT, --DIR, and --PORTOT as applicable, and remove BSANTREG. Values that would otherwise have gone in BSANTREG may be placed in a supplemental qualifier that is almost identical to that variable, but which further qualifies BSLOC instead of BSSPEC.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"5. The following variables generally would not be used in BS: --POS, --ORNLO, --ORNHI, --STRNLO, --STNRHI, --STNRC, --NRIND, --LEAD, --CSTATE, --ACPTFL, --FAST, --TOX, --TOXGR, --SEV, --DTHREL.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
