{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"It has been shown that improper storage or isolation methods might compromise the usability of a sample.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Rows 1-2: The A260/A280 and A260/A230 rations are used to determine the purity of the RNA sample. Any ratios outside of the accepted values may indicated contamination with protein or reagents used during the extraction process.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a021","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Row 3: The amounts of both 28S and 18S ribosomal RNA are measured and then a ratio is calculated. Because values in --TESTCD cannot begin with a number, the test code has been prefixed with an \"I\" for integrity.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0198_a022","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":198,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.2 Biospecimen Findings (BS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Row 4: The RNA integrity number is a quality measurement calculated using a special algorithm and used to determine the usability of the RNA sample.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10-15_O26_NEW1-7","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
