{"atom_id": "ig34_p0213_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 213, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 4", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22a", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0213_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 213, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows data from a CCR5 cytotoxic T helper assay where test condition, stimulating agent, and replicate information is included to illustrate use of CPTSTCND, CPCNDAGT, CPREPNUM, and CPCOLSRT.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_inline_R10_R15_NEW1_NEW7_round3_batch22a", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0214_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 214, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Because not all cellular markers are expressed constitutively at detectable levels, an externally applied condition may need to be added to the test system to enable measurement or to test the functionality of the cell population being investigated. CPTSTCND was developed to capture any variable condition (i.e., a condition which can vary as opposed to is fixed) imposed on the assay system at the time the assay is conducted. Its primary use is when it is needed to differentiate results for the same test and specimen run under different assay conditions (e.g., stimulated vs unstimulated).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OPTION_E_RERUN_p214_216_219_strict_NEW3_outer_pipe_R10_verbatim", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0214_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 214, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Repeated measures (replicates) are typically incorporated into an assay to monitor reproducibility and may be reported in addition to a summarized result value. CPREPNUM and CPCOLSRT have been developed to distinguish replicate results from calculated summary results (e.g., the mean of replicates).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OPTION_E_RERUN_p214_216_219_strict_NEW3_outer_pipe_R10_verbatim", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0214_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 214, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-3: Illustrate how the test condition (CPTSTCND), replicates (REPNUM) and collected summary result type (CPCOLSRT) are used for a test system involving unstimulated CCR5+ cytotoxic T-lymphocytes. The two replicates and mean of the unstimulated condition are reported.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OPTION_E_RERUN_p214_216_219_strict_NEW3_outer_pipe_R10_verbatim", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0214_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 214, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 4-6: Illustrate the association between CPTSTCND, which identifies the condition applied to the assay system at runtime, and CPCNDAGT, which identifies the agent (if appropriate) used to impose the condition. CPREPNUM and CPCOLSRT are used as described for rows 1-3.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OPTION_E_RERUN_p214_216_219_strict_NEW3_outer_pipe_R10_verbatim", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0214_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 214, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.3 Cell Phenotype Findings (CP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 7: Shows the record for the ratio of the stimulated to unstimulated populations based on mean results (i.e., records with CPCOLSRT = \"MEAN\"). The CPANMETH variable is populated with the formula used to calculate the result. Note that calculated values provided in a lab report are considered collected rather than derived.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_OPTION_E_RERUN_p214_216_219_strict_NEW3_outer_pipe_R10_verbatim", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
