{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| NHOID | Non-Host Organism Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined identifier for a non-host organism which should only be used when the organism is the subject of the TEST. This variable should be populated with an intuitive name based on the identity of the non-host organism as reported by a lab (e.g., \"A/California/7/2009 (H1N1)\"). It is not to be used as a qualifier of the result in the record on which it appears. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of records within a dataset for a subject. May be any valid number (including decimals) and does not have to start at 1. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFREFID | Reference ID | Char | | Identifier | A unique identifier for the assayed genetic specimen. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined identifier. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFLNKID | Link ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to link related records across domains. This may be a one-to-one or a one-to-many relationship. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFLNKGRP | Link Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to link related records across domains. This will usually be a many-to-one relationship. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFTESTCD | Short Name of Genomic Measurement | Char | (GFTESTCD) | Topic | Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in GFTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in GFTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). GFTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFTEST | Name of Genomic Measurement | Char | (GFTEST) | Synonym Qualifier | Long name for GFTESTCD. The value in GFTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFTSDTL | Measurement, Test, or Examination Detail | Char | (GFTSDTL) | Variable Qualifier | Description of a reportable qualifying the assessment in GFTESTCD and GFTEST. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFCAT | Category for Genomic Finding | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of topic-variable values. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSCAT | Subcategory for Genomic Finding | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a further categorization of GFCAT values. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFORRES | Result or Finding in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFORRESU | Original Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Unit for GFORRES. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFORREF | Reference Result in Original Units | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Reference value for the result or finding as originally received or collected. GFORREF uses the same units as GFORRES, if applicable. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSTRESC | Result or Finding in Standard Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from GFORRES, in a standard format or in standard units. GFSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in GFSTRESN. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSTRESN | Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from GFSTRESC. GFSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0221_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 221, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized units used for GFSTRESC, GFSTRESN, GFSTREFC, and GFSTREFN. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSTREFC | Reference Result in Standard Format | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Reference value for the result or finding copied or derived from GFORREF in a standard format. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSTREFN | Numeric Reference Result in Std Units | Num | | Variable Qualifier | Reference value for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format or in standard units. GFSTREFN uses the same units as GFSTRESN, if applicable. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFRESCAT | Result Category | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Used to categorize the result of a finding. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFINHERT | Inheritability | Char | (INHERTGF) | Variable Qualifier | Identifies whether the variation can be passed to the next generation. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFGENREF | Genome Reference | Char | | Variable Qualifier | An identifier for the genome reference used to generate the reported result. For example, Genome Reference Consortium Human Build 38 patch release 13 may be represented as \"GRCh38.p13\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFCHROM | Chromosome Identifier | Char | | Variable Qualifier | The designation (name or number) of the chromosome or contig on which the variant or other feature appears. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSYM | Genomic Symbol | Char | * | Variable Qualifier | A published symbol for the portion of the genome serving as a locus for the experiment/test. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSYMTYP | Genomic Symbol Type | Char | (SYMTYPGF) | Variable Qualifier | A description of the type of genomic entity that is represented by the published symbol in GFSYM. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFGENLOC | Genetic Location | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Specifies the location within a sequence for the observed value in GFORRES. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFGENSR | Genetic Sub-Region | Char | | Variable Qualifier | The portion of the locus in which the variation was found. Examples: \"Exon 15\", \"Kinase domain\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSEQID | Sequence Identifier | Char | | Variable Qualifier | A unique identifier for the sequence used as the reference to identify the genetic variation in the result. Examples: \"NM_001234\", \"ENSG00000182533\", \"ENST00000343849.2\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFPVRID | Published Variant Identifier | Char | | Variable Qualifier | A unique identifier for the variation that has been publicly characterized in an external database. Examples: \"rs2231142\", \"COSM41596\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFCOPYID | Copy Identifier | Char | | Variable Qualifier | An arbitrary identifier used to differentiate between copies of a genetic target of interest present on homologous chromosomes. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate that a question was not asked or a test was not done, or a test was attempted but did not generate a result. Should be null or have a value of \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFREASND | Reason Test Not Done | Char | | Record Qualifier | Reason not done. Used in conjunction with GFSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFXFN | External File Path | Char | | Record Qualifier | The filename and/or path to external data not stored in the same format and possibly not the same location as the other data for a study. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFNAM | Laboratory/Vendor Name | Char | | Record Qualifier | Name or identifier of the vendor that provided the test result. When more than 1 vendor is involved in the generation of the result, additional vendors should be represented as supplemental qualifiers. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFSPEC | Specimen Material Type | Char | (GENSMP) | Record Qualifier | Identifies the type of genetic material used for the measurement. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFMETHOD | Method of Test or Examination | Char | (METHOD) | Record Qualifier | The test method by which the examination is performed by the wet lab in order to yield the result reported in the dataset. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFRUNID | Run ID | Char | | Record Qualifier | A unique identifier for a particular run of a test performed by the wet lab on a particular batch of samples. This identifier can be used to distinguish between records for the same test performed at different times. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFANMETH | Analysis Method | Char | (GFANMET) | Record Qualifier | The method of secondary processing performed by the dry lab to yield the result reported in the dataset. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFBLFL | Baseline Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be \"Y\" or null. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFDRVFL | Derived Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate a derived record (e.g., a record that represents the average of other records such as a computed baseline). Should be \"Y\" or null. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0222_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 222, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFLLOQ | Lower Limit of Quantitation | Num | | Variable Qualifier | Indicates the lower limit of quantitation for an assay. Units will be those used for GFSTRESU. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFREPNUM | Repetition Number | Num | | Record Qualifier | The instance number of a test that is repeated within a given timeframe for the same test performed by the wet lab. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITNUM | Visit Number | Num | | Timing | Clinical encounter number. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISIT | Visit Name | Char | | Timing | Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITDY | Planned Study Day of Visit | Num | | Timing | Planned study day of VISIT. Should be an integer. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFDTC | Date/Time of Specimen Collection | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date and time of specimen collection. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFDY | Study Day of Specimen Collection | Num | | Timing | Actual study day of visit/collection/exam expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFTPT | Planned Time Point Name | Char | | Timing | Text description of time when a measurement or observation should be taken as defined in the protocol. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See GFTPTNUM and GFTPTREF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFTPTNUM | Planned Time Point Number | Num | | Timing | Numerical version of GFTPT used in sorting. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFELTM | Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Elapsed time relative to a planned fixed reference (GFTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date time variable, but an interval, represented as ISO duration. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char | | Timing | Name of the fixed reference point referred to by GFELTM, GFTPTNUM, and GFTPT. Examples: \"PREVIOUS DOSE\", \"PREVIOUS MEAL\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| GFRFTDTC | Date/Time of Reference Time Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by GFTPTREF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "¹In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "GF – Assumptions", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. The Genomics Findings domain is used to represent findings related to the structure, function, evolution, mapping, and editing of subject and non-host organism genomic material of interest. This domain includes but is not limited to assessments and results for genetic variation and transcription, and summary measures derived from these assessments. The GF domain is used for findings from characteristics assessed from nucleic acids and may include subsequent inferences and/or predictions about related proteins/amino acids. However, direct assessments of proteins (e.g., assessments of amino acids) are out of scope for this domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. Regarding genetic testing on non-host organisms (including but not limited to bacteria, viruses, and parasites), the following additional assumptions apply:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Tests that give genetic results (e.g., expressed in terms of genetic variation, specific sequence information) on non-host organisms that have been identified in subject samples should be represented in GF. To distinguish these findings from subject genetic data, the variable NHOID must be populated to identify the non-host organism as the focus of the record (see Section 9.2, Non-host Organism Identifiers, assumption 2 for more information).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§9.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. If the purpose of the test is to detect or determine the identity of a viable, non-host organism or infectious agent in a subject sample, data should be represented in the Microbiology Specimen (MB) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0223_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 223, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. Tests that are used to determine the resistance/susceptibility of a non-host organism to a drug on a genetic basis should be represented in the Microbiology Susceptibility (MS) domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "d. If the test provides both genetic data and susceptibility/resistance data, genetic data should be represented in GF and the susceptibility/resistance data should be represented in the MS domain (See Section 6.3.5.7.2, Microbiology Susceptibility, assumption 1b for more information).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.5.7.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. The platform used to detect the finding may be represented in SPDEVID. Attributes used in conjunction with a platform (e.g., assay panel, reagents) may be represented in the Device Identifiers (DI) domain and other associated device domains. See the SDTM Implementation Guide for Medical Devices (SDTMIG-MD) for further information about SPDEVID and the device domains.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. Values populated in GFCAT and GFSCAT are sponsor-defined and there is no CDISC Controlled Terminology for these variables.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. Genomic symbols are represented in GFSYM.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. GFTESTCD and GFTEST should not include genomic names or symbols, including but not limited to official gene symbols.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. For human genetic data, standard nomenclature populated in variable GFSYM must be obtained from the genomic symbol list maintained in the HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee (HGNC) database (www.genenames.org).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "6. When populating GFGENSR, caution should be exercised for annotations of loci where more than 1 annotation applies. In such cases, the source of the annotation should be captured and documented in Define-XML. In addition, the value populated in GFGENSR may be dependent on the precision of the value populated in GFSEQID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "7. Values populated in GFGENREF, GFSEQID, and GFPVRID should reflect the level of granularity collected (e.g., version, build, patch, release) to support interpretation of the reported result.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "8. GFMETHOD lists wet lab techniques for the execution of genomics or genetic testing. Methods related to specimen processing or reagents are not represented in GFMETHOD.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "9. The following variables generally would not be used in GF: --POS, --BODSYS, --ORNRLO, ORNRHI,--STNRLO, --STNRHI, --STNRC, --NRIND, --CHRON, --DISTR, --ANTREG, --LOC, --LAT, --DIR, --PORTOT, --LEAD, --CSTATE, --SPCCND, --FAST, --TOX, --TOXGR, --SEV.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "GF – Examples", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows findings from an assessment of single nucleotide and copy number variation generated from biocomputational analysis with wet laboratory methodology targeted genome sequencing. Findings from this assessment show variation from DNA extracted from an individual's tumor tissue. As the DNA specimen was extracted from tumor tissue, the inheritabilty of the variation is considered to be somatic.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 1: Shows the predicted amino acid change due to the single nucleotide variant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 2: Shows the predicted coding sequence change due to the single nucleotide variant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 3: Shows the classification of the variant impact given the predicted amino acid change.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 4: Shows the number of times the locus specified in variables GFCHROM and GFGENLOC was observed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 5: Shows the percent variant read depth to total read depth.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 6: Shows the number of copies of the gene of interest within the genome of the tumor cell.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0224_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 224, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 7: Shows the number of altered exons within the gene of interest in the genome of the tumor cell.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0225_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 225, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 8: Shows the ratio of the copy number of the gene of interest in the tumor cell to the reference number of copies.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
