{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 6 | ABC123 | GF | 123101 | 6 | 4401470-2-6 | MICRISTB | Microsatellite Instability | DETECTION | Not Detected | Not Detected | NR-24 | msi_abc_gf.csv | ACME Laboratories | DNA | CAPILLARY ELECTROPHORESIS | MSI-010418 | 1 | VISIT | 1 | 2020-02-04 | -2 |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": "pdf_p227+top", "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 5", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example includes 3 datasets (i.e., MB and MS in addition to GF). The purpose of this 3-part example is to illustrate how these domains are appropriately used in cases where the concepts in each domain are very closely related. Specifically, the example demonstrates the use of these domains by following a subject through a hypothetical scenario of influenza diagnosis, genetic evaluation of the virus, and interpretation of drug susceptibility resulting from genetic testing.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Tests that diagnose or identify the presence of an infectious agent in a subject sample are represented in the MB domain, regardless of the methodology used. In this example, the subject was diagnosed with influenza A H3N2 via a nucleic acid amplification test (NAAT) at the baseline visit. MBTEST = \"Microbial Organism Identification\" because the assay does not specifically test for the presence of 1 organism or subtype to the exclusion of all others.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.5.7.2"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "CODE_LITERAL", "verbatim": "mb.xpt", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "| Row | STUDYID | DOMAIN | USUBJID | MBSEQ | MBREFID | MBTESTCD | MBTEST | MBORRES | MBSTRESC | MBSPEC | MBLOC | MBMETHOD | VISITNUM | VISIT | MBDTC |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": "pdf_p227+middle", "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| 1 | INFLU122 | MB | INF01-01 | 1 | INFLU0101 | MCORGIDN | Microbial Organism Identification | INFLUENZA A VIRUS SUBTYPE H3N2 | INFLUENZA A VIRUS SUBTYPE H3N2 | MUCUS | NOSTRIL | NUCLEIC ACID AMPLIFICATION TEST | 1 | BASELINE | 2020-06-11 |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": "pdf_p227+middle", "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Next, a series of virus samples extracted from the subject underwent targeted single nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) testing to determine the feasibility of using the neuraminidase inhibitor oseltamivir to treat the infection (i.e., drug susceptibility testing).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Findings from this testing provide both genetic data in the form of the genotype identified and the susceptibility/resistance data as inferred phenotype. Genotypic findings are represented in the GF domain, and inferred susceptibility/resistance in MS.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The GFTEST \"Single Nucleotide Variation\" is used for SNP tests. GFTSTDTL indicates that the results are expressed as predicted amino acid change instead of nucleotide change. GFSYM = \"NA\", the published gene symbol for the influenza neuraminidase gene. GFGENLOC represents the position in the protein sequence where the targeted variation which confers resistance to oseltamivir occurs. GFSEQID is the reference sequence/segment to which the results are compared.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0227_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 227, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "Note the use of NHOID, which is populated with the name of the organism to which the testing applies. Note: It is important to use this identifier to distinguish between tests that apply to a non-host organism and tests that apply to the study subject/host.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0228_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 228, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "GFLNKID serves as the link between this dataset and the MS dataset which follows.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0228_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 228, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 1:\tShows the result of a targeted test to detect a single nucleotide polymorphism in the influenza neuraminidase gene known to confer resistance to the drug oseltamivir. The result (R292R) indicates that the amino acid residue R (arginine) at position 292 remains unchanged at the baseline visit", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0228_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 228, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.4 Genomics Findings (GF)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 2-3:\tShow the results of the same targeted test at the day 2 and day 5 visits. The results (R292K) show that a mutation has occurred at position 292 from the amino acid R (arginine) to the amino acid K (lysine).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
