{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISREFID | Reference ID | Char | | Identifier | Internal or external specimen identifier. Example: \"458975-01\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined identifier. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISTESTCD | Immunogenicity Test/Exam Short Name | Char | (ISTESTCD) | Topic | Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in ISTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in ISTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). ISTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISTEST | Immunogenicity Test or Examination Name | Char | (ISTEST) | Synonym Qualifier | Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in ISTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Example: \"Immunoglobulin E\". | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISTSTCND | Test Condition | Char | (TESTCOND) | Variable Qualifier | Identifies any planned condition imposed by the assay system on the specimen at the time the test is performed. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISCNDAGT | Test Condition Agent | Char | | Record Qualifier | The textual description of the agent used to impose a test condition. Examples are different stimulating agents used in immunoassays such as those in the Interferon Gamma Response assay (e.g., Mycobacterium tuberculosis ESAT-6, CFP-10, TB 7.7, Mitogen). | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISBDAGNT | Binding Agent | Char | (MICROORG)(ISBDAGT) | Variable Qualifier | Text description of the agent that is binding to the entity in the ISTEST variable. ISBDAGNT is used to indicate that there is a binding relationship between the entities in the ISTEST and ISBDAGNT variables, regardless of direction. ISBDAGNT is not a method qualifier. It should only be used when the actual interest of the measurement is the binding interaction between the 2 entities in ISTEST and ISBDAGNT. In other words, the combination of ISTEST and ISBDAGNT should describe the entity or the analyte being measured, without the need for additional variables. The binding agent may be (but is not limited to) a test article, a portion of the test article, a related compound, an endogenous molecule, an allergen, or an infectious agent. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISTSTOPO | Test Operational Objective | Char | (TSTOPOBJ) | Variable Qualifier | Text description of the high-level purpose of the test at the operational level. If populated, valid values are \"SCREEN\", \"CONFIRM\", and \"QUANTIFY\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISMSMCBE | Molecule Secreted by Cells | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Text description of the entity secreted by the cells represented in ISTEST. The combination of ISTEST and ISMSCBCE should describe the entity or the analyte being measured, without the need for additional variables. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISTSTDTL | Test Detail | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Further description of ISTESTCD and ISTEST. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISCAT | Category for Immunogenicity Test | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of topic-variable values across subjects. Example: \"SEROLOGY\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0229_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 229, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSCAT | Subcategory for Immunogenicity Test | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of ISCAT. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_HEADER", "verbatim": "| Variable Name | Variable Label | Type | Controlled Terms, Codelist or Format¹ | Role | CDISC Notes | Core |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISORRES | Results or Findings in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISORRESU | Original Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for ISORRES. Examples: \"Index Value\", \"gpELISA\", \"unit/mL\". | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISORNRLO | Reference Range Lower Limit in Orig Unit | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Lower end of reference range for continuous measurement in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISORNRHI | Reference Range Upper Limit in Orig Unit | Char | | Variable Qualifier | Upper end of reference range for continuous measurement in original units. Should be populated only for continuous results. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings copied or derived from ISORRES, in a standard format or in standard units. ISSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in ISSTRESN. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSTRESN | Numeric Results/Findings in Std. Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from ISSTRESC. ISSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized units used for ISSTRESC and ISSTRESN. Examples: \"Index Value\", \"gpELISA\", \"unit/mL\". | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSTNRLO | Reference Range Lower Limit-Std Units | Num | | Variable Qualifier | Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements for ISSTRESC/ISSTRESN in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous measurements. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSTNRHI | Reference Range Upper Limit-Std Units | Num | | Variable Qualifier | Upper end of reference range for continuous measurements in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSTNRC | Reference Range for Char Rslt-Std Units | Char | | Variable Qualifier | For normal range values that are character in ordinal scale or if categorical ranges were supplied. Examples: \"-1 to +1\", \"NEGATIVE TO TRACE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISNRIND | Reference Range Indicator | Char | (NRIND) | Variable Qualifier | Indicates where the value falls with respect to a reference range defined by ISORNRLO and ISORNRHI, ISSTNRLO and ISSTNRHI, or by ISSTNRC. Examples: \"NORMAL\", \"ABNORMAL\", \"HIGH\", \"LOW\". Sponsors should specify in the study metadata (Comments column in the Define-XML document) whether ISNRIND refers to the original or standard reference ranges and results. Should not be used to indicate clinical significance. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate a test was not done. Should be null if a result exists in ISORRES. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISREASND | Reason Not Done | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes why a measurement or test was not performed. Used in conjunction with ISSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISNAM | Vendor Name | Char | | Record Qualifier | Name or identifier of the laboratory or vendor who provided the test results. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSPEC | Specimen Type | Char | (SPECTYPE) | Record Qualifier | Defines the types of specimen used for a measurement. Example: \"SERUM\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSPCCND | Specimen Condition | Char | (SPECCOND) | Record Qualifier | Free or standardized text describing the condition of the specimen. Examples: \"HEMOLYZED\", \"ICTERIC\", \"LIPEMIC\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISSPCUFL | Specimen Usability for the Test | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Describes the usability of the specimen for the test. The value will be \"N\" if the specimen is not usable, and null if the specimen is usable. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISMETHOD | Method of Test or Examination | Char | (METHOD) | Record Qualifier | Method of the test or examination. Examples: \"ELISA\", \"ELISPOT\". | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISLOBXFL | Last Observation Before Exposure Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Operationally derived indicator used to identify the last non-missing value prior to RFXSTDTC. The value should be \"Y\" or null. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISBLFL | Baseline Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Indicator used to identify a baseline value. Should be \"Y\" or null. Note that ISBLFL is retained for backward compatibility. The authoritative baseline for statistical analysis is in an ADaM dataset. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0230_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 230, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| ISDRVFL | Derived Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be \"Y\" or null. Examples of records that might be derived for the submission datasets include those that represent the average of other records, do not come from the CRF, or are not as originally received or collected. If [continues on next page] | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2+inline-R10-R15+O-P1-26+NEW1-NEW8", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
