{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a015","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| 7 | RSC1230 | IS | RSV1230-011 | 3 | 13671 | | MBIGGAB | Microbial-induced IgG Antibody | HUMAN RESPIRATORY SYNCYTIAL VIRUS-PROTEIN B | QUANTIFY | STUDY VACCINE-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY | HUMORAL IMMUNITY | 1:500 | 500 | 500 | titer | SERUM | ELISA | 4 | VISIT 3 | 2017-09-27 |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0236_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":236,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Thus far, all the IS tests illustrated are measurements of concentrations of a substance (e.g., antibody titer). However, some immunogenicity tests are actual counts of immune cells that secrete a particular substance. These tests are described by the combination of ISTEST (Immunogenicity Test or Examination Name) and ISMSCBCE (Molecule Secreted by Cells), where ISTEST identifies the type of cells that secrete a specific","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"substance (e.g., antibody-secreting cells, cytokine-secreting cells) and ISMSCBCE names the substance (e.g., IgG antibody, interferon-gamma). The following 2 examples introduce the IS domain-specific variable, ISMSCBCE, and illustrate its use with ISTEST to represent a complete immunological analyte of interest.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"Example 6","heading_level":6,"sibling_index":6,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example shows data about the assessment of antibody-secreting cells (ASCs).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Traditional methods such as enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) that monitor humoral immune responses after immunization or infection typically only quantify specific antibody titers in serum. These methods do not provide any information about the actual number and location of the immune cells that secrete antibodies or cytokines.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The enzyme-linked immunospot (ELISpot) assay is a method to detect and quantify analyte-secreting T or B cells. During ELISpot testing, a colored precipitate forms and appears as spots at the sites of analyte localization (analytes typically are cytokines or antibodies), with each individual spot representing an individual analyte-secreting cell. The spots can be counted with an automated ELISpot reader system or manually, using a stereomicroscope. This example shows how to represent the quantification of ASCs as the number of spots per million peripheral blood mononuclear cells (PBMC) as determined by B-cell ELISpot from a vaccine trial.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"The IS domain-specific variable ISMSCBCE introduced in this example allows flexibility in data representation and post-coordination of the various secreted antibody types and their respective ASCs. This approach liberates the ISTEST variable from having to house precoordinated and thus hyperspecific values crafted based on secretion and cell types.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 1:\tShows the total number of IgG ASCs from a subject's blood sample. In this case, ISTEST=\"Antibody-secreting Cells\"; the entity secreted by the cells in ISTEST is represented by the variable ISMSCBCE (i.e. IGG antibody non-specific to any antigen).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 2:\tShows the number of H1-specific IgG ASCs from the same subject's blood sample. In this case, ISTEST=\"Antibody-secreting Cells\"; the entity secreted by the cells in ISTEST is in ISMSCBCE (i.e. IgG antibody specific to H1 antigen).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0237_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":237,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 3:\tShows the number of H3-specific IgG ASCs from the same subject's blood sample. In this case, ISTEST=\"Antibody-secreting Cells\"; the entity secreted by the cells in ISTEST is in ISMSCBCE (i.e. IgG antibody specific to H3 antigen).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
