{"atom_id":"ig34_p0239_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":239,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| 3 | SAU1230 | IS | SAU1230-011 | STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS 04-02981 | 3 | 13668 | MBFAB | Functional Microbial-induced Antibody | STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS-EPITOPE X | OPSONIZATION INDEX | STUDY VACCINE-RELATED IMMUNOGENICITY | HUMORAL IMMUNITY | 5000 | 5000 | 5000 | SERUM | OPSONOPHAGOCYTIC KILLING ASSAY | 3 | VISIT 2 | 2017-09-27 |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"Example 10","heading_level":6,"sibling_index":10,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example shows how to present data from an autoimmune disease study, specifically how to represent information from disease-specific autoantibody tests.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Sjögren's syndrome (SS) is a systemic autoimmune disease characterized by dry eyes and dry mouth. Diagnosis of SS is generally based on the detection of antinuclear antibodies (ANAs), that is, anti-Ro (SS-A) and anti-La (SS-B) antibodies.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 1-5:\tShow the screening (row 1) and quantification (rows 2, 4) of ANAs. Rows 2 and 3 are grouped together using ISGRPID=\"1a\"; this means the titer result in row 2 is specifically related to the particular nuclear staining pattern (i.e., speckled) finding in row 3. The speckled pattern of ANA is typically indicative of SS, systemic lupus, and mixed connective tissue disease. Rows 4 and 5 are grouped together using ISGRPID=\"1b\"; this means the titer result in row 4 is specifically related to the nuclear staining pattern (i.e., nucleoar) finding in row 5. Rows 1 to 5 are grouped together using ISGRPID with values starting with the number \"1\", indicating that these records are related. The antinuclear antibodies test is post-coordinated and represented by both ISTEST=\"Autoantibody\" and ISBDAGNT=\"NUCLEAR AUTOANTIGENS\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0240_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":240,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 6-11:\tShow the screening and quantification of the various SS-specific autoantibodies. SS autoantigens are represented by the ISBDAGNT variable, whereas the ISTEST=\"Autoantibody\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_optionE_rerun","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
