{"atom_id":"ig34_p0243_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":243,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBLLOD | Lower Limit of Detection | Char | | Variable Qualifier | The lowest threshold (as originally received or collected) for reliably detecting the presence or absence of substance measured by a specific test. The value for the field will be as described in documentation from the instrument or lab vendor. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0243_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":243,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | (LBSTRESC) | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from LBORRES in a standard format or standard units. LBSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in LBSTRESN. For example, if a test has results \"NONE\", \"NEG\", and \"NEGATIVE\" in LBORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in LBSTRESC as \"NEGATIVE\". For other examples, see Original and Standardized Results. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0243_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":243,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBSTRESN | Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from LBSTRESC. LBSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0243_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":243,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized unit used for LBSTRESC or LBSTRESN. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0243_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":243,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBSTNRLO | Reference Range Lower Limit-Std Units | Num | | Variable Qualifier | Lower end of reference range for continuous measurements for LBSTRESC/LBSTRESN in standardized units. Should be populated only for continuous results. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
