{"atom_id":"ig34_p0243_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":243,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBSTNRC | Reference Range for Char Rslt-Std Units | Char | | Variable Qualifier | For normal range values that are character in ordinal scale or if categorical ranges were supplied. Examples: \"-1 to +1\", \"NEGATIVE TO TRACE\". | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0243_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":243,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBNRIND | Reference Range Indicator | Char | (NRIND) | Variable Qualifier | Indicates where the value falls with respect to reference range defined by LBORNRLO and LBORNRHI, LBSTNRLO and LBSTNRHI, or by LBSTNRC. Examples: \"NORMAL\", \"ABNORMAL\", \"HIGH\", \"LOW\". Sponsors should specify in the study metadata (Comments column in the Define-XML document) whether LBNRIND refers to the original or standard reference ranges and results. LBNRIND is not used to indicate clinical significance. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
