{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBDRVFL | Derived Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to identify a derived record. The value should be \"Y\" or null. Records that represent the average of other records, or do not come from the CRF, or are not as originally received or collected are examples of records that might be derived for the submission datasets. If LBDRVFL=\"Y\", then LBORRES may be null, with LBSTRESC and (if numeric) LBSTRESN having the derived value. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBTOX | Toxicity | Char | * | Variable Qualifier | Description of toxicity quantified by LBTOXGR. The sponsor is expected to provide the name of the scale and version used to map the terms, utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBTOXGR | Standard Toxicity Grade | Char | * | Record Qualifier | Records toxicity grade value using a standard toxicity scale (e.g., the NCI CTCAE). If value is from a numeric scale, represent only the number (e.g., \"2\" not \"Grade 2\"). The sponsor is expected to provide the name of the scale and version used to map the terms, utilizing the external codelist element in the Define-XML document. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBCLSIG | Clinically Significant, Collected | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate whether a collected observation is clinically significant based on judgment. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| VISITNUM | Visit Number | Num | | Timing | Clinical encounter number. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| VISIT | Visit Name | Char | | Timing | Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
