{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBDY | Study Day of Specimen Collection | Num | | Timing | Study day of specimen collection, measured as integer days. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. This formula should be consistent across the submission. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBENDY | Study Day of End of Observation | Num | | Timing | Actual study day of end of observation expressed in integer days relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC in Demographics. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0244_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":244,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBTPT | Planned Time Point Name | Char | | Timing | Text description of time when specimen should be taken. This may be represented as an elapsed time relative to a fixed reference point, such as time of last dose. See LBTPTNUM and LBTPTREF. Examples: \"Start\", \"5 min post\". | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBTPTNUM | Planned Time Point Number | Num | | Timing | Numerical version of LBTPT to aid in sorting. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBELTM | Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Planned elapsed time (in ISO 8601) relative to a planned fixed reference (LBTPTREF). This variable is useful where there are repetitive measures. Not a clock time or a date/time variable. Represented as ISO 8601 duration. Examples: \"-PT15M\" to represent the period of 15 minutes prior to the reference point indicated by LBTPTREF, \"PT8H\" to represent the period of 8 hours after the reference point indicated by LBTPTREF. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char | | Timing | Name of the fixed reference point referred to by LBELTM, LBTPTNUM, and LBTPT. Examples: \"PREVIOUS DOSE\", \"PREVIOUS MEAL\". | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBRFTDTC | Date/Time of Reference Time Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time of the reference time point, LBTPTREF. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBPTFL | Point in Time Flag | Char | (NY) | Timing | An indication that the specimen was collected at a single point in time. The value is \"Y\" or null. The intent of this variable in the LB domain is to aid mapping to LOINC codes in the dataset, when LOINC part \"Time Aspect\" = \"Pt\". | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a006","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| LBPDUR | Planned Duration | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | Planned duration of specimen collection. If LBPTFL is \"Y\" then LBPDUR is null. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a007","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"NOTE","verbatim":"¹In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"HEADING","verbatim":"LB – Assumptions","heading_level":5,"sibling_index":3,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"1. This domain captures laboratory data collected on the CRF or received from a central provider or vendor.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"2. For lab tests that do not have continuous numeric results (e.g., urine protein as measured by dipstick), descriptive tests such as urine color), LBSTNRC could be populated either with normal range values that are a range of character values for an ordinal scale (e.g., \"NEGATIVE TO TRACE\") or a delimited set of values that are considered to be normal (e.g., \"YELLOW\", \"AMBER\"). LBORNRLO, LBORNRHI, LBSTNRLO, and LBSTNRHI should be null for these types of tests.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"3. LBNRIND can be added to indicate where a result falls with respect to reference range defined by LBORNRLO and LBORNRHI. Examples: \"HIGH\", \"LOW\". If toxicity grading is available, values would be represented in the variables LBTOX and LBTOXGR. Clinical significance would be represented as described in Section 4.5.5, Clinical Significance for Findings Observation Class Data, in LBCLSIG (see also LB Example 1).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"4. For lab tests where the specimen is collected over time (e.g., 24-hour urine collection), the start date/time of the collection goes into LBDTC and the end date/time of collection goes into LBENDTC. See Section 4.4.8, Date and Time Reported in a Domain Based on Findings.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"5. Any Identifiers, Timing variables, or Findings general observation class qualifiers may be added to the LB domain, but the following qualifiers would not generally be used: --BODSYS, --SEV.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"6. A value derived by a central lab according to its procedures is considered collected rather than derived. See Section 4.1.8.1, Origin Metadata for Variables.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0245_a015","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":245,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"7. The variable LBORRESU uses the UNIT codelist. This means that sponsors should be submitting a term from the CDISC Submission Value column in the published Controlled Terminology List that is maintained for CDISC by NCI EVS. When sponsors have units that are not in this column, they should first check to see if their unit is mathematically synonymous with an existing/published unit from the UNIT codelist and submit their lab values using the published CDISC submission value. Example: \"g/L\" and \"mg/mL\" are mathematically synonymous, but only \"g/L\" is the submission value in","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "the CDISC Unit codelist. If this is not the case, the unit must be added as a codelist extensible value in the Define.xml, and a new-term request must be submitted.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a.   CDISC Controlled Terminology Rules for Lab and Unit are available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "8.   The LBLOINC variable contains a code from the Logical Observation Identifiers Names and Codes (LOINC) database that identifies a specific laboratory test. The LOINC to LB Mapping Codetable, available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology, may be used to identify appropriate CDISC CT values for a test with a particular LOINC code. In addition to LBTEST, LBSPEC, LBMETHOD, and LBORRESU, the aspects of a test that are associated with a LOINC code may be represented in the variables LBTPT, LBANMETH, LBPOS, LBLOC, LBFAST, LBTSTCND, LBBDAGNT, LBTSTOPO, LBRESSCL, LBRESTYP, LBCOLSRT, LBLLOD, LBPTFL, and LBPDUR. These additional variables are only required to be populated when necessary to provide a semantically meaningful distinction between records with different LBLOINC values.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "LB – Examples", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example illustrates the use of previously published LB domain variables and introduces several new variables that were added to SDTMv2.0, including LBTSTCND, LBRESSCL, LBRESTYP, LBCOLSRT, LBLLOD, LBTMTHSN, LBPTFL, and LBPDUR. These variables, in part, aid in harmonization to LOINC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 1:   Shows a value collected in 1 unit, but converted to selected standard unit. See Section 4.5.1, Original and Standardized Results of Findings and Tests Not Done, for additional examples for the population of result qualifiers. The result was evaluated by the investigator and determined to be not clinically significant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Section 4.5.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 2-3:   Show 2 records for alkaline phosphatase done at the same visit, a day apart. LBPTFL is set to \"Y\" for both rows because each result is based on a sample from a single point in time.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 4-5:   Show 2 derived records (mean of records 2 and 3 and maximum value of records 2 and 3) grouped by a common LBGRPID value. The derived result in row 4 is described as a mean (LBCOLSRT=\"MEAN, ARITHMETIC\"), but LBDRVFL is missing because the mean result was provided by the vendor. The derived result in row 5 was derived by the sponsor, and so is flagged as derived (LBDRVFL=\"Y\"); LBCOLSRT is not populated because the result is not a collected summary result. For both derived results, the sponsor chose to populate LBRESSCL, LBRESTYP, LBSPEC, and LBFAST consistent with the 2 individual alkaline phosphatase records but did not populate LBLOINC or LBPTFL because neither derived record represented a single point in time. The sponsor chose to populate LBDTC with the first of the 2 specimen collection dates.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 6:   Shows use of LBTMTHSN to represent \"HIGH SENSITIVITY\" for the high-sensitivity C-reactive protein (hs-CRP) test.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 7, 10:   Show use of LBTSTCND. For the cryoglobulin test, 1-day cold incubation is noted; for the platelet aggregation test, collagen induced is noted.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 8:   Shows use of LBLLOD for a prostate-specific antigen test.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 9:   Shows use of LBPDUR to represent the planned duration of \"PT24H\" for collection of urine samples for the protein test. LBPTFL is set to missing because this test was not conducted at a single point in time.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 12-13:   Show a suggested use of the LBSCAT variable. LBSCAT could be used to further classify types of tests within a laboratory panel (e.g., \"DIFFERENTIAL\"). The LYMLE result was evaluated by the investigator and determined to be not clinically significant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0246_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 246, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 15:   Shows the proper use of the LBSTAT variable to indicate \"NOT DONE\", where a reason was collected when a test was not done. LBRESSCL, LBRESTYP, LBLOINC, LBSPEC, LBMETHOD, and LBPTFL are populated to describe the properties of the test that was not done.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0247_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 247, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 16:   Shows measuring of the subject's cholesterol. The normal range for this test is <200 mg/dL. Note that although in this example the sponsor has decided to make LBSTNRHI=\"199\", other sponsors may choose a different value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0247_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 247, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.6 Laboratory Test Results (LB)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Row 17:   Shows use of LBPTFL set to \"Y\" to indicate that the test used a sample taken at a single point in time.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
