{"atom_id":"ig34_p0251_a008","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":251,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.1 Microbiology Specimen (MB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"a. In cases of tests that target an organism, group of organisms, or antigen for identification, MBTEST equals the name of the organism/antigen targeted by the identification assay, and","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0251_a009","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":251,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.1 Microbiology Specimen (MB)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"i. MBTSTDTL should be \"DETECTION\".","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
