{"atom_id":"ig34_p0252_a024","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":252,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0252_a025","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":252,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| NHOID | Non-host Organism ID | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined identifier for a non-host organism which should only be used when the organism is the subject of the TEST. This variable should be populated with an initiative-name based identifier of the non-host organism as reported by a lab (e.g., \"ACUHAIII7/2009 (H1N1)\"). It is not to be used as a qualifier of any other test. | Perm |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0252_a026","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":252,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of each record for a subject in a given domain. It is a number assigned to a subject (or a parameter, in the case of the Trial Summary domain). May be any valid number (including decimals) and does not have to start at 1. | Req |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0252_a027","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":252,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Optional group identifier, used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain. In SDTMIG v3.2 this was an Expected variable. In this version, the core designation has been changed to Permissible. | Perm |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0252_a028","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":252,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSREFID | Reference ID | Char | | Identifier | Optional internal or external identifier (e.g., an identifier for the culture/isolate being tested for susceptibility). | Perm |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0252_a029","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":252,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor reference number. May be preprinted on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. | Perm |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0252_a030","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":252,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSLNKID | Link ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to link related records across domains. This may be a one-to-one or a one-to-many relationship. For example, it may be used to link genetic findings (in the PF domain) about a microbe to the original culture of that microbe (in MB), or to susceptibility records in MS if needed. | Perm |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0253_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":253,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSTESTCD | Short Name of Assessment | Char | (MSTESTCD) | Topic | Short character value for MSTEST used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical format to a horizontal format. It can be used when converting data to a horizontal format with a column name used when converting a data set from a vertical format to a horizontal format with a number (e.g., \"TEST1\" is not valid). MSTESTCD cannot contain characters other than those outlined in the SDTM IG MIC for Microbiology Susceptibility. MSTESTCD cannot contain characters other than those outlined in the CDISC IG MIC for Microbiology. | Req |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0253_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":253,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"CODE_LITERAL","verbatim":"MSTESTCD","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0253_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":253,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSTEST | Name of Assessment | Char | (MSTEST) | Synonym Qualifier | Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in MSTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: \"Minimum Inhibitory Concentration\", \"Microbial Susceptibility\". | Req |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
