{"atom_id":"ig34_p0253_a021","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":253,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| MSSTRESC | Result or Finding in Standard Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from MSORRES in a standard format or in standard units. MSSTRESC should store all result values in character format; if results are numeric values, they should be stored in MSSTRESN. When MSORRES contains results such as \"NONE\", \"NEG\", and \"NEGATIVE\" in MSORRES and these results effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in MSSTRESC as \"NEGATIVE\". | Exp |","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
