{"atom_id":"ig34_p0255_a023","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":255,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"1. Microbiology Susceptibility testing includes testing of the following types:","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0255_a024","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":255,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"a. Phenotypic drug susceptibility testing (qualitative), which may involve determining susceptibility/resistance (qualitative) at a predefined concentration of drug, or determining a specific dose (quantitative) at which a drug inhibits organism growth or some other process associated with virulence.","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0255_a025","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":255,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"i. For studies using qualitative testing methods, MSAGENT, MSCONC, and MSCONCU are used to represent the predefined drug, concentration, and units, respectively. Results are represented with values such as \"SUSCEPTIBLE\" or \"RESISTANT\".","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0255_a026","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":255,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"CODE_LITERAL","verbatim":"MSAGENT","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
