{"atom_id":"ig34_p0255_a031","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":255,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.2 Microbiology Susceptibility (MS)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"ii. For studies using quantitative testing methods, MSAGENT is used to represent the drug being tested; MSCONC and MSCONCU are not used. The concentration at which growth is inhibited is the result in these cases (MSORRES, MSSTRESC/MSSTRESN), with units being represented in MSORRESU/MSSTRESU.","cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T08:15:00Z"}}
