{"atom_id":"ig34_p0258_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":258,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 1-2: Show that a gram stain was used on a subject sputum sample to identify the presence of gram negative cocci (row 1) and to quantify the bacteria (row 2). MBORRES in row 2 represents an ordinal result (MBRSLSCL = \"Ord\"), such as from a published quantification scale. This value decodes to \"FEW\" as shown in MBSTRESC. The quantification scale used is represented as Supplemental Qualifiers of MB.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0258_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":258,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 3-4: Show that the same gram-stained sample was used to identify and quantify the presence of gram negative rods.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0258_a014","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":258,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 5-6: Show that microbial culture of the same sample was used at the same visit to identify the presence of two organisms, \"STREPTOCOCCUS PNEUMONIAE\" and \"KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE\" (MBORRES).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0258_a015","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":258,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 7: Shows that microbial culture of a subsequent sample at a later visit indicated only the presence of \"KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE\" (MBORRES).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0258_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":258,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Row 8: Shows that microbial culture of a third subject sample at the third visit indicated \"NO GROWTH\" (MBORRES) of any organisms.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
