{"atom_id":"ig34_p0258_a029","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":258,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"1 | ABC | MB | ABC-01-101 | MBTSTDTL | CELL COUNT | MBQSCAL | Quantification Scale | CDC semi-quantitative score for gram staining | CRF","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0259_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":259,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 1-2: Show that the sponsor drug (MSAGENT) was tested against \"STREPTOCOCCUS PNEUMONIAE\" (NHOID) from subject sample SP01 and that the drug has a minimum inhibitory concentration (MSTESTCD/MSTEST) of 0.004 mg/L (row 1). This led to the conclusion that this organism is susceptible to that drug (row 2).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0259_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":259,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 3-4: Show that penicillin was tested against the same organism from the same sample and was found to have a minimum inhibitory concentration of 0.023 mg/L (row 3). This led to the conclusion that \"STREPTOCOCCUS PNEUMONIAE\" is resistant to penicillin (row 4).","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0259_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":259,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 5-8: Similar to rows 1-4, the sponsor drug (rows 5-6) and penicillin (rows 7-8) were tested against \" KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE\" from an additional sample from the same subject at a later time point. Results from these tests indicated that the organism was susceptible to sponsor drug, yet had intermediate resistance to penicillin.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0259_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":259,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.7.3 Microbiology Specimen/Microbiology Susceptibility Examples","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 9-10: A test against \"KLEBSIELLA PNEUMONIAE\" from an additional sample at a later time point showed little change in the minimum inhibitory concentration of penicillin, and that the organism was still classified as having intermediate resistance to this drug.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
