{"atom_id":"ig34_p0267_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":267,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.8 Microscopic Findings (MI)","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"In this study, IHC staining for NK2 homeobox 1 (NKX2-1; also known as thyroid transcription factor 1) was reported at a detailed level. Staining intensity of individual cells was assessed on a semi-quantitative scale ranging from 0 to 3+, and the percentage of tumor cells at each staining intensity level was reported. These results were used to calculate the H-score, which ranges from 0 to 300.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:01Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0267_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":267,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.5.8 Microscopic Findings (MI)","atom_type":"LIST_ITEM","verbatim":"Rows 1-4:\tShow the percentage of cells at each H-Score staining intensity.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:01Z"}}
