{"atom_id":"ig34_p0268_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":268,"page_region":"full","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.1 Pharmacokinetics Concentrations (PC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PCTESTCD | Pharmacokinetic Test Short Name | Char | | Topic | Short name of the analyte or specimen characteristic. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in PCTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). PCTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: \"ASA\", \"VOL\", \"SPG\". | Req","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:02Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0268_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":268,"page_region":"full","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.1 Pharmacokinetics Concentrations (PC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"PCTEST | Pharmacokinetic Test Name | Char | | Synonym Qualifier | Name of the analyte or specimen characteristic normally performed by a clinical laboratory is considered a lab test. The value in PCTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: \"Acetylsalicylic Acid\", \"Volume\", \"Specific Gravity\". | Req","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_round5_inline","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:02Z"}}
