{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "STUDYID | Study Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Unique identifier for a study. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "DOMAIN | Domain Abbreviation | Char | PP | Identifier | Two-character abbreviation for the domain. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number. | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Used to tie together a block of related records in a single domain to support relationships within the domain and between domains. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPTESTCD | Parameter Short Name | Char | (PKPARMCD) | Topic | Short name of the pharmacokinetic parameter. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in PPTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). PPTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Examples: \"AUCALL\", \"TMAX\", \"CMAX\". | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPTEST | Parameter Name | Char | (PKPARM) | Synonym Qualifier | Name of the pharmacokinetic parameter. The value in PPTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: \"AUC All\", \"Time of CMAX\", \"Max Conc\". | Req", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPCAT | Parameter Category | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of related records. For PP, this should be the name of the analyte in PCTEST whose profile the parameter is associated with. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a028", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSCAT | Parameter Subcategory | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | Categorization of the model type used to calculate the PK parameters. Examples: \"COMPARTMENTAL\", \"NON-COMPARTMENTAL\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a029", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPORRES | Result or Finding in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Result of the measurement or finding as originally received or collected. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0271_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 271, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPORRESU | Original Units | Char | (PKUNIT) (PKUWG) (PKUWKG) (PKUDMG) (PKUDUG) | Variable Qualifier | Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for PPORRES. Example: \"ng/L\". See PP Assumption 3. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:01:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings, copied or derived from PPORRES in a standard format or standard units. PPSTRESC should store all results or findings in character format; if results are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in PPSTRESN. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSTRESN | Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric results or findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from PPSTRESC. PPSTRESN should store all numeric test results or findings. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (PKUNIT) (PKUWG) (PKUWKG) (PKUDMG) (PKUDUG) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized unit used for PPSTRESC and PPSTRESN. See PP Assumption 3. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate that a parameter was not calculated. Should be null if a result exists in PPORRES. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPREASND | Reason Parameter Not Calculated | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes why a parameter was not calculated, such as \"INSUFFICIENT DATA\". Used in conjunction with PPSTAT when value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSPEC | Specimen Material Type | Char | (SPECTYPE) | Record Qualifier | Defines the type of specimen used for a measurement. If multiple specimen types are used for a calculation (e.g., serum and urine for renal clearance), then this field should be left blank. Examples: \"SERUM\", \"PLASMA\", \"URINE\". | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPANMETH | Analysis Method | Char | (PKANMET) | Record Qualifier | Analysis method applied to obtain a summarized result. Analysis method describes the method of secondary processing applied to a complex observation result. Example: A named formula used to calculate AUC, such as \"LIN-LOG TRAPEZOIDAL METHOD\". Sponsor-defined formulas can also be represented by this variable. Example: Calculating ratio AUCs where the PPANMETH may be \"DRUG METABOLITE 1 TO DRUG PARENT\" or \"DRUG METABOLITE 2 TO METABOLITE 1\". | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "TAETORD | Planned Order of Element within Arm | Num | | Timing | Number that gives the planned order of the element within the arm. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPDTC | Date/Time of Parameter Calculations | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Nominal date/time of parameter calculations. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPDY | Study Day of Parameter Calculations | Num | | Timing | Study day of the collection, in integer days. The algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in the Demographics (DM) domain. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPTPTREF | Time Point Reference | Char | | Timing | The description of a time point that acts as a fixed reference for a series of planned time points. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPRFTDTC | Date/Time of Reference Point | Char | ISO 8601 datetime or interval | Timing | Date/time of the reference time point from the PC records used to calculate a parameter record. The values in PPRFTDTC should be the same as that in PCRFTDTC for related records. | Exp", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPSTINT | Planned Start of Assessment Interval | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | The start of a planned evaluation or assessment interval relative to the time point reference. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "PPENINT | Planned End of Assessment Interval | Char | ISO 8601 duration | Timing | The end of a planned evaluation or assessment interval relative to the time point reference. | Perm", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "NOTE", "verbatim": "\u00b9In this column, an asterisk (*) indicates that the variable may be subject to controlled terminology. CDISC/NCI codelist values are enclosed in parentheses.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "PP \u2013 Assumptions", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. Pharmacokinetics Parameters is a derived dataset, and may be produced from an analysis dataset with a different structure. As a result, some sponsors may need to normalize their analysis dataset in order for it to fit into the SDTM-based PP domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. Information pertaining to all parameters (e.g., number of exponents, model weighting) should be submitted in the SUPPPP dataset.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. There are separate codelists used for PPORRESU/PPSTRESU where the choice depends on whether the value of the pharmacokinetic parameter is normalized.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. Codelist \"PKUNIT\" is used for non-normalized parameters.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. Codelists \"PKUDMG\" and \"PKUDUG\" are used when parameters are normalized by dose amount in milligrams or micrograms, respectively.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0272_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 272, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. Codelists \"PKUWG\" and \"PKUWKG\" are used when parameters are normalized by weight in grams or kilograms, respectively.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:02:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0273_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 273, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. Multiple subset codelists were created for the unique unit expressions of the same concept across codelists. This approach allows study-context appropriate use of unit values for pharmacokinetics (PK) analysis subtypes. Controlled Terminology Rules for PK are available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0273_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 273, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. Any Identifiers, Timing variables, or Findings general observation class qualifiers may be added to the PP domain, but the following qualifiers would not generally be used: --BODSYS, --SEV.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0273_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 273, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "PP \u2013 Examples", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0273_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 273, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 7, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0273_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 273, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.2 Pharmacokinetics Parameters (PP)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows PK parameters calculated from time-concentration profiles for the parent drug and 1 metabolite in plasma and urine for one subject. Note that PPRFTDTC is populated in order to link the PP records to the respective PC records. In this example, PPSPEC is null for observed total clearance (PPTESTCD = \"CLO\") records because it is calculated from multiple specimen sources (i.e., plasma and urine).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:03:00Z"}}
