{"atom_id": "ig34_p0275_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 275, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Note that the reference time point and the analyte are part of the natural key (see Section 3.2.1.1, Primary Keys) for both datasets. In this relationship, --GRPID is a surrogate key, and must be populated so that each combination of analyte and reference time point has a separate value of --GRPID.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["Section 3.2.1.1"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
