{"atom_id": "ig34_p0275_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 275, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This section illustrates 4 methods for representing relationships between PC and PP records under 4 different circumstances. All these examples are based on the same PC and PP data for 1 drug (i.e., drug X).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0275_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 275, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The different methods for representing relationships are based on which linking variables are used in RELREC.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0275_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 275, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "\u00a76.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Method A (many to many, using PCGRPID and PPGRPID)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
