{"atom_id":"ig34_p0279_a034","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":279,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Only some records in PC were used to calculate all pharmacokinetic parameters; time points 8 and 9 on day 1 were not used for any pharmacokinetic parameters.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:04:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0279_a035","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":279,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example uses --GRPID values in the PCGRPID (Example 2) and PPGRPID (Example 2) columns. Note that for the 2 excluded PC records, PCGRPID = \"EXCLUDE\"; for other PC records, PCGRPID = \"DY1_DRGX\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:04:00Z"}}
