{"atom_id":"ig34_p0280_a035","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":280,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"Only some records in PC were used to calculate some parameters; time points 8 and 9 on day 1 were not used for half-life calculations, but were used for other parameters.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0280_a036","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":280,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"This example uses --GRPID values in the PCGRPID (Example 3) and PPGRPID (Example 3) columns. Note that the 2 excluded PC records have PCGRPID = \"DY1_DRGX_B\"; the other PC records have PCGRPID = \"DY1_DRGX_A\". Note also that the PP records for half-life calculations have PPGRPID = \"DYDRGX_HALF\", whereas the other PP records have PPGRPID = \"DY1DRGX_A\".","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0280_a037","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":280,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records","atom_type":"SENTENCE","verbatim":"All pharmacokinetic concentrations for day 8 were used to calculate all pharmacokinetic parameters. Because day 8 relationships are the same as in Example 1, they are not included here.","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.2","ts":"2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0280_a038", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 280, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records — Example 3", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Method A (Many to Many, Using PCGRPID and PPGRPID)", "heading_level": 7, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0280_a039", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 280, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records — Example 3", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-3: The relationship with RELID \"1\" includes all PC records with PCGRPID = \"DY1_DRGX_A\", all PC records with PCGRPID = \"DY1_DRGX_B\" (which in this case is all the PP records for Day 1) and all PP records with PPGRPID = \"DYIDRGX_A\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0280_a040", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 280, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.9.3 Relating PP Records to PC Records — Example 3", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 4-6: The relationship with RELID \"2\" includes only PC records with PCGRPID = \"DY1_DRGX_A\" and all PP records with PPGRPID = \"DYIDRGX_HALF\".", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:05:00Z"}}
